{[%evp 0,131,29,-19,26,19,12,12,12,14,31,30,29,30,39,6,1,-16,-23,-23,-47,-47,-47,-46,-30,-30,-30,-61,-55,-48,-48,-53,-53,-53,-53,-53,-34,-124,-86,-86,-63,-71,-71,-71,-67,-59,-73,-52,-54,-59,-27,-33,-33,-57,-63,-55,-38,-38,-62,-31,0,0,92,98,121,71,98,79,69,69,69,70,58,58,90,99,99,99,131,91,193,208,224,224,219,217,219,224,238,223,244,217,239,227,258,286,275,275,275,275,287,287,287,287,300,262,300,292,292,268,350,123,123,123,126,134,132,128,130,127,207,188,408,399,833,972,1229,1237,1292,1314,1334,1431,1576,1720] I had lost the previous game due to a stupid blunder, so I was hoping to fix my mistake today! Also previously I had never won in a must-win situation in the World Cup before, so I was looking forward to changing my destiny!!} 1. e4 {This looked like an interesting choice!} c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 g6 6. f3 Bg7 {I wasn't expecting this, now I realized that high chances for the game to end in a draw :)!} 7. Be3 $5 {[%cal Gg5d8] I managed to pull myself together and found a line where I couldn't see any clear way to forced equality!} Nc6 8. Qd2 O-O {Greedy VD :), I couldn't believe that he wanted to win the d5-pawn :).} 9. Bc4 {[%cal Gb3d5] I wanted to fight for my equal rights :).} Rb8 10. O-O-O (10. h4) 10... Bd7 11. g4 {[%csl Gd1] I felt the king is doing fine on d1, due to the shelter provided by the d4-pawn.} Na5 (11... b5 12. Bb3 Ne5 13. h4 Nc4 14. Bxc4 bxc4) 12. Bb3 b5 13. Bh6 $5 {[%csl Yb4][%cal Gh1e1] The computer didn't like this decision, but to be honest I don't think it understood my play for quite a while :) in this game!} Bxh6 (13... e5 14. Nf5) 14. Qxh6 {Trying to remove the bishop from the a5-e1 diagonal, so that I can prepare Re1.} b4 (14... Nxb3+ 15. Nxb3 Rc8 16. h4 Qc7 17. Rd2 b4 18. Nd5 Nxd5 19. exd5 f6 20. h5 g5 21. f4 Qc4 22. fxg5 Qe4 23. Rhd1 Qe3 24. Nd4 Bxg4 25. Ne6 Bxe6) 15. Nd5 Nxb3+ 16. Nxb3 {[%cal Ga4a5,Ga4e8,Gh1e1] GO BACK SIMON!} Nxd5 (16... e5) 17. exd5 Rb6 18. h4 $3 {[%cal Ge8d8,Gc2b1] I was very proud of this move! My main concern was the king's safety and If I can get it to safety then I can play for attack without any concern!} (18. Rhe1 e5) 18... e5 {I was happy to see this, as I felt the king would be nicely placed on d8! On the kingside, I can create some play against his majesty!} 19. Nd2 {Now that my king is safe, it is time to begin the onslaught!} (19. dxe6) 19... Qe7 (19... Ra6 20. Ne4 f5 21. Ng5 (21. h5 fxe4 22. hxg6 Qe7 23. fxe4) 21... Qe7 22. h5 Rf6 23. Kb1 (23. hxg6 Rxg6 24. Qxh7+ Qxh7 25. Nxh7 b3 26. a3 bxc2 27. Rd2 Ra5 28. g5) 23... Qg7 24. Qxg7+ (24. hxg6 Qxh6 25. Rxh6 Rxg6 26. Rxh7 Be8 27. Rdh1 Rxg5 28. Rh8+) 24... Kxg7 25. h6+ Kg8 26. Rhf1 Rb6 27. b3 Rb8 (27... a5) 28. f4 e4 29. Rd4 a5 30. Re1 Rc8 31. Kb2 Rff8 (31... Bb5) 32. gxf5 gxf5 33. Rg1 Kh8 34. Rc4) 20. Ne4 (20. g5 f5 (20... Bf5 21. h5 Qc7 22. Ne4 Bxe4 23. fxe4 Rb7) 21. h5 Be8 {with an equal game for Black and I felt my chances to win in this position were rather slim due to Black's central passed pawn.} {Of course, people might have expected to see my recent favorite with} 22. Rh4 Rb5 23. Nc4 f4 24. Rhh1 Qc7 25. Nd2 gxh5 26. Ne4 Bg6 27. Rxh5 Rc5 28. Rh2 Rc8 (28... Rc4 29. Rdh1 Qg7 30. Nxd6 Qxh6 31. gxh6 Rd4 32. Re1 Rxd5 33. Nc4 Re8 34. Rhe2) 29. Nxc5 Qxc5 30. Rdh1 Qxd5) (20. Rdg1 f6 (20... Kh8 21. Kb1) 21. Ne4 Qg7 22. Qe3 Kh8 23. Kb1 Bb5 24. Qd2 Qc7 25. b3 a5 26. g5 f5 27. h5 fxe4 28. hxg6 exf3 29. Qf2 Rb7 30. Rxh7+ Qxh7 31. gxh7) 20... f5 21. gxf5 {I have a clear target... The Black king!!} gxf5 {I was happy to see this, as I felt it was going to take some effort to win the fight for the key open file!} (21... Bxf5 22. h5 Qg7 {also looks bad.} 23. Qe3 {looked very interesting and it was a complete mess after} (23. Qd2 Bxe4 {I wasn't sure who was better here, but at least my king was kind of safe on d1 for the time being.} 24. fxe4 {was another line, But I didn't like} g5 25. h6 Qg6 $1 {An important check, not wasting time retreating the queen.}) 23... Bxe4 24. Qxe4 Qh6+ 25. Kb1 gxh5) 22. Rhg1+ Kh8 {This I felt weakens his king even more!} 23. Rg6 {[%csl Rg8][%cal Gf3e4] Firmly stopping the pawn advance and Black is left with too many weaknesses to defend.} fxe4 24. Rdg1 $1 {[%cal Rb5b7,Gb5e5,Gc1e1] A very nice preparing the deadly Re1 and also trying to provoke a6!} Qf7 25. Kb1 $1 {Continuing the act of provocation, I guess VD didn't understand what I was up to... (In my defence I also didn't know myself :), neither does the computer :)).} (25. Rg7 Qf4+ (25... Qf5 26. Rxh7+ Qxh7 {looked horrible for me with a winning attack for Black.} 27. Qxf8+) 26. Qxf4 exf4 {Surprisingly Black is going to find out that the attack is very difficult to defend against...while the bishop and the pawns are silent spectators!} {I rejected} 27. Rxd7 {due to} exf3 $1 {I didn't want to allow the bishop to come back! (of course stupid comp doesn't understand this simple concept and recommends 25.Re1!)} (27... Rg8 $1 28. Rxg8+ Kxg8 29. fxe4) 28. Rgg7 Re8 {[%csl Rb6,Rb7][%cal Gb3b7] Now the b6-bishop will constantly need the supervision of the queen!} {My original intention was} 29. Rxh7+ {but then thought that Black can go} Kg8 $1 {Just like my king which is very safe thanks to the d-pawn as a shelter...Black can also do the same :)!} 30. Rdg7+ Kf8 {[%cal Gc8c7,Gd8b8] followed by Rc7 and Kc8 if needed!} 31. Rxa7 {was safer maybe} Kg8 $1 32. Rag7+ Kf8 {[%csl Ya4,Yc6][%cal Gb3a4] Black queen can't stop Qa4 anymore!} 33. Rf7+ Kg8 $1 {[%csl Ga4][%cal Ga4a5,Gh1e1]} 34. Rhg7+ Kh8 {Now the situation is completely different, but still I wasn't sure and wanted to avoid this if possible :).} {My first intention was} 35. Rg4 {to continue to bully the bishop but...}) 25... exf3 26. Rg7 Bf5 27. Rxf7 Rxf7 28. Rf1 {Forcing e3!} Be4 (28... Bh3 {[%cal Ge7b4] was the way to fight!} 29. Rf2 e4 {The king is a bit safer here than on h8 still, it should be very good for white...But I felt the game continuation was stronger!}) 29. Qe6 $1 {[%cal Gf1f7] Finally the plan is clear, I am going to play for domination and Black's pawns are useless :)!} Bg6 30. Kc1 $1 {[%cal Gd1g4,Gg4h5] The queen is coming to h5 or g4 with a lot of destructive power!} (30. h5 Bxh5 31. Qh3 (31. Rg1 Rb8 {I was very happy to pull off this epic win taking the match into tiebreaks! Winning in a must-win situation always gives you special happiness and also I was proud of the level I showed in this game :)!} 32. Qxd6 Re8 33. Qc5 Bg6 34. d6 e4 {[%cal Gb4b8] and the queenside pawn shall promote :)!}) 31... Bg6 32. Rxf3 Rxf3 33. Qxf3 {I will win the bishop for the a-pawn and then collect the d4-pawn leading to a win.}) 30... Kg7 {Panic! This only prolongs the inevitable :)!} 31. Kd2 (31. Qh3 h5 {[%csl Gd5] A dominating post for the queen!} (31... e4 32. h5 Bf5 $1 {I just wanted to get this move in to avoid any saving chances for Black!} 33. Qh4 h6 {[%csl Yd4,Gg6][%cal Ge4g6,Ge4d3] The endgame is easily winning due to the same diagonal principle where the bishop supports the pawn and also stops the enemy passed pawn!} 34. Rg1+ Kh7 {I just had to make sure not to blunder like in the first game :)!} 35. Qd8 Rg7 36. Rxg7+ Kxg7 37. Qe7+ Kg8 38. Kd2) 32. Rxf3 Rxf3 33. Qxf3) 31... Rf4 (31... h5 32. Rg1 (32. Ke3 Rf6 33. Qh3 e4) 32... Rf6 $1 {[%cal Gh3h7,Gh3h2] A cute retreat winning the h7-pawn.} 33. Qe7+ Rf7 34. Qe6 {I already saw that the bishop endgame was winning, but wanted to get it in the most ideal scenario and also felt maybe I can win keeping the queens on the board!} Rf6) 32. Ke3 $3 {[%csl Gh1][%cal Ge2d3] Keeping the rooks at any cost!! I think VD didn't expect this epic rook move which keeps the tension and now things are hopeless for Black!} Rf6 33. Qd7+ {Preparing Re1, if the rook joins the fight then it's over!} Rf7 {[%csl Gd3][%cal Gd1h5] Desperately trying to stop the rook from getting activated!} 34. Qh3 Bxc2 (34... b3 {Time to improve the pawn structure and create a mating net around the black king!} 35. h5 Bf5 {[%csl Rh8]} 36. Qh4) 35. Rg1+ {One step at a time! c1 is better than h1.} (35. Qg4+ Bg6 (35... Kf8 {Keeping the king locked in!} 36. Qc8+) 36. h5) 35... Bg6 36. h5 {[%csl Gd3][%cal Gd1d3] Now the queen has to retreat to stop Qd7 penetration.} f2 {An error allowing me to get what I wanted!} 37. Rf1 $1 {[%cal Gb4f8,Gd1e1] Attacking the rook and preparing Re1!} Bc2 (37... Bf5 38. h6+ {[%csl Rb7] This was the idea behind Qb5, now Rf8 loses the b7-pawn!} Kf8 39. Qh4 Ke8 40. Rxf2 {Channeling Greedy VD against the Master :)!}) 38. h6+ {Now f-file is equally destructive!} Kg6 39. Qg4+ $1 {[%cal Gb5h5] Preparing to go Qh5 and Rf7.} 1-0


