{[%evp 0,111,19,29,23,12,37,14,-4,4,9,5,-21,-26,-4,-67,-22,-41,-28,-2,-12,-35,-30,-1,36,-37,-25,-40,-26,-13,13,-18,-18,-18,-18,-15,-30,-19,-35,-47,-37,-62,4,-16,-7,-20,-20,12,-14,-49,-5,-47,-5,6,14,-36,-57,-97,-23,-23,40,45,43,21,45,-8,86,0,-1,2,22,0,0,0,1,-17,-15,0,0,0,0,0,27,21,12,39,40,42,42,16,42,43,43,0,43,35,33,540,839,934,1022,1032,1075,1092,1105,1122,1157,1281,1283,1330,1330,1300,1894,1894]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. Nf3 Bg7 5. cxd5 $5 {A reversed Schmid-Benoni! To be honest, I had never seen it.} Nxd5 6. e4 Nxc3 7. bxc3 c5 8. Rb1 O-O {The most solid move.} 9. Be2 cxd4 10. cxd4 Qa5+ 11. Bd2 Qxa2 12. O-O b6 13. Qc1 Bb7 14. Bc4 Qa4 15. Bb5 Qa2 16. Re1 Rc8 17. Qd1 Qc2 18. Qe2 Nc6 (18... Qc7) 19. Bd3 (19. e5 Nd8 20. Bd7 Rcb8 21. h4 Bd5 22. Rbc1 Qa2 23. Ng5 h6 24. Nh3 Ne6 25. Qe3 Rd8) (19. Rec1 Qa2 20. Bc4 Nxd4 21. Nxd4 Rxc4 22. Qxc4 Qxd2 23. Nc6 Qd7 24. Qd5 Bxc6 25. Rxc6 Qxd5 26. exd5 Be5 (26... Bd4) 27. Kf1 Bd6 28. Ra1) (19. d5 Nd4 20. Nxd4 Bxd4) 19... Qa2 {Here as well Black has more than enough compensation!} 20. Bc4 (20. Ra1 Qb2 (20... Qb3 21. Reb1 Qe6 22. d5) 21. Ra4 (21. Reb1 Nxd4) 21... Qb3 (21... b5 22. Bxb5 a5) 22. Rea1 Nd8 23. R4a3 (23. Rxa7 Ne6) 23... Qe6 24. Rxa7 Rxa7 (24... Qd6 25. Be3 Nc6) 25. Rxa7 Qd6 (25... Ra8 26. Rxa8 Bxa8 27. h3 Qa2 28. Kh2 Qb2 29. d5 Nb7 30. Qe3 Nc5 31. Qf4) 26. Be3 e6 27. Qb2) 20... Qa4 21. Bb3 (21. Ra1 Qc2 22. Ra2 Nxd4 23. Rxc2 Nxe2+ 24. Rxe2 Rxc4 25. Rxc4 Ba6) 21... Qa3 (21... Qa6 22. Qe3 Na5 (22... e6 23. d5 exd5 24. Bxd5 (24. exd5 Na5) 24... Na5 25. Qa3 Bxd5 26. exd5 Rc5 27. d6 Qc8 28. Qd3 Qc6 29. d7 Rd8 30. Bb4 Nb7 31. Rbd1) (22... Rf8 23. Ra1 Na5 (23... Qb5 24. Rec1) 24. Reb1 e6 (24... Rac8 25. Bd1) 25. Bd1 Bc6 26. Be2 Qc8 27. Ne5 (27. Bxa5 bxa5 28. Rxa5 Rb8)) 23. Bxf7+ Kxf7 24. Ng5+ Kg8 (24... Ke8 25. Qh3 Bxd4 26. Qxh7 b5 27. Bxa5 Qf6 28. Red1) 25. Qh3 h6 26. Ne6 (26. Qe6+ Kh8 27. Re3 (27. Nf7+ Kh7 28. Bxh6 b5 (28... Qc4 29. d5) 29. Qh3 Kg8 30. Bxg7 Kxg7 31. Ng5 Rh8 32. Qd7 Qf6 33. Ne6+ Kf7 34. d5) 27... b5 28. Nf7+ (28. Bxa5 Rc6 29. Nf7+ Kh7 30. Ng5+ Kh8) 28... Kh7 29. Ng5+ Kh8 30. Nf7+ Kh7 31. Ng5+)) 22. Bxf7+ (22. e5 e6 23. d5 exd5 24. Bxd5 Nd4 (24... Nd8) 25. Bxf7+ Kxf7 26. Nxd4 Qa2 27. Qg4 Kg8) 22... Kxf7 23. Qc4+ e6 24. Ng5+ Ke8 25. Nxe6 (25. Qxe6+ Qe7 26. Qg8+ Bf8) 25... Qe7 26. Nxg7+ (26. d5 Nd4 (26... Ne5 27. Qb3) 27. Qa4+ b5 28. Rxb5 Nxb5 29. Qxb5+ Kf7 30. Nxg7 (30. Ng5+ Kg8 31. d6 Qxd6 32. Qxb7 Qc6 33. Qf7+ Kh8 34. Qb3 h6 35. Nf7+ Kh7 36. Qh3 h5 37. Ng5+) 30... Kxg7 31. d6 Qxd6 32. Qxb7+ Qc7 33. Bc3+ Kh6 34. Bd2+ Kg7) 26... Qxg7 27. Bc3 $2 (27. Qe6+ Qe7 (27... Ne7 28. d5) 28. Qg8+ Kd7 29. Qc4 Ke8 30. Qg8+ Kd7 31. Qc4 Ke8 32. Qa4 Kf7 33. Qb3+ Kg7 34. Bc3) 27... Nd8 $1 (27... Nxd4 28. Qxd4 Qxd4 29. Bxd4 Rc4 30. Ba1 Bc6) 28. Qb3 Rc7 $2 (28... Rxc3 29. Qxc3 Ne6 30. Rbd1 Rd8) 29. Ba1 Rac8 30. d5 Qd7 31. Qb2 Qe7 32. Rbd1 (32. Qh8+ Qf8 33. Qe5+ Qe7 (33... Re7 34. Qd4)) 32... Nf7 (32... Rc2 33. Qh8+ Qf8 34. d6 Bc6 35. d7+ Bxd7 36. Qxf8+ Kxf8 37. Rxd7 R2c7 38. Rd5) 33. e5 Rc2 34. Qb5+ {Suddenly, it's unclear who is playing for a win!} Qd7 (34... Kf8 35. e6 Nd6 36. Qb3) 35. Qxd7+ Kxd7 36. e6+ Kd6 37. exf7 (37. Bf6 Ng5 (37... Nh6 38. Be5+ Ke7 39. d6+ Kxe6 40. Bg7+) (37... R2c7 38. Bh4 Rc4 39. Bg3+ Ke7 40. exf7+ Kxf7 41. d6 Re8 42. f4) 38. Be5+ (38. Bxg5 Bxd5) 38... Kc5 (38... Ke7 39. d6+ Kxe6 40. d7) 39. e7 Bxd5 40. e8=Q Rxe8 41. Bd4+ Kd6 42. Rxe8) 37... Rf8 38. Re6+ Kd7 39. Rf6 Re2 40. f4 {Unbelievably enough, Black never took a decision to swap queens. True, it was hard to see Levon's winning idea coming.} (40. Bc3 Re7 41. Bb4 Rexf7 42. Rd6+ Kc8) (40. Rf3 Re7 41. Ra3 a6 42. Bd4 Rexf7 43. Bxb6 Rf5) 40... Re7 41. Be5 Rexf7 42. Rd6+ Ke8 $2 (42... Ke7 43. Re1 Rd8) 43. Re1 (43. Ra1) 43... Re7 44. Rc1 Rff7 45. Bf6 Rd7 46. Re6+ Kf8 $4 47. d6 $3 {Finally Levon has got what he wanted, and it's a masterpiece! He's going to queen one of his queenside pawns, as Black is totally paralysed on the kingside, while his bishop is stuck on c2!} Kg8 (47... a5) 48. h4 Rf8 49. Bg5 (49. Rc7 $132 Rxc7 {went very well for Black in another game:} 50. dxc7 Kf7 51. Rd6 Rc8 52. Bd8 b5 $1 53. Rd7+ Kg8 $1 54. Bf6 a5 $15 {0-1 (39) Agayev,N (2350)-Stupak,K (2586) Baku AZE 2017} 55. Kf2 $5 {and then c2 might be the right solution} a4 56. Ke3 a3 57. Kd4) 49... Kf7 (49... Kg7 $36 50. h5) 50. Rce1 (50. Re7+ Rxe7 $15 51. Bxe7 $6 Rc8 $17 52. Rd1 $1 {in order to play Ra3, or answer Nxd3 or Bxd3 with Rd2, was perhaps what White had to do.} Ke8 53. d7+ Kxe7 54. dxc8=Q Bxc8 55. Ra1 {would give Black full compensation for the pawn.} a5 56. Rb1 Kd6 57. Rxb6+ Kc5 58. Rb8 Be6) 50... Bc6 51. h5 (51. Re7+ Kg8 52. Rc1 Rxd6 53. Rc7 Bd7 $1 $19 {Some timid move like} 54. Be7 {was better. The a4-pawn is hanging, by the way...} Rd4 $5 55. Bxf8 Kxf8 56. Rxa7 h5 57. Rcc7 Ke7 $15 58. Rab7 $5 Rd6 59. g4) 51... a5 (51... gxh5 $11 52. Re7+ $5 Kg8 53. Rc1 Rxd6 54. Rc7 $11 Be4 $1 55. Be7 Rg6 56. Bxf8 $8 Kxf8 57. Rd1 Ke8 {would surely have brought Black the full point.} 58. Re1 Kd8) 52. Re7+ (52. hxg6+ hxg6 53. Re7+ Kg8) 52... Kg8 53. hxg6 hxg6 (53... Rxd6 {and White wins!} 54. gxh7+ $11 {But} Kh8 {was an easy draw:} 55. R7e6 (55. R1e6 $11 Rxe6) 55... Rxe6 56. Rxe6 Ba8 57. Rxb6 Kxh7 58. Ra6) 54. R1e6 Rf7 55. Rxg6+ Kh7 56. Rh6+ {A tough one for Vidit!} Kg7 $5 57. Ree6 (57. Ree6 Rf8 58. g4 (58. Reg6+ Kf7 59. f5 $18)) (57. g4 $1 $11) ({It's now too late for} 57. f5 $4 Rdxe7 58. dxe7 {because of} Be8 $3 59. g4) 1-0


