{Diagram [#] In this game Vidit had huge advantage in the early phase of the game. However, he missed several chances and the game was likely to end in a draw. He played} 1. c4 {thinking that it is a draw in any case.} c6 $3 {Quite unexpected turn of events. Black cannot stop the passed pawn, and if Black captures...} 2. Nf3 {Diagram [#]} d5 $1 {Now, Black is completely lost and has no available tricks. Levon won the game in few more moves.} 3. Qb3 (3. d4 Nf6 4. e3 Bg4 5. Nc3 e6 6. h3 Bh5 7. g4 Bg6 8. cxd5 Nxd5 9. Ne5 Bb4 10. Bd2 Nd7 11. Nxg6 hxg6 12. a3 Ba5 13. Bg2 g5 14. Qc2 Rc8 15. Rd1 Bc7 16. Ne2 Nf8 17. Qb3 Rb8 18. e4 Nf4 19. Bxf4 Bxf4 20. h4 e5 21. d5 Ng6 22. dxc6 Qa5+ 23. Nc3 O-O 24. cxb7 Qc7 25. Nd5 Qxb7 26. Qxb7 Rxb7 27. b4 gxh4 28. Bf1 Bg5 29. Rh3 Rd8 30. Bc4 Rbb8 31. Rhd3 Rdc8 32. Bb3 Rb7) 3... d4 (3... Nf6) 4. e3 c5 5. Qb5+ Nc6 6. Qxc5 e5 7. Qb5 a6 8. Qb3 Bc5 (8... Nf6 9. d3 (9. exd4 e4 10. d5 exf3 11. dxc6 Bc5 12. cxb7 (12. d4 Bxd4 13. Be3 Ng4) 12... Qe7+ 13. Qe3 Bxe3 14. bxa8=Q Bd4+ 15. Kd1 O-O 16. gxf3 Bb7 17. Qxf8+ Kxf8) 9... Bb4+ 10. Bd2 Bxd2+ 11. Nbxd2 dxe3 12. fxe3 Ng4) 9. d3 Nf6 10. e4 O-O 11. Be2 Bb4+ 12. Nbd2 a5 13. O-O Nd7 14. Qd1 Bd6 15. Ne1 (15. Nb1 Nc5 16. Na3 f5 17. exf5 Bxf5 18. Nb5 Bb8 19. b3 Nb4 20. Ba3 Ra6) 15... Nc5 16. Nb3 Na6 (16... Ne6 17. Bg4 a4 18. Nd2) 17. Nd2 Nc5 18. Nb3 Na6 19. Nd2 1-0


