9. Nd3) (14... Ne4 15. Bxe7 Qxe7 16. f3 Nd6 17. Rc1 Nf5 18. Qd2 Qh4 19. Rcd1 c5 20. Nxc5 Nxd4 21. g3 Qe7 22. b4) 15. Bxf6 $40 Bxf6 $5 16. Nc5 (16. Rc1) 16... Re8 17. Qc2 Rc7 18. f4 Bc8 19. Re3 $11 {was also not very convincing for White, although once more, Duda won: 1-0 (75) Duda,J (2753)-Harikrishna,P (2719) chess24.com 2020.} Qd6 20. Rae1 Rce7 21. Rc3 Rc7 22. Rc1) (12... a6 13. Ba4 (13. Bxc6 Bxc6 14. Qb3 Qd6 15. Re3 Bd8 16. Bf4 Nh5 17. Nxc6 Nxf4 18. Ne5) (13. Bd3 Be6) 13... Be6 (13... Re8) 14. Bxc6 bxc6 15. Na4 h6 16. Bxf6 Bxf6 17. Rc1 Re8 18. Nc5) 13. Rc1 {Anyway!} (13. a3 a6 14. Ba4 b5 15. Bc2 Be6 16. Re3 Nxe5 17. Rxe5 h6 18. Bh4 Nd7) 13... a6 {Leitao,Rafael: 'Diagram [#]'} 14. Bxc6 $1 Bxc6 15. Qf3 Qd6 (15... h6 16. Bh4 Qb6) (15... Qb6 16. Bxf6 $18 {1-0 (30) Duda,J (2734)-Moussard,J (2608) chess24.com 2020} Bxf6 17. Nxd5 Bxd5 18. Qxd5 Bxe5 19. Qxe5 Rxe5 20. Rxc8+) 16. h3 $5 {Leitao,Rafael: '!' A typical but excellent pawn sacrifice.} (16. Re3 Bd7 (16... h6 17. Bh4 Bd7 18. Nxd7 Qxd7 19. Rce1 b5 20. Bxf6 Bxf6 21. Nxd5 Bxd4 22. Rd1 Qa7) 17. Nxd7 Qxd7 18. Rce1 h6 19. Bxf6 Bxf6 20. Nxd5 Bxd4 21. Rd1) 16... Bd8 (16... h6 17. Bh4 Qb4 $19) (16... Qb4 {Leitao,Rafael: '- 12/86'} 17. Re3 Qxb2 (17... Qd6) (17... Qxd4 18. Rce1 Bb5 (18... Bd6 19. Bxf6 gxf6 20. Qxf6) (18... Bd8 19. Nxc6 Rxe3 20. Bxe3) (18... Kf8 19. Qf5 g6 20. Qf3 $5 Kg7 $2 (20... a5 $5) 21. Nxc6 $16 {1-0 (30) Sjugirov,S (2650)-Cheparinov,I (2710) Riyadh 2017} bxc6 22. Rxe7 $44) (18... Qc5 19. Nxc6 Rxc6 (19... bxc6 20. Bxf6 gxf6 21. Qh5) 20. Bxf6 Rxf6 21. Qxd5 $1 Qxd5 {Leitao,Rafael} 22. Nxd5 Re6 23. Rxe6 fxe6 24. Rxe6) 19. Nxb5 axb5 20. Bxf6 Bxf6 21. Qxf6 $11 {Again Duda got no advantage, but he seems to love this line anyway! 0-1 (51) Duda,J (2737)-So,W (2780) chess.com 2018} gxf6 $5 22. Rg3+ Kf8 (22... Kh8 23. Nxf7#) 23. Nd7#) 18. Rb1 Qa3 19. Nxc6 bxc6 20. Rbe1 Qd6 21. Bxf6 gxf6 (21... Qxf6 22. Qxf6) 22. Qh5) 17. Re3 Rf8 $8 18. Rce1 {Leitao,Rafael: ''} Qb4 (18... Nd7) 19. Qf5 Ra8 $2 20. Rd1 $1 {Now it's over.} (20. Bh6 gxh6 (20... g6 21. Bxf8 gxf5 22. Bxb4 (22. Z0 $19)) 21. Qf4 Kh8 22. a3 (22. Qxh6 Ng8 (22... Z0)) 22... Qxb2 (22... Qe7 23. Ng6+ (23. Z0 $13)) (22... Qd6 $2 {Leitao,Rafael} 23. Nxf7+ $1) 23. Qxh6 Qxa3 (23... Ng8) 24. Rg3 Ne8 25. Ne4 Qe7 (25... Qb4 26. Nc5 $15 {0-1 (27) Hauke,C (2295)-Schlindwein,R (2440) Germany 1996} Qxe1+ $5 {looks to me like better move - simply answering c1 in a funny way and preventing xe4.} 27. Kh2 {Leitao,Rafael}) 26. Nf6) 20... Ne8 (20... Qxb2 21. Rb1 Qa3 22. Nxc6 bxc6 23. Ne4 (23. Nxd5 $6 Qd6) 23... Qxa2 24. Nxf6+ Bxf6 25. Bxf6 gxf6 26. Rg3+ {and Black's position is awful.}) (20... Kh8) 21. Bf4 Nf6 (21... Nd6 {Leitao,Rafael} 22. Nxc6 bxc6 23. Qd7 $16 Nc4 $16 24. Re8 Ba5 25. Rxa8 Rxa8 26. Qxc6) (21... f6 22. Qe6+ Kh8 $16 23. Nf7+ {Leitao,Rafael} Rxf7 24. Qxf7 $1 $146) 22. Rg3 {Leitao,Rafael: '!'} Kh8 (22... Qe7 23. Qg5 g6 (23... Ne8 24. Qxe7 Bxe7 25. Nxc6 bxc6 $14 26. Na4) 24. Qh6) (22... g6 23. Bh6 Re8 24. Nxg6 $14 hxg6 $5 25. Rxg6+ fxg6 (25... Kh8 $1 26. Bg7+ Kh7 $1 {would also be great for White.} 27. Rg3+ Kg8 $132 28. Bxf6+ $13 {Leitao,Rafael}) 26. Qxg6+) 23. Rdd3 Be8 24. a3 (24. Rxg7 Kxg7 25. Rg3+ (25. Nc6 bxc6 26. Rg3+ Kh8 27. Be5 Qe7 28. Qg5 Rg8 29. Qxg8#) 25... Kh8 26. Nc6 Bxc6 $44 27. Be5 Qe7 28. Qg5) 24... Qxb2 (24... Qb6 {Leitao,Rafael} 25. Rxg7 Kxg7 26. Bh6+ $1 Kxh6 (26... Kh8 27. Bxf8) 27. Rg3 $16 Nh5 28. Ng4+ Kg7 29. Nf6+ Nxg3 30. Qg5+ Kh8 31. Qh6 Bxf6 32. Qxf8# $16) 25. Rxg7 Kxg7 26. Rg3+ {Leitao,Rafael: '#' Allowing mate on the board is usually a sign of respect! What a crushing game by Artemiev.} Kh8 27. Nxd5 (27. Bh6 {[%cal Rg1g8]} Rg8 28. Nxd5 Rxg3 29. Nxf6 $18 Rg6 30. Nxg6+ hxg6 $4 31. Qe5) 27... Nxd5 28. Bh6 Bf6 (28... Rg8 $18 29. Rxg8+ $5 Kxg8 $6 30. Qg4+ $18 {The c4-pawn is lost.}) 29. Qxf6+ $5 (29. Bxf8 $18 {Leitao,Rafael} Qc1+ {was better, but after} 30. Kh2 {or 20.Nc5, Black's position remains awful.} Qf4) 29... Nxf6 30. Bg7+ Kg8 31. Bxf6# $18 1-0


