{Diagram [#] In this game Vidit was holding comfortably. However, Fabiano was ahead on time while Vidit thought a lot and was playing on seconds for most of the game. Fabiano finally managed to get into 2 bishops vs knight endgame which he won without any mistakes. I am not sure if Fabiano studied this kind of endgame, or he won by playing it over the board. Either way it is impressive. Fabiano offered a really funny reason that he had to use the restroom!!} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. e3 e6 5. Nf3 Nbd7 6. Bd3 dxc4 7. Bxc4 b5 8. Bd3 Bd6 9. O-O a6 (9... O-O) 10. e4 e5 (10... c5 11. e5 cxd4 12. exf6 dxc3 13. fxg7 Rg8 14. Be4) 11. Ne2 (11. Bg5 h6 (11... exd4 12. Nxd4 Ne5 13. Bc2 Bg4 14. f3 Bc5 15. Nce2 Be6 16. Kh1 Bc4 17. Nf5 O-O 18. Qe1) 12. Bh4 O-O 13. Rc1 (13. Bc2) 13... Re8 14. a3 Ra7 15. Bb1 Bb8 16. Re1 exd4 17. Qxd4 Ne5) (11. Kh1 exd4 12. Nxd4 Ne5 13. Be2 Bc5 14. Nb3 Qxd1 15. Nxd1 Bb6 16. f3 Be6) (11. Bc2 O-O 12. Bg5 h6 13. Bh4 exd4 (13... Re8) 14. Qxd4 Qe7 15. Rad1 Bc7 16. e5 Bxe5 (16... Nxe5 17. Rfe1 Nxf3+ 18. gxf3 Be6 19. Ne4) 17. Nxe5 Qxe5 18. Qd3 Qh5 19. Bg3) (11. a4) 11... c5 (11... O-O 12. Qc2 (12. a4 Bb7) (12. Be3) 12... c5 13. dxe5 Nxe5 14. Nxe5 Bxe5 15. Rd1 Qc7 16. Ng3 c4 17. Be2 Bb7 18. Bf3 Rfe8 19. Re1 Nd7) 12. d5 (12. dxe5 Nxe5 13. Nxe5 Bxe5 14. f4 Bd4+ 15. Kh1 Bb7) 12... c4 13. Bc2 O-O 14. Ng3 Re8 15. Nh4 Nc5 16. Nhf5 Bf8 17. Qf3 h6 18. Bd2 Nb7 19. b3 Bxf5 20. Nxf5 Nd6 21. Nxd6 {#} Qxd6 $5 22. bxc4 Rec8 23. Rfc1 (23. Bb3 bxc4 24. Ba4 (24. Bc2 c3 25. Be3 Rab8) 24... c3 25. Bxc3 Nxe4 26. Bc6 Nxc3 27. Bxa8 e4 28. Qe3 Rc4) 23... Rxc4 24. Bd3 Rcc8 (24... Rcc8 25. Qh3 Qd7 26. Qg3 Qd6) 1-0


