{[%evp 0,70,16,-12,13,12,15,-21,-11,-5,13,0,8,-12,2,-28,-24,-18,-21,-7,1,-48,-49,-78,-88,-85,-81,-76,-67,-67,-69,-62,-91,-75,-36,-97,-80,-68,-70,-102,-107,-103,-99,-145,-152,-184,-127,-108,-105,-82,-80,-157,-157,-200,-211,-200,-197,-197,-196,-181,-201,-354,-445,-828,-847,-1043,-1050,-1050,-1069,-1074,-1074,-1272,-1258]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Bg5 dxc4 5. e4 b5 6. a4 c6 $1 7. Nc3 b4 8. Nb1 {A positional pawn sacrifice to gain two tempi as compensation.} Ba6 $1 9. e5 h6 $1 {A very important move. Black prepares ...d7 / ...c8 to defend the strong c4-knight.} 10. Bxf6 $6 {A straightforward continuation, but regaining the pawn is better and equalises the game.} gxf6 $1 11. exf6 c5 (11... Qxf6) (11... Qd5 12. Qc2 c5 13. Nbd2 cxd4 14. Bxc4 Bxc4 15. Qxc4 (15. Nxc4 d3 16. Qc1 Qe4+ 17. Ne3 Nd7 18. Nd2) 15... Qxc4 16. Nxc4 Nd7 17. Rc1 Nxf6 18. Nxd4 Bg7 19. Ke2 O-O 20. Ne3) 12. Nbd2 c3 (12... Nc6 13. Bxc4 $132 Bxc4 $6 {xf6 is not a real threat, so this move makes no sense.} 14. Nxc4 $1 Qxf6 15. a5 $17 {1/2 (62) Kalashian,D (2451)-Petrosian,D (2501) Yerevan 2010} (15. Qe2 Nxd4 16. Nxd4 cxd4 17. Ne5 (17. Nb6) (17. Qe4 Rd8 18. Qc6+ Rd7) (17. O-O Rd8 18. Ne5 Rd5 19. Nd3 Bd6) 17... d3 (17... a6 18. O-O Bg7 19. f4 (19. Nc6)) 18. Nxd3 (18. Qe4 Rc8 19. Nxd3 Bd6 20. O-O O-O) 18... Qd4 19. Qf3 Rd8 20. Qc6+ Qd7 21. Qxd7+ Rxd7 22. Ke2) (15. dxc5 Rd8 16. Qe2 Bxc5 17. O-O O-O 18. Rac1 Nd4 19. Nxd4 Bxd4 20. Rcd1 Bc5 21. Ne5 Rxd1 22. Rxd1 Rd8) (15. d5 O-O-O (15... Rd8 16. dxc6 Rxd1+ 17. Rxd1) (15... exd5 16. Qxd5 Rd8 17. Qe4+ Qe7) 16. d6 Rg8) 15... O-O-O (15... Nxd4 {is the main move and is analysed in other games.} 16. Qa4+ Ke7 17. Rd1 Rd8 18. Nxd4 Rxd4 19. O-O Qf4 20. Qb5 Kf6 (20... Rxc4 21. Rd3 f5 22. g3) 21. Ne3 (21. b3) (21. g3 Qc7 22. Rfe1) 21... Qc7 22. Qe2 Rg8) 16. Qe2 Nxd4 17. Nxd4 $17 Rxd4 18. O-O $1) 13. bxc3 bxc3 14. Ne4 cxd4 (14... c4 15. Be2) 15. Bb5+ (15. Nxd4 Qd5 (15... Bb4 $1 16. Nc2 Qd2+ (16... Qxd1+ 17. Rxd1 Bxf1 $1 {Clearing the way for d1.} 18. Kxf1 a5 19. Ke2) 17. Qxd2 cxd2+ $17 18. Kd1 Bxf1 19. Rxf1 Ba5) 16. f3 Bxf1 17. Rxf1 (17. Kxf1 Qc4+ 18. Ke1 Bb4 19. Nc2 $132 Nc6 $6) 17... Bb4) 15... Bxb5 16. axb5 Qd5 (16... d3 17. O-O c2 18. Qd2 Qd5 (18... a5 $1 19. Ra4) 19. Nc3 Qd6 20. Ra4 Nd7 21. Rd4 $17 {(Lalith-Macieja, Internet 2018) White had no compensation for the sacrificed pawn.} Qc7 22. Rxd3 Nxf6 23. Rc1 Bg7 $1 24. Rxc2 O-O 25. Nd5 Qb7 26. Nxf6+ Bxf6 $132 27. Qxh6 {is not recommendable because the black king remains in the centre and the c7-square is weak:} Qe4 28. Rcd2 Rad8 $36 29. Re3 Qf5 $1 {Pinning the knight is the best.} 30. h3 {(Cuenca Jimenez-Hungaski, Neuquen 2017)}) 17. Qxd4 Qxb5 $17 18. Nxc3 (18. Ne5 $17) 18... Bb4 19. O-O-O Qa5 (19... Qb6) 20. Nb5 Na6 21. Qd7+ Kf8 22. Kb1 Ba3 (22... Bc5) 23. Rd3 Qb4+ 24. Kc2 Qa4+ 25. Kd2 Bb4+ 26. Ke2 Kg8 $17 27. Ne5 Qc2+ 28. Kf3 Rf8 29. Rhd1 h5 30. Qd4 Rh7 31. Qf4 Bc5 32. Nd4 Qa2 33. R1d2 Qd5+ 34. Ke2 Bb4 35. Ndc6 Qc5 36. Ne7+ $1 {is the strongest move:} Kh8 0-1


