{[%evp 0,61,23,13,28,28,59,16,15,2,17,22,18,-16,1,1,1,-4,-23,-21,-14,7,3,1,1,-32,48,38,46,56,67,67,75,33,53,58,49,48,51,76,84,88,79,79,70,76,76,75,81,81,76,76,76,25,50,-14,0,0,0,7,5,5,0,0] Fier and Vidit are both opening specialists and provided some interesting discussions. Let's see two games from their match.} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 {Vidit goes for the Petroff. He is a very agressive and entertaining player, but in a match it is good to be solid with Black.} 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bg5 e5 7. Nf5 Bxf5 8. exf5 Be7 9. Bxf6 Bxf6 10. Nd5 O-O 11. c3 (11. Nxf6+ Qxf6 $44 {and Black has a solid compensation.} 12. Qf3 {Is enough for a draw.} Nc6 13. Bc4 e4 14. Qd1 e3 15. O-O Ne5 16. Bd5 $1 $11 {followed by Bf8  Bf8} exf2+ {Diagram [#]} 17. Rxf2 $1 Nc6 18. c3 Rac8) 11... Nd7 12. Bc4 {Diagram [#]} b5 $1 $146 {A very good novelty.} 13. Bb3 Nc5 14. O-O {Diagram [#]} Rb8 $1 $146 15. Re1 Kh8 16. Bc2 $1 g6 17. Qg4 Rg8 18. Rad1 e4 $6 19. Bxe4 Nxe4 20. Qxe4 b4 21. fxg6 Rxg6 22. Nxb4 Rb5 23. Qc6 Re5 24. Qxa6 Rxe1+ 25. Rxe1 {Now White can try to press a little bit.} Be5 26. g3 {After this move it is a draw.} {Diagram [#]} Qh4 $1 27. Qd3 Qh3 28. Qf3 Rf6 29. Qg2 Qe6 30. f4 Bd4+ 31. Kf1 Be3 $1 $14 32. Nd5 $1 {was more precise.} 1/2-1/2


