1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd3 d5 6. cxd5 exd5 7. a3 Bd6 8. Qc2 c6 9. Nge2 Re8 10. Bd2 b6 11. f3 (11. O-O {- 151/183 Aronian,Levon 2772 - Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi 2727, Berlin 2022 - 151/183}) 11... c5 {Diagram [#]} 12. b4 $5 $146 {Novelty! An interesting move that leads to a highly complicated and unclear position, difficult to handle for both sides.} (12. g4 {- 153/(186)} c4 13. Bf5 Bxf5 14. Qxf5 g6 15. Qg5 Nc6 {With no danger for Black} 16. h4 (16. O-O Bf8 17. Qh4 h6 18. Rad1 b5 19. Qf2 ({Pawn capture does not promise much:} 19. Nxb5 $6 Rb8 20. Nbc3 Rxb2 $17) 19... Qd7 20. Qg2 Bg7 21. h4 Ne7 22. Nf4 a5 23. Nce2 Reb8 $5 (23... Qb7 24. g5 hxg5 25. hxg5 Nd7 26. Kf2 b4 27. Rh1 $13 {Firouzja,Alireza 2804 - Dominguez Perez, Leinier 2753, Bucuresti 2022}) 24. g5 hxg5 25. hxg5 Ne8 26. Kf2 b4 $15 {and Black has a decent initiative on the queenside.}) 16... Kg7 $5 (16... Bf8 17. h5 h6 ({A bit weaker is} 17... b5 $6 18. hxg6 fxg6 19. Kf1 b4 20. axb4 Nxb4 21. Nf4 $16 {with a much better position for White, as in Petrov,Nikita 2558 - Anuj,Shrivatri 2383, Paracin 2022}) 18. Qh4 g5 19. Qh3 Qd7 $13) 17. h5 h6 18. Qh4 g5 19. Qf2 Qd7 $15) 12... cxb4 13. Nb5 bxa3 14. e4 {Obviously, Harikrishna counted on this move when he went for 12.b4. White claims the centre, but the pawn sacrifice still needs to be justified.} ({White does not achieve anything after} 14. Nxd6 $6 Qxd6 15. Qa4 a5 16. Qxa3 Qxa3 17. Rxa3 {with a slight edge for Black after} Ba6 $15) 14... dxe4 15. fxe4 {Diagram [#]} Ba6 $1 {Apparently, Black found the way to generate some counterplay, hoping to obtain sufficient compensation after a piece sacrifice.} 16. e5 Bxe5 17. dxe5 Rxe5 18. Bc3 Nc6 $6 ({Surely better is} 18... Bxb5 19. Bxe5 Qxd3 20. Qxd3 Bxd3 21. Rxa3 Bc4 22. Bxf6 gxf6 $13 {with unclear position.}) 19. Rd1 Qe7 20. Bxe5 Nxe5 21. O-O Nxd3 ({Black will suffer in case of} 21... a2 22. Ned4 ({Or} 22. Qc7 Nfd7 23. Ned4 $16 {with a clear advantage for White.}) 22... Nxd3 23. Rxd3 $16) 22. Qxd3 Qc5+ 23. Ned4 Rd8 (23... a2 24. Qf5 Rd8 25. Rc1 Qxf5 26. Rxf5 Bb7 27. Nb3 Bd5 28. Na1 $18 {and White is totally winning.}) 24. Rfe1 a2 {Diagram [#]} 25. Qc3 $1 {The key move! It is extremely hard to suggest any plan for Black, as his position is completely hopeless.} h6 26. Qxc5 bxc5 27. Nc7 Bc4 (27... cxd4 28. Nxa6 d3 29. Ra1 d2 30. Red1 $18) 28. Nc6 $1 $18 Rxd1 29. Rxd1 Bd3 (29... Ne4 30. Na5 Bd3 31. Ra1 $1 Bb1 32. Nd5 f5 33. Nb3 $18) 30. Ra1 Bb1 31. Kf2 Ng4+ 32. Ke2 Nxh2 33. Ne5 f6 34. Nc4 Be4 35. Ne3 f5 36. Rxa2 g5 37. Ncd5 Kf7 38. Nc3 {A truly remarkable victory for Harikrishna, which secured him the first prize at the Praha Chess Masters 2022.} 1-0


