{[%evp 0,48,28,28,28,10,10,10,28,4,4,-1,-1,-1,8,11,48,-3,1,-18,-8,-27,-23,-55,-31,-60,-64,-42,-60,-72,-71,-77,-88,-90,-54,-51,-52,-63,-53,-73,-71,-76,-62,-123,-123,-123,-127,-284,-288,-318,-282]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qc2 O-O 5. a3 Bxc3+ 6. Qxc3 d5 7. Bg5 c5 8. cxd5 $6 cxd4 9. Qxd4 Nc6 10. Qd2 (10. Qc3 $6 Nxd5 $1 {The correct way to go to the endgame,} 11. Bxd8 Nxc3 12. Bh4 Na4 $1 13. O-O-O e5 14. e3 Bf5 {and without queens Black also has a nice attack.} 15. Bd3 Bxd3 16. Rxd3 {(Zierk,S (2499)-Hosseinzadeh,N (2217) Chess.com blitz 2020)} Na5 $1 17. Ne2 Rac8+ 18. Nc3 f6 19. Kc2 b5 $17) (10. Qf4 $6 Nxd5 $1 {Similar like in the previous line above.} 11. Bxd8 Nxf4 12. Bg5 e5 13. e3 Nd5 14. Bb5 Be6 15. Bxc6 bxc6 16. e4 Nb6 17. Nf3 f6 18. Bd2 a5 19. Rc1 Nc4 20. Bc3 Rab8 $15 {Borsuk,K (2431)-Vaibhav,S (2600) Chess.com blitz 2020}) (10. Qh4 exd5 (10... Qa5+ $5) 11. Bxf6 (11. e3 $2 d4 $1 12. O-O-O (12. Bd3 $2 Qa5+ 13. Ke2 Bf5 14. Bxf6 Bxd3+ 15. Kxd3 gxf6 $19 {Colin,V (2415)-Sumets,A (2581) Calvi 2009}) (12. Bxf6 $2 Qa5+ $1 {Another great intermediate move!} 13. b4 Nxb4 $19) 12... Bf5 13. Bxf6 Qc7 $3 {What a smart reply! Black ignores the f6-bishop, instead he creates discover threat on the c-file.} 14. e4 Rac8 $3 {Another brilliant continuation!} 15. exf5 Na5+ $19) (11. Nf3 Bf5 12. Bxf6 (12. e3 {(Vigo Allepuz,D (2156)-Tsatsalashvili,K (2271) Barbera del Valles 2008)} d4 $1 13. Bc4 (13. exd4 $2 Qa5+ 14. Nd2 Rfe8+ $19) (13. Nxd4 $2 Qa5+ 14. b4 Nxb4 $19) 13... dxe3 $132) 12... gxf6 {see 11.xf6.}) 11... gxf6 12. Nf3 (12. e3 Bf5 13. Nf3 {transposes to 12.f3.}) 12... Bf5 13. e3 (13. Qf4 Be4 14. Rd1 Re8 15. h4 Ne5 16. Nxe5 fxe5 17. Qd2 d4 $36 {Gordievsky,D (2471)-Sjugirov,S (2673) Khanty-Mansiysk 2014}) 13... Re8 (13... d4 $5) 14. Qa4 (14. Be2 $6 d4 $1 {The strong move before White castles!} 15. O-O dxe3 16. fxe3 Rxe3 17. Bc4 Bg6 $15 {Kozhuharov,S (2446)-Sjugirov,S (2673) Chess.com blitz 2017}) 14... Qb6 15. Qb5 d4 16. Qxb6 axb6 17. Bc4 dxe3 18. Ke2 exf2+ 19. Kxf2 Ne5 20. Bb5 Rec8 21. Rac1 Rc5 $15 {De Paz Gonzalez,Y (2152)-Rund,H (2187) ICCF email 2020}) 10... exd5 11. Nf3 (11. Qf4 $5 d4 $1 $36) 11... h6 12. Bxf6 (12. Bh4 $6 Re8 13. e3 $2 g5 14. Bg3 Ne4 $19) 12... Qxf6 13. e3 d4 $1 14. Nxd4 Rd8 15. Rd1 $2 (15. Be2 Nxd4 16. exd4 Rxd4 17. Qc3 {(Gonda,L (2522)-Horvath,A (2519) Balatonlelle 2009)} Bf5 $36) 15... Nxd4 16. exd4 Be6 $6 (16... Bd7 $1 17. Be2 Ba4 $19) 17. Be2 Bb3 18. Rc1 Rxd4 19. Qe3 $6 (19. Qc3) 19... Ba4 20. O-O Re8 21. Qf3 Rf4 22. Qd3 Qxb2 23. Bf3 Bb5 24. Qd6 Rf6 0-1


