{[%evp 0,58,19,38,25,16,16,16,11,1,14,8,-9,-20,12,4,14,21,53,2,53,47,88,15,7,76,76,20,21,20,70,68,64,47,53,53,47,33,37,38,38,13,60,44,48,49,36,40,44,8,34,8,8,8,8,0,7,4,8,0,1]} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. d4 exd4 5. Nxd4 Bb4 6. Nxc6 bxc6 7. Bd3 d5 8. exd5 O-O 9. O-O Bg4 10. f3 Bh5 11. Bg5 cxd5 12. Bxf6 Qxf6 13. Nxd5 Qxb2 14. Rb1 (14. Kh1 $6 {- a waste of time.} Bd6 15. Qd2 Rab8 (15... Bg6 $1 {After the exchange of bishops, White's pawns become weaker than Black's.} 16. Nf4 Bxd3 17. Nxd3 Qb5 $15) 16. Rae1 Qxa2 17. Ra1 Qb2 18. Rxa7 Ra8 (18... Bg6 $5) 19. Rxa8 Rxa8 20. Qg5 Bg6 21. Ne7+ Bxe7 22. Qxe7 $11 {Kabanov,N - Lysyj,I Cheliabinsk 2018}) 14... Bc5+ 15. Kh1 Qe5 16. f4 $1 (16. Re1 Qd6 $11) 16... Bxd1 17. fxe5 Bg4 18. Rf4 (18. Nxc7 $5 {creates more problems:} Rac8 19. Rb7 (19. Nb5 Be6 20. a4 Rfd8 $44 {The black piece activity compensates for the lack of a pawn.}) 19... Rfd8 $1 {Black solves the problems with precise play.} (19... Rcd8 20. Rb5 Be3 (20... Bb6 21. Nd5 Bd7 22. Rb4 Bc5 23. Rc4 $14) 21. Nd5 $14) 20. e6 (20. Na6 Bd4 21. Rfxf7 Bxe5 22. Rf1 Be6 23. Rxa7 Bd4 $44) (20. Nb5 Be6 21. Nd6 Bd5 22. Rb5 Rc7 23. a4) 20... fxe6 (20... Bxe6 $6 21. Nxe6 fxe6 22. Rff7 Bd4 23. g3 $36) 21. Bc4 Rf8 22. Rxf8+ Bxf8 23. h3 Bd6 24. hxg4 Rxc7 25. Bxe6+ Kf8 $11 {Due to the opposite-coloured bishops, Black achieves a draw without any problems.}) 18... Be6 $6 ({Black could get sufficient compensation in two ways:} 18... Bd7 19. Nxc7 Rac8 20. Nd5 Rb8 21. Re1 Rb2 $44) (18... Rab8 19. Ra1 h5 20. h3 Rbd8 21. Nxc7 Bc8 $44) 19. Nxc7 Rab8 20. Ra1 Bb6 (20... Bd7 {was preferable.}) 21. Nxe6 fxe6 22. Rxf8+ (22. Rc4 $1 {kept some chances.}) 22... Rxf8 23. Bc4 Kf7 {Black achieves a draw without problems.} 24. Rd1 Rd8 25. Rf1+ Ke7 26. Bd3 h6 27. g3 Bc7 28. Bg6 Rf8 29. Rxf8 Kxf8 1/2-1/2


