1. d4 {Paunovic,Tomislav Yermolinsky,A Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Yermolinsky,Alex'} Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 Bb4 5. Qa4+ {Yermolinsky,A: 'In search of a new weapon against the Ragozin defence, White revisits the 1930's theory.' In search of a new weapon against the Ragozin defence, White revisits the 1930's theory. Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Yermolinsky,Alex: 'In search of a new weapon against the Ragozin defence, White revisits the 1930's theory.''} ({Yermolinsky,A: 'Both' Both} 5. Bg5 {Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Yermolinsky,Alex'}) ({Yermolinsky,A: 'and' and} 5. cxd5 {Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Yermolinsky,Alex'} exd5 6. Bg5 {Yermolinsky,A: 'are topical.' are topical.}) 5... Nc6 {Yermolinsky,A: 'It's all about the placement of the black knight ahead of its c-pawn, which according to the classical principles of the Queens Gambit puts Black in disadvantage. Vyacheslav Ragozin made an important contribution by arguing the point.' It's all about the placement of the black knight ahead of its c-pawn, which according to the classical principles of the Queens Gambit puts Black in disadvantage. Vyacheslav Ragozin made an important contribution by arguing the point. Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Yermolinsky,Alex: 'It's all about the placement of the black knight ahead of its c-pawn, which according to the classical principles of the Queens Gambit puts Black in disadvantage. Vyacheslav Ragozin made an important contribution by arguing the point.''} 6. e3 O-O 7. Qc2 {Yermolinsky,A: '[#] Sooner or later White has to return the queen to her proper spot, so it can be done right away.' [#] Sooner or later White has to return the queen to her proper spot, so it can be done right away. Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Yermolinsky,Alex: '[#] Sooner or later White has to return the queen to her proper spot, so it can be done right away.''} (7. Bd2 {Yermolinsky,A: 'is best answered by the immediate' Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Yermolinsky,Alex' is best answered by the immediate} dxc4 $1 8. Bxc4 Bd6 {Yermolinsky,A: 'getting ready for e6-e5, which is the main idea in the Ragozin.' getting ready for e6-e5, which is the main idea in the Ragozin.} 9. O-O e5 10. h3 a6 11. Qc2 exd4 12. exd4 b5 $1 13. Be2 Nb4 14. Qd1 Bb7 {Yermolinsky,A: 'Yermolinsky-D.Zilberstein, San Francisco 2007' Yermolinsky-D.Zilberstein, San Francisco 2007}) 7... Re8 {Yermolinsky,A: 'Vidit settles on one of the most popular choices.' Vidit settles on one of the most popular choices. Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Yermolinsky,Alex: 'Vidit settles on one of the most popular choices.''} ({Yermolinsky,A: 'Others include' Others include} 7... dxc4 {Yermolinsky,A: 'which may eventually transpose to the game,' Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Yermolinsky,Alex' which may eventually transpose to the game,}) (7... Ne7 {Yermolinsky,A: 'which I view as admission of guilt, as Black is trying to reposition the "badly placed" knight,' Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Yermolinsky,Alex' which I view as admission of guilt, as Black is trying to reposition the "badly placed" knight,}) ({Yermolinsky,A: 'and, finally my personal favorite' and, finally my personal favorite} 7... b6 {Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Yermolinsky,Alex'}) 8. Bd2 Bd6 {Yermolinsky,A: 'Black's idea is to wait for the white light-squared bishop to come out before taking on c4. I wonder if it's worth the trouble.' Black's idea is to wait for the white light-squared bishop to come out before taking on c4. I wonder if it's worth the trouble. Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Yermolinsky,Alex: 'Black's idea is to wait for the white light-squared bishop to come out before taking on c4. I wonder if it's worth the trouble.''} 9. h3 ({Yermolinsky,A: 'The point of Black's early rook move is visible after' The point of Black's early rook move is visible after} 9. c5 {Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Yermolinsky,Alex'} Bf8 {Yermolinsky,A: 'where the threat of e6-e5 forces White into' where the threat of e6-e5 forces White into} 10. Bb5 Bd7 11. Bxc6 Bxc6 12. Ne5 {Yermolinsky,A: 'which, incidentally, might not be so bad for him.' which, incidentally, might not be so bad for him.}) 9... a6 10. a3 Bd7 11. Be2 dxc4 12. Bxc4 h6 {Yermolinsky,A: '[#] So, Black has won a local battle for a tempo (Bf1-e2xc4), but what are his accomplishments? The Bd7 move might have made sense when the white queen was on a4, but now it looks like a waste of time. In the meantime, thanks to the Re8 move Black must guard the g5-square before moving the e-pawn forward.' [#] So, Black has won a local battle for a tempo (Bf1-e2xc4), but what are his accomplishments? The Bd7 move might have made sense when the white queen was on a4, but now it looks like a waste of time. In the meantime, thanks to the Re8 move Black must guard the g5-square before moving the e-pawn forward. Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Yermolinsky,Alex: '[#] So, Black has won a local battle for a tempo (Bf1-e2xc4), but what are his accomplishments? The Bd7 move might have made sense when the white queen was on a4, but now it looks like a waste of time. In the meantime, thanks to the Re8 move Black must guard the g5-square before moving the e-pawn forward.''} 13. g4 $3 {Yermolinsky,A: 'No matter what your engines say I absolutely admire Radjabov's concept. If Black can be punished for his opening transgressions it must be done in a resolute fashion.' Paunovic,Tomislav: 'N' Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Yermolinsky,Alex: '!!'' No matter what your engines say I absolutely admire Radjabov's concept. If Black can be punished for his opening transgressions it must be done in a resolute fashion. Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Yermolinsky,Alex: 'No matter what your engines say I absolutely admire Radjabov's concept. If Black can be punished for his opening transgressions it must be done in a resolute fashion.''} (13. O-O {Paunovic,Tomislav: '- 134/ 140'} e5 {Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Yermolinsky,Alex'} 14. Rae1 Qe7 15. Nh4 {Yermolinsky,A: 'Aronian-Giri, 2017' Aronian-Giri, 2017}) 13... e5 {Yermolinsky,A: 'A classic strategy of meeting a flank attack with counterstrike in the centre, but it's wrought with dangers of opening the diagonal for the white bishop.' A classic strategy of meeting a flank attack with counterstrike in the centre, but it's wrought with dangers of opening the diagonal for the white bishop. Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Yermolinsky,Alex: 'A classic strategy of meeting a flank attack with counterstrike in the centre, but it's wrought with dangers of opening the diagonal for the white bishop.''} (13... b5 {Paunovic,Tomislav: '!?'} 14. Ba2 b4 {Yermolinsky,A: 'deserved attention.' deserved attention. Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Yermolinsky,Alex: 'deserved attention.''} 15. Ne2 $13 {Paunovic,Tomislav}) 14. g5 b5 ({Yermolinsky,A: 'Here and on the next move Vidit should have tried a a piece sacrifice:' Here and on the next move Vidit should have tried a a piece sacrifice: Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Yermolinsky,Alex: 'Here and on the next move Vidit should have tried a a piece sacrifice:''} 14... Nxd4 15. exd4 exd4+ 16. Ne2 b5 17. Bd3 {Paunovic,Tomislav: '!'} hxg5 18. Nxg5 c5 19. O-O {Paunovic,Tomislav} (19. O-O-O $5 {Paunovic,Tomislav}) 19... Qb6 20. b3 $14) 15. Ba2 exd4 {Yermolinsky,A: 'This will meet with a devastating response. [#]' Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Diagram [#]' This will meet with a devastating response. [#] Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Yermolinsky,Alex: 'This will meet with a devastating response. [#]''} ({Yermolinsky,A: 'Still,' Still, Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Yermolinsky,Alex: 'Still,''} 15... Nxd4 {Paunovic,Tomislav: '!?'} 16. exd4 exd4+ 17. Ne2 {Paunovic,Tomislav: '- 14...b5'} Qe7 18. Nfxd4 hxg5 {Yermolinsky,A: 'was there for the taking.' Paunovic,Tomislav: '' Paunovic,Tomislav: ' c5' was there for the taking. Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Yermolinsky,Alex: 'was there for the taking.''}) 16. gxh6 $3 {Yermolinsky,A: 'Guess who's coming to dinner - White threatens Qg6!' Guess who's coming to dinner - White threatens Qg6! Paunovic,Tomislav: 'Yermolinsky,Alex: 'Guess who's coming to dinner - White threatens Qg6!''} (16. Rg1 $5 {Paunovic,Tomislav} Ne5 $1 (16... dxc3 $2 17. Bxc3 $18) (16... d3 17. Qxd3 hxg5 18. Nxg5 Ne5 1