{[%evp 0,87,24,16,18,-11,-7,-3,17,10,17,11,27,-8,-15,0,25,18,30,15,18,11,12,9,12,12,22,-53,-53,-81,-65,-88,-14,-71,7,-1,2,25,26,19,19,19,51,10,42,-53,-61,-50,-60,-49,-20,-102,-79,-130,-134,-133,-112,-135,-140,-174,-161,-188,-184,-197,-171,-99,241,-36,227,-55,30,45,511,-14,5,-34,-53,-53,210,164,172,162,158,183,211,170,286,212,29995,29996]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd3 d5 6. a3 Bxc3+ 7. bxc3 dxc4 8. Bxc4 c5 9. Ne2 Qc7 10. Bd3 Nc6 11. O-O e5 12. Ng3 Rd8 13. f4 exd4 {The pawn exchange on f4 and opening of the f-file would be a big mistake, immediately creating the threat of an exchange sacrifice on f6 with a winning attack.} 14. cxd4 cxd4 (14... b6 $2 {was met in the game Sarana,A - Le,Q Rapid, Chess.com INT 2022. Alexey could get a big advantage by} 15. Bb2 $1 ({instead of} 15. Qe2) 15... cxd4 16. Rc1 $16) (14... b5 $2 {is also a mistake.} 15. Nh5 ({White has an easier way to advantage} 15. dxc5 $1 Qe7 16. Qc2 b4 17. Re1 $16) 15... Nd5 16. e4 $1 (16. Qc2 $2 {Sarana,A - Nakamura,H Blitz,Chess.com INT 2022}) 16... Nc3 17. Qe1 $1 cxd4 18. e5 $40 {with a decisive attack}) 15. e4 $44 {This is an important position. White has realized a typical pawn sacrifice. The strategic idea of this pawn sacrifice is a basis of the whole variation! White has a sufficient compensation.} Ng4 (15... Bg4 $6 {The bishop on g4 has been placed poorly. Qc2 is considerably more useful move.} 16. Qc2 Nh5 $6 17. Nxh5 Bxh5 18. e5 h6 19. Bd2 $16 {Sarana,A - Svane,R Blitz, Chess.com INT 2022}) 16. e5 ({It is possible to try to prepare against the invasion of the black knight onto e3:} 16. Qf3 $5 Ne3 17. Re1) 16... Qe7 $2 {Developing initiative in this position ( as in most cases) is easier than defending.} (16... Qb6 $2 {is one more obviously mistaken move.} 17. h3 (17. Rb1 Qc5 18. Qf3 $16) 17... Ne3 18. Qh5 h6 (18... g6 $2 19. Qh6 $18) 19. Rf3 Qb3 {Sarana,A - Jumabayev,R Rapid, Chess.com INT 2022} 20. Be4 $1 {gave a huge advantage to White.}) ({Only an immediate invasion -} 16... Ne3 $1 {has been leading to a position with the both sides' chances} 17. Bxe3 dxe3 18. Qe2 $44) 17. Qf3 Be6 18. h3 Ne3 19. Bxe3 dxe3 20. Qxe3 $16 {White has the better pawn structure, space advantage as well as real chances of organizing a dangerous attack on the opponent's king.} f6 21. Be4 fxe5 22. f5 Bc4 23. f6 gxf6 24. Nf5 Qf8 25. Rf3 Kh8 26. Rg3 Nd4 27. Kh2 Nxf5 28. Bxf5 Rd4 29. Qf3 Qf7 30. Bc2 Rad8 31. Re1 Rd2 32. Bxh7 R8d4 33. Be4 Be6 34. Qe3 Qf8 35. Rg6 Bg8 36. Qg3 Bh7 37. Rg4 Rxe4 38. Rexe4 b6 39. Rh4 Rd7 40. a4 Rg7 41. Reg4 Re7 42. Rc4 Rd7 43. Qg4 Qf7 44. Rc8+ 1-0


