{The decisive game of the match featured a theoretical duel in the Catalan.} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. g3 dxc4 5. Bg2 Nc6 6. Qa4 Bb4+ 7. Bd2 Nd5 {Diagram [#]} 8. Qc2 $5 {A rare move.} (8. Bxb4 {- 135/164} Ndxb4 9. O-O Rb8 10. Na3 O-O 11. Qb5 b6 12. Qxc4 Ba6 13. Nb5 Qd5 14. Qxd5 Nxd5 15. a4 Na5 {and Black held. This is a very well known position, Lysyj,Igor 2643 - Harutyunyan,Tigran K 2515, Moscow 2017 - 131/166}) 8... b5 {True to his style, Fier goes for the most dynamic option.} (8... Nb6 {was played in Eljanov,Pavel 2703 - Mekhitarian,Krikor Sevag 2546, Douglas 2018}) 9. a4 Bxd2+ 10. Nbxd2 Ncb4 11. Qc1 (11. Qb1) 11... c6 12. b3 c3 (12... cxb3 13. Nxb3 O-O 14. O-O a5 $11 {Korogodski,Leonid - Dillenburg,Alberto, corr 2018}) 13. Ne4 {Diagram [#]} c2 $146 (13... bxa4 {- 149/(165)} 14. Rxa4 c2 $146 (14... a5) 15. Qd2 O-O 16. O-O a5 17. Rc1 Ba6 $13 {Wojtaszek, Radoslaw 2687 - Shankland,Samuel 2691, Praha 2021}) 14. a5 $5 {A somewhat surprising move. White wants to avoid a7-a5 once and for all. Objectively Black's position is ok, but it is not easy to play. White has a clear plan: Nc5, e4, and capture the c2-pawn.} O-O (14... e5 $145 $1 15. Nxe5 (15. dxe5 O-O 16. Qd2 Qe7 17. O-O Bg4 18. Nd4 Qxe5 19. h3 Bxh3 20. Bxh3 Qxe4 21. Bg2 Qe7 22. Bxd5 cxd5 $15) 15... f6 16. Nf3 Qe7 17. Nc5 Nc3 18. Qe3 Nb1 19. Qc1 Nc3 $11) 15. Qd2 Qe7 16. O-O Rd8 17. Nc5 Na6 18. Qxc2 Nxc5 19. Qxc5 Qxc5 20. dxc5 $14 {White has a slight advantage in this endgame and won after some more adventures.} Bd7 21. Rfd1 Be8 22. Kf1 Kf8 23. Ng5 Ke7 $6 (23... Nc3 $145 24. Rdc1 b4 25. Nxh7+ Ke7 26. Ng5 Rab8 27. Ne4 Nb5 28. Ke1 e5 $44) 24. Ne4 f6 25. Nd6 Bg6 26. Rac1 Rab8 27. Rd4 b4 28. Rcc4 e5 29. Rh4 $16 Ke6 {Diagram [#]} 30. a6 $6 (30. Ke1 Kd7 (30... h5 31. g4 $16) 31. Bh3+ Kc7 32. Bf5 $16) (30. Bh3+) 30... Bb1 $2 (30... Nc7 $1 31. Bh3+ $145 Ke7 32. Nf5+ Kf8 33. Rxb4 Rxb4 34. Rxb4 Nxa6 35. Ra4 Nxc5 36. Rxa7 Rd1+ 37. Kg2 Rd2 38. Ra8+ Kf7 39. Ra7+ Kf8 $11) 31. Bh3+ Ke7 32. Bf5 $18 Bxf5 33. Nxf5+ Kf7 34. Rxh7 Kg6 35. Rxg7+ Kxf5 36. e4+ Ke6 37. exd5+ cxd5 38. Rh4 Rdc8 39. Rb7 Ra8 40. Rhh7 Rc6 41. g4 d4 42. Rbd7 Re8 43. Rxa7 $18 Rxc5 44. Rab7 d3 45. Rb6+ Kd5 46. Rd7+ (46. Rd7+ Ke4 47. Rxb4+ Rc4 48. Rxc4+ Kf3 49. Rxd3# {#}) 1-0


