1. d4 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Pikula,Dejan'} Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 d5 4. Bg2 Be7 5. Nf3 O-O 6. O-O dxc4 7. Qc2 (7. Qa4 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi} a6 {½-½ (85) Caruana,F (2828)-Dominguez Perez,L (2739) Saint Louis USA 2019}) 7... a6 8. Qxc4 b5 9. Qc2 Bb7 10. Bd2 {Vigorito,D & TonyK: 'I must confess that I never liked this move for White. It seems too artificial.'} Be4 11. Qc1 c6 {Vigorito,D & TonyK: '!?' Vigorito,D & TonyK: 'A relatively new line, which seems quite solid for Black.' Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'This line, introduced at the high level in the game Giri-Kramnik, used to be considered equal in the past few years. However, recently many players with White came up with micro ideas to test Black. I had one such idea for this game.'} 12. a4 ({For} 12. Rd1 {see Shankland,S (2725) -Radjabov,T (2757) Wijk aan Zee 2019}) 12... Nbd7 ({This is the favoured choice.} 12... b4 {looks playable too. Presumably White will move the d2-bishop and play Nbd2-c4.}) 13. Nc3 Bg6 14. Nh4 {Vigorito,D & TonyK: 'A natural enough move, but Black seems fine.'} (14. Ne5 Nxe5 15. dxe5 Nd5 {was covered by Max in Giri,A  (2768)-Kramnik,V (2769) London 2014}) 14... Bh5 {Vigorito,D & TonyK: '!'} 15. h3 {Vigorito,D & TonyK: 'It's a move. This is the engine's top choice, but that may be because everything else is worse!' Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'A rare move. This was played in Caruana-Dominguez in the USA Championship 2019.'} ({As Max points out} 15. Bxc6 $2 b4 $1 16. Bxa8 bxc3 17. Bf3 cxd2 18. Qxd2 Bxf3 19. Nxf3 Qa8 $15 {and the two minor pieces better the rook and pawns.}) ({White does not gain anything from} 15. axb5 axb5 {as} 16. Bxc6 $2 Rxa1 17. Qxa1 b4 {wins the e2-pawn and gives Black the upper hand, Garbett,P (2229)-Howell,D (2649) Devonport 2015}) ({Beliavsky won with} 15. Qe1 {but this was because of his huge rating advantage.} Nd5 (15... b4 $1 16. Na2 a5 $1 17. Bxc6 Rc8 $44) 16. Nf3 b4 17. Ne4 $6 (17. Nxd5 cxd5 18. Bxb4) 17... Qb6 $15 {Beliavsky,A  (2526)-Di Benedetto,D (2236) Skopje 2019}) ({White won a rapid game with} 15. Bf3 $6 {but this looks strange.} b4 16. Na2 Bxf3 17. Nxf3 c5 {looks at least equal for Black as White's Na2 and queen are both misplaced.} 18. Rd1 a5 19. dxc5 Bxc5 20. Be3 Qb6 21. Bd4 Bxd4 (21... e5 22. Bxc5 Nxc5 $17) 22. Rxd4 Nc5 23. Qd1 {Yu Yangyi (2739)-Wang Hao (2735) Hengshui rapid 2019} Rfe8 $5 {...e5}) 15... Nd5 ({Perhaps Black should prefer} 15... b4 $5 16. Na2 a5 {The c6-pawn is loose, but so is e2.}) 16. axb5 axb5 17. Nxd5 $146 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'N!?' 'N!?' Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Pikula,Dejan: 'N'' Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'A new concept. The resulting positions look quite harmless. But as the game shows, White's idea does have some poison.'} (17. Rxa8 {- 141/(167) Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Pikula,Dejan: '- 141/(167)''} Qxa8 18. e4 {which looks more ambitious.} Nb4 19. Bg5 Qd8 20. Bxe7 Qxe7 21. Qe3 Rd8 22. Rc1 {which the computer assesses as level, but White's position looks easier.} Nf8 23. Bf3 Bxf3 24. Nxf3 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '' '' Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '½-½ (85) Caruana,F (2828)-Dominguez Perez,L (2739) Saint Louis USA 2019'} Nd7 25. Kg2 h6 26. h4 Nb6 27. b3 Nd7 28. Rd1 Ra8 29. Qe2 Nf6 30. Ne5 Nd7 31. Ng4 Nf6 32. Ne3 Ra3 33. e5 Nd7 34. Ne4 Nb6 35. Qh5 Rxb3 36. Ng4 N4d5 37. Ra1 Ra3 $2 38. Nxh6+ (38. Nef6+ $1 {is even stronger} Nxf6 (38... gxf6 39. Nxh6+ Kg7 40. Rxa3 Qxa3 41. exf6+ Nxf6 42. Qg5+ $18) 39. exf6 gxf6 40. Rxa3 Qxa3 41. Nxf6+ Kg7 42. Qe5 $18) 38... gxh6 39. Nf6+ Nxf6 40. exf6 Rxg3+ $1 41. fxg3 Qxf6 $16 {was still tricky, and Black held out in Caruana,F (2828) -Dominguez Perez,L (2739) Saint Louis USA-ch 2019}) 17... cxd5 18. Bf3 (18. Rxa8 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Pikula,Dejan'} Qxa8 19. Qc7 Bxh4 20. Qxd7 Bf6 21. e3 Qa4 $11) 18... Bxf3 19. Nxf3 Qb6 {Vigorito,D & TonyK: 'It's hard to believe that White has anything here, but in the game Black has some trouble neutralizing the c-file.'} 20. Qc2 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'It might look harmless for Black, and it could actually be. Before the game, I didn't see a clear way to neutralize the pressure on both the c-file and the a-file. It felt a little uncomfortable for Black. My theory was approved by Wang Hao as he thought for more than 35 mins!'} Rac8 (20... h6 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Pikula,Dejan'} 21. Rxa8 Rxa8 22. Rc1 Nf6 23. Qc7 Qxc7 24. Rxc7 Bd6 25. Rc6 (25. Rb7 Rb8 $11) 25... Ne4 $11) 21. Qd3 Ra8 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Looks strange!'} 22. Rxa8 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '!' '!'} Rxa8 23. Rc1 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Taking complete control over c-file. Whereas black can't make much use of the open a-file. Also it's hard for black to come up with a plan. Whereas white just plays Bf4 and puts the major pieces on the c-file'} h6 (23... Bd6) 24. Bf4 g5 {Diagram [#] Vigorito,D & TonyK: '?!' Vigorito,D & TonyK: 'An unnecessary weakening of the black kingside.' Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Pikula,Dejan: 'Diagram [#]'' Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'A very committal decision. But I understand the reasoning. The threats of Rc7 were quite annoying.'} (24... Nf6) (24... Bd6 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi doesn't really work.} 25. Bxd6 Qxd6 26. Qxb5 Rb8 27. Qa4 Rxb2 28. Rc8+ Kh7 29. Rd8 $18) 25. Ne5 $1 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '!?' '!?' Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Pikula,Dejan: '!'' Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Straightforward and tempting!'} (25. Be3 $5 Nf6 26. h4 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Pikula,Dejan'} (26. Ne5 $14 {- 25.Ne5}) (26. Kg2 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi} Ne4 27. Ne5 {followed by ideas of h4 was also an idea.}) 26... Ne4 27. hxg5 hxg5 28. Ne5 $14) 25... Nxe5 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '?' '?' Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'A pleasant surprise!'} (25... gxf4 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Pikula,Dejan'} 26. Nxd7 Qa7 27. Ne5 fxg3 28. Qxg3+ Kh7 (28... Kf8 29. Kh2 $1 Qxd4 30. Rc7 $18) 29. Qd3+ f5 30. Kf1 $14) (25... Nf6 $142 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Pikula,Dejan: ''' Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Looked more compact.'} 26. Be3 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '' '' Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Pikula,Dejan: '- 25.Ne5''} (26. Rc6 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi} Qb7 $1 27. Be3 Ne4 28. Qc2 Bd6 {Keeps things together concretely!}) 26... Ne4 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Pikula,Dejan'} 27. g4 Qb7 28. f3 Nd6 29. b3 $14) 26. Bxe5 $14 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '' '' Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Pikula,Dejan: '''} b4 $6 (26... Bf8 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'and Bg7 next is more tenable. Wang Hao clearly seemed frustrated at his position as he started to blitz out the moves from now on.'} 27. h4 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Pikula,Dejan'} Bg7 28. hxg5 hxg5 29. Kg2 $14) 27. Qf3 {Vigorito,D & TonyK: 'Threatening Qh5.' Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '?!' '?!' Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'It's very tempting to attack on the kingside. The move itself is not bad as such, but in hindsight it seems like a step in the wrong direction.'} (27. h4 $1 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'The queen on d3 is ideally placed as Black can't play f6. At the same time it's not easy to see how Black can possibly avoid the opening up of the kingside.'} g4 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Pikula,Dejan'} (27... gxh4 $2 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Pikula,Dejan'} 28. gxh4 Bxh4 29. Rc7 Qa6 30. Qf3 $18) (27... Qd8 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Pikula,Dejan'} 28. hxg5 hxg5 29. Kg2 $16) 28. Qe3 Bf8 29. f3 $16) 27... Qd8 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '!' '!'} (27... f6 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi} 28. Rc7 Bd8 29. Rd7 Qc6 30. Rxd8+ $1 {was the point!} Rxd8 31. Qxf6 $18) 28. Qh5 Bf8 (28... Qf8 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi} 29. Rc7 $18 {Black's completely paralyzed.}) 29. Rc7 $16 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Pikula,Dejan: '''} Qe8 {Vigorito,D & TonyK: 'Black is just hanging on.'} 30. h4 $6 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '?' '?' Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Pikula,Dejan: '?!'' Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'The big mistake! This throws away the entire advantage. I actually thought for over 20mins at this point. Probably the theory that if you think over 20mins you are more likely to make a mistake has some sense to it!'} (30. Rb7 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Pikula,Dejan'} Bg7 (30... f5 31. Qf3 $16) 31. h4 f6 32. Qxe8+ Rxe8 33. Bd6 $16) (30. Kg2 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Apparently just keeping the status quo was the way.'} Bg7 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi} 31. Bxg7 Kxg7 32. f4 $1 gxf4 33. Qg4+ Kf8 34. Qxf4 Kg7 {There are many good moves, but I like the Engine's suggestion of Kf3 :D} 35. Kf3 $16) 30... f5 $1 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Pikula,Dejan: '!''} 31. Qf3 g4 $2 {Vigorito,D & TonyK: 'Missing his chance.' Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'The decisive error. As soon as I had played h4, I realized that instead of the automatic g4, Black can take on h4, with the concrete of idea of exchanging the queens. The logic behind this mistake could be that the entire game Black was trying to close up the kingside! He chose the wrong moment to do so.'} (31... gxh4 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '!' '!'} 32. gxh4 Qg6+ 33. Bg3 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Pikula,Dejan'} (33. Kh2 Ra1 {Vigorito,D & TonyK: 'is perfectly acceptable for Black.' Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Pikula,Dejan'} (33... Qg4 $1 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi The point! Black is now completely fine.}) 34. Rc8 Kf7 35. Rc7+ Kg8 $11) (33. Qg2 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Pikula,Dejan'} Qxg2+ 34. Kxg2 Ra2 35. Rc8 Kf7 36. Rc7+ Kg8 $11) 33... Qg4 $11) 32. Qe3 Rc8 33. Ra7 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '!' '!' Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Probably Black thought that he could keep challenging the rook on the 7th rank.'} (33. Rb7 $2 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi} Qc6 34. Ra7 Qc1+) 33... Qc6 (33... Ra8 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi} 34. Rb7 $1 Qc6 35. Rc7 $1 {The clever rook dance evades the exchange.}) 34. Bf4 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '!' '!' Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Protecting c1 and avoiding the queen exchange.'} Qb6 {Diagram [#] Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Pikula,Dejan: 'Diagram [#]''} 35. Qe5 $1 $18 {Vigorito,D & TonyK: '!' Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '!' '!' Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Pikula,Dejan: '+-!'' Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Very precise! There was another tempting option, which leads to a study like draw.'} (35. Rd7 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi Initially I was tempted to go in this direction.} Qc6 36. Rd6 {This flashy move looked quite tempting!} Qc1+ $1 (36... Bxd6 37. Qxe6+ $18) 37. Qxc1 Rxc1+ 38. Bxc1 Bxd6 39. Bxh6 {It looks like White is pawn up and he should be winnning, but in fact Black saves the game.} b3 $1 40. Bd2 {The only idea for white is to try to attack the b3 pawn with the King.} e5 41. Bc3 (41. dxe5 Bxe5 42. Bc1 Kh7 {is easy draw.}) 41... e4 42. e3 {The plan seems simple. Bring the king to d2 and then play Ba5 and Kc3.} Kf7 43. Kf1 Kg6 44. Ke2 Be7 45. Kd2 {[#]} f4 $3 {Absolutely brilliant defense} 46. exf4 Bf6 $1 $11 {Surprisingly, There is no way to improve!}) 35... h5 (35... Qxa7 36. Qxe6+ Qf7 37. Qxc8) 36. Qf6 {Vigorito,D & TonyK: 'Menacing Be5, Black can resign.'} Rc1+ 37. Bxc1 Qxa7 38. Qxe6+ Qf7 39. Qc8 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '+-' '+-' Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Now the win is technical and White has more than one way to convert.'} Kh7 40. Bf4 Kg6 41. Be5 Be7 42. Qc6+ Kh7 43. e3 {Vigorito,D & TonyK: 'GM technique.'} Bf8 44. Bd6 Bxd6 45. Qxd6 {Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '+-' '+-'} b3 46. Qb6 1-0


