{Vigorito, D: 'Black plays a novelty in this wild line. I think it is suspicious, but the whole thing is very complicated.'} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. e4 d6 5. f3 O-O 6. Be3 c5 7. Nge2 Nc6 8. d5 Ne5 9. Ng3 h5 (9... e6 10. Be2 exd5 {L'alternative}) 10. Be2 h4 11. Nf1 e6 12. f4 (12. Nd2) 12... Nxc4 $1 {[%csl Re1] Le défaut de la variante Saemisch pour les Blancs est sa lenteur et les noirs ont trouvé cette idée récemment qui leur donne un bon contre-jeu} 13. Bxc4 b5 14. Bxb5 exd5 15. e5 {Vigorito, D: '!'} (15. exd5 Rb8 {Vigorito, D: 'see Parligras, M (2565) -Kurnosov, I (2657) Abu Dhabi 2013'} 16. Rc1 a6 17. Be2 Rxb2 18. Rc2 Rxc2 19. Qxc2 Re8 20. h3 Qa5 21. Bd2 Qb4 22. Kd1 Bf5 23. Bd3 Qd4 24. Bxf5 gxf5 25. Qxf5 Ne4 26. Nxe4 Rxe4 27. Qc8+ Kh7 28. Qf5+ Kg8 29. Qc8+ Kh7 30. Qf5+ Kg8 {½-½ (30) Baramidze,D (2599)-Naiditsch,A (2715) Baden Baden 2014}) 15... d4 $146 ({Vigorito, D: 'the original game was'} 15... dxe5 $142 {Vigorito, D: '?!'} 16. fxe5 Bg4 (16... h3 17. exf6 (17. gxh3 d4 $13) 17... hxg2) 17. exf6 $1 Bxd1 18. fxg7 Kxg7 19. Bxc5 h3 20. Rxd1 hxg2 21. Rg1 gxf1=Q+ 22. Kxf1 {Vigorito, D: 'see Svidler, P (2747)-Grischuk, A (2764) London 2013'} Qh4 23. Rg2 Rfd8 24. Rd4 Qh5 25. Rf4 d4 26. Bxd4+ Rxd4 27. Rxd4 Rb8 28. a4 a6 29. Bxa6 Qf3+ 30. Rf2 Qh1+ 31. Ke2 Rxb2+ 32. Rd2 Qc1 33. Kd3 Rb6 34. Bc4 Rd6+ 35. Bd5 Rd7 36. Rf4 f5 37. Rd4 Kh6 38. h4 Rc7 39. Bc4 Qf1+ 40. Re2 f4 41. Kc2 f3 {½-½ (41) Svidler,P (2747)-Grischuk,A (2764) London 2013}) ({I think Black's best is the immediate} 15... Bg4 $1 16. Be2 (16. exf6 Bxd1 17. fxg7 Kxg7 18. Rxd1 d4 19. Rxd4 $1 (19. Bxd4+ cxd4 20. Rxd4 Qb6) 19... cxd4 20. Bxd4+ f6 $13) 16... Bxe2 17. Qxe2 $1 dxe5 18. fxe5 Nd7 (18... d4 19. exf6 Qxf6 20. Ne4 Qe5 (20... Qe6 21. Bf4 Rfe8 22. Nfd2 f5 23. O-O fxe4 24. Rae1 e3 25. Nf3 {Kaufman}) 21. Ned2) 19. Bf4 (19. Nxd5 Nxe5 20. Rd1 Re8 $13) 19... g5 20. Bd2 Nxe5 21. Ne3 d4 22. Rd1 Nc6 23. O-O dxe3 24. Bxe3 Qe7 25. Nd5 Qe4 26. Qh5 Nb4 27. Qf3 Qxf3 28. Rxf3 Rfd8 29. Ne7+ Kh8 30. Rxd8+ Rxd8 31. Bxc5 Rd1+ 32. Kf2 Rb1 $11 {1/2-1/2 (54) Rawlings, A (2387)-Berg, E ICCF 2013}) 16. exf6 Bxf6 (16... Qxf6 $6 17. Nd5) 17. Nd5 ({White could try} 17. Bc6 $5 dxc3 $5 (17... Rb8 18. Nd5 dxe3 19. Nfxe3 Bd4 (19... Bxb2 20. Rb1) 20. Rb1 $14) 18. Bxa8 cxb2 19. Rb1 c4 $13 {White is up a rook and a piece but Houdini gives White just a slight edge!}) 17... dxe3 18. Nfxe3 Bd4 $13 {[%csl Gd4]} (18... Qa5+ $2 19. Qd2 Qxb5 20. Nxf6+) (18... Bxb2 19. Rb1 Bd4 20. Bc6 {would be 17.Bc6!? above}) 19. Nc2 {Vigorito, D: '?'} (19. Qa4 {[%cal Ge1c1,Ga4b5]} Rb8 20. O-O Be6 21. Kh1) ({White still seems for choice after} 19. Bc6 Rb8 20. Rb1 {Vigorito, D: ''}) 19... Qa5+ 20. Qd2 Qxb5 21. Nxd4 cxd4 22. Nf6+ {Vigorito, D: 'Perhaps White realized he had to change course here.'} ({Black has his material back and is certainly ok now because} 22. Nc7 $2 {does not work:} Qc6 23. Nxa8 Re8+ 24. Kf2 (24. Kd1 $2 Bg4+) (24. Kf1 $2 Ba6+ 25. Kf2 h3 $1) 24... Bb7 25. Rhg1 d3 $1 26. Rae1 (26. Qxd3 $2 Qc5+ 27. Kf1 Bxa8) 26... Qc5+ 27. Re3 Rxe3 28. Qxe3 Qc2+ 29. Ke1 Qb1+ 30. Kf2 Qxb2+ 31. Ke1 Bxa8 $17 32. Qxd3 $2 Qc1+ 33. Kf2 Qxf4+ 34. Ke2 Qxh2 $19) 22... Kh8 23. Qxd4 {[%cal Gd4h8,Gd4b2]} Qc5 $1 {Vigorito, D: '=' Vigorito, D: 'Now it's just an equal ending.'} 24. Qxc5 dxc5 25. O-O-O (25. O-O) 25... Kg7 26. Nd7 Re8 27. Rd2 Re4 28. Rf1 Ba6 $132 {Le  doit dominer le  dans cette position ouverte} 29. Rf3 Be2 30. Rc3 Bg4 31. Nxc5 Rxf4 32. b3 Re8 33. Kb2 Bf5 34. a4 Rf1 35. Rc4 g5 36. a5 Rfe1 37. Rcd4 Rb1+ 38. Ka2 Ree1 39. Rd5 Kg6 40. Rf2 Ra1+ 41. Kb2 Rab1+ 1/2-1/2


