1. e4 {Vidit,S} c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. g3 {After suffering on the black side of this line in the previous game, I decided to play this line just before I went to sleep. I didn't have much time to prepare as the last round started early in the morning.} e5 7. Nde2 Be7 8. Bg2 b5 9. Nd5 Nxd5 10. Qxd5 Ra7 11. Be3 Rb7 {Until here my opponent was playing fast.} 12. O-O {This retained some flexibility regarding the queen's position.} O-O {He played this after a long period of thought. From now on Areschenko played all the moves after thinking for a considerable amount of time.} 13. Qd3 Be6 14. b3 Nd7 (14... b4 {I remembered that this was the main move. But over the board, I was wondering why not the simple ...d7? And he indeed played ...d7!}) 15. Nc3 (15. f4 Nf6 16. f5 Bd7 17. h3 Bc6 18. c4 bxc4 19. bxc4 Nd7 {I was a bit hesitant to play like this. My kingside looks more vulnerable than dangerous.}) 15... Nf6 16. a4 {I wanted to open the a-file before I fought for the d5-square.} Qb8 (16... Qd7 17. axb5 axb5 18. Bg5 {The play would be similar to the game. Of course one can argue if the queen is better placed here than on b8.}) 17. axb5 axb5 18. Bg5 (18. Ra5 b4 19. Nd5 {I always am a bit surprised to see the engine giving such positions as better.} Bxd5 20. exd5 Bd8 21. Ra6 Bb6 22. Bxb6 Rxb6 {I actually think Black is very comfortable here.}) 18... b4 19. Bxf6 Bxf6 20. Nd5 Bd8 (20... Bxd5 21. Qxd5 Rc8 22. Ra2 $14) 21. Rfd1 (21. Ra6 {Later on I thought that this was probably a better way to play. To fight for the a-file immediately} Bd7 (21... Bb6 22. Nxb4 Bd7 $1 {I didn't see such cheeky moves!}) 22. Rfa1 Bb5 23. Qe3 Bxa6 24. Rxa6 Qc8 {Probably I over-estimated the compensation. Black has a fine position.}) 21... Bxd5 (21... Bb6 22. Nxb4 Qc8 23. Nd5 Bxd5 24. Qxd5 Rc7 25. Qxd6 Bd4 26. Bh3 Qb8 27. Ra8 $14) 22. Qxd5 Bb6 23. Bf1 (23. Qxd6 {was my original intention, but after ...c7 I didn't see a clear way to play and the moves were too easy for Black} Rc7 24. Rd2 Bd4 $132) 23... Bc5 (23... Ra7 {I thought the best way was to not allow ...a6 and with it the control of the a-file, but apparently it's not that clear} 24. Rxa7 Qxa7 25. Qxd6 $1 Bxf2+ 26. Kh1 $14) 24. Ra6 g6 25. Bc4 Kg7 26. Kg2 {I purposefully delayed da1. I wanted to provoke some kingside weakening!} (26. Rda1 Qc7 {and the queen comes to e7. I don't see a clear plan to improve my position.}) 26... f5 {A questionable decision. It weakens the king more than providing any activity.} (26... Ra7 $11) 27. Rda1 {I missed a tactic in this line. Probably f3 or exf5 is stronger:} (27. f3 Rbf7 28. exf5 Rxf5 29. Rf1 $1 {White keeps a bind on the light squares}) (27. exf5 {is probably even better than 27.f3:} Rxf5 28. f3 Rbf7 29. Ra8 Qc7 30. Qe4 $14) 27... Ra7 (27... fxe4 28. Ra8 Rxf2+ 29. Kh1 Qc7 30. Qxe4 $1 {White has to be accurate!} (30. Rg8+ Kh6 31. Qxe4 (31. Re1 Rb8 $19) 31... Qe7 32. Bd3 {I thought this wins} Qf6 33. Qxb7 e4 $1 {I stopped my calculation one move too early! Now the tables are turned!}) 30... Rf8 (30... Qe7 31. Re8 Qxe8 32. Qxb7+ Kf6 33. g4 $1 e4 34. h4 Ke5 $1 35. Qg7+ Kf4 36. Qf6+ Kg3 37. Rg1+ Kh3 38. Bf1+ Rxf1 39. Qxf1+ Kxh4 40. Qf6+ Kh3 { And it's a DRAW?!!?!!}) 31. Rxf8 Kxf8 32. Rf1+ Kg7 33. g4 Ra7 34. g5 Qb7 35. Bd5 Qc8) 28. exf5 Rxa6 29. Rxa6 gxf5 (29... Qc8 $1 {was a nice move} 30. Bd3 gxf5 31. f3 $14) (29... Rxf5 30. f3 $14) 30. Ra5 $1 Kh8 31. Rb5 Qe8 (31... Qa8 32. Rb7) 32. Rb7 e4 33. Qd1 $1 {I am proud to find the strongest move and a nice trick which made me 2700! :)} f4 $2 (33... Qg6 34. Bd5 Qf6 35. h4 $16 {White keeps the pressure.}) 34. Rb8 f3+ 35. Kh1 {I was very happy to win this game and also crossing 2700! It's not a big deal of course, but it did give me a very nice feeling :)} 1-0


