{Fernandez,Daniel Howard: 'Sam Collins: 'A very important game between two of the front runners in this year's Tata Steel B group.''} 1. e4 {[%emt 0:00:05] Fernandez,Daniel Howard Fernandez,Daniel Howard Fernandez,Daniel Howard} c5 {[%emt 0:00:14]} 2. Nf3 {[%emt 0:00:12]} d6 {[%emt 0:00:07]} 3. Bb5+ {[%emt 0:00:19]} Bd7 {[%emt 0:00:34]} 4. Bxd7+ {[%emt 0:00:17]} Nxd7 {[%emt 0:00:12] Less popular than the queen recapture, though it is not clear to me quite why. Fernandez,Daniel Howard: 'Less popular than the queen recapture, though it is not clear to me quite why. Sam Collins: 'Fernandez,D: 'Less popular than the queen recapture, though it is not clear to me quite why.'''} 5. O-O {[%emt 0:00:18]} Ngf6 {[%emt 0:00:07]} (5... g6 {was the move I tried in one outing against one of the players currently in Wijk:} 6. c3 Ngf6 7. Re1 Ne5 $6 {A typical idea, but White is not obliged to take by any means! My opponent achieved an advantage but then lost it at some later point:} 8. d4 cxd4 9. cxd4 Nxf3+ 10. Qxf3 Bg7 11. e5 dxe5 12. dxe5 Nd5 13. Rd1 e6 14. Nc3 O-O 15. Nxd5 exd5 16. Rxd5 Qb6 17. h4 $6 Rad8 $11 {Jones, G-Fernandez,D London 2016}) 6. Qe2 {[%emt 0:00:15]} (6. Re1 e6 7. c3 Be7 8. d4 O-O 9. Bg5 h6 10. Bxf6 Bxf6 11. Na3 cxd4 12. cxd4 Nb6 $11 {Vachier Lagrave,M-Nakamura,H Palma de Mallorca 2017, failed to achieve anything much.}) 6... Qc7 {[%emt 0:01:35]} (6... Rc8 7. c3 e6 8. d4 cxd4 9. cxd4 d5 10. e5 Ne4 11. Be3 Nb6 12. Ne1 f5 13. f3 Ng5 14. b3 Nf7 15. Nd3 Nd7 16. Nd2 Be7 17. Rac1 O-O 18. Rxc8 Qxc8 19. Rc1 Qb8 20. Nf4 Re8 21. g4 fxg4 22. fxg4 Bg5 23. Nd3 Bxe3+ 24. Qxe3 Nd8 25. Nf4 Nc6 26. Nf3 Qd8 27. Rf1 Qe7 28. h4 Nf8 29. Rf2 Rc8 30. Kg2 {½-½ (30) Mamedov,R (2680)-Ivanchuk,V (2729) Kocaeli 2017}) 7. Rd1 {[%emt 0:04:23] Fernandez,Daniel Howard: 'Sam Collins: 'This general approach, waiting for Black to announce his setup before playing c3/d4 or d4 directly, was advocated by Gawain in his repertoire book several years ago.''} (7. c3 {Fernandez,Daniel Howard: 'Sam Collins: 'has been the most popular move.'' is main and we can only assume from his later play that Black wanted Fernandez,Daniel Howard: 'is main and we can only assume from his later play that Black wanted Sam Collins: 'Fernandez,D: 'is main and we can only assume from his later play that Black wanted'''} e6 (7... Ne5 {Fernandez,Daniel Howard} 8. d4 ({I think White is better after} 8. Nxe5 dxe5 9. d3 $14) 8... Nxf3+ 9. Qxf3 e6 10. Re1 Be7 11. e5 dxe5 12. dxe5 Nd5 $11 {I.Sukandar - N. Dzagnidze, Tromsoe 2014 (0-1 in 39).}) (7... g6 {(Fernandez,Daniel Howard) doesn't work well against c3 and d4 setups (one of the points made by Gawain in his book).} 8. d4 cxd4 9. cxd4 $14 e5 $2 10. Nc3 a6 11. Bg5 $16 {J.Riff - B.Rezki, Marseille 2009 (1-0 in 25)}) 8. d4 Be7 $11 {or similar, with a fairly solid position and completion of development one move away for both sides.} (8... d5 {Fernandez,Daniel Howard} 9. e5 Ne4 {F. Fernandez Fuentes - E.Regue Farran, Tarragona 2015 (0-1 in 42)} 10. Be3 $14 {and I'm not convinced ...Qc7 is a useful move for Black, so White seems to be half a tempo up on the standard 6...e6 7.c3 lines.})) (7. d3 $5 {(Fernandez,Daniel Howard) was played in G.Meier - M.Bach, Copenhagen 2010 (1-0 in 40). Obviously this isn't the most ambitious approach, but ...Qc7 is generally directed against d4 so the idea makes some sense.}) (7. c4 {(Fernandez,Daniel Howard) is also possible.} e6 8. b3 Be7 9. Bb2 O-O 10. Nc3 a6 (10... Ne5 $5) 11. d4 cxd4 12. Nxd4 $14 {with a space advantage and typical edge in E.Schmittdiel - N.Krieg, Germany 2012 (1-0 in 52) .}) 7... e6 {[%emt 0:03:38]} 8. d4 {[%emt 0:00:26]} (8. c4 $5 {was the logical way to implement a 'light square only' pawn structure. To avoid being slightly worse, Black has to make a tough strategic call between ...e5 and ...e5.}) 8... cxd4 {[%emt 0:00:53]} 9. Nxd4 {[%emt 0:00:03]} (9. Rxd4 $5 {merited consideration, still trying to set up with c4, e.g.} Rc8 10. Na3 Be7 11. Rc4 Qb8 12. Rxc8+ Qxc8 13. c4 $132) 9... Rc8 {[%emt 0:01:07] Fernandez,Daniel Howard: 'Sam Collins: '!?' '!?'' A nice point. Now White would really rather not play c3, so his options are limited. Fernandez,Daniel Howard: 'A nice point. Now White would really rather not play c3, so his options are limited. Sam Collins: 'Fernandez,D: 'A nice point. Now White would really rather not play c3, so his options are limited.'''} (9... a6 {Fernandez,Daniel Howard} 10. c4 Rc8) 10. Nb5 {[%emt 0:14:33] Fernandez,Daniel Howard: 'Sam Collins: 'This won't be repeated.''} (10. b3 $5 {Fernandez,Daniel Howard: 'Sam Collins: 'followed by 11.c4 is a way to get a Maroczy setup and would be my preference, for example'' This leads to the setup White wanted, he just has to see that ...e5 is not favourable.} a6 (10... e5 11. Nb5 Qxc2 12. Qxc2 Rxc2 13. N1a3 $14) (10... Be7 {Fernandez,Daniel Howard} 11. c4) 11. c4 Be7 12. Bb2 $11 {Fernandez,Daniel Howard: 'Sam Collins: 'Fernandez,D: '='''} O-O {Fernandez,Daniel Howard} 13. Nc3 {transposes to Monjac - Pridigar. Sam Collins: '' '' Sam Collins: 'with the type of position White typically aims for in this line: M.Monjac -L.Pridigar, Nova Gorica 2014 (1-0 in 29).'}) 10... Qxc2 {[%emt 0:10:43]} (10... Qb8 {(Fernandez,Daniel Howard) is also playable but there is nothing wrong with the forcing option.}) 11. Qxc2 {[%emt 0:04:16]} Rxc2 {[%emt 0:00:23]} 12. N1a3 {[%emt 0:01:32]} (12. N1c3 {(Fernandez,Daniel Howard) doesn't trap the rook, since} a6 13. Na3 (13. Nxd6+ Bxd6 14. Rxd6 Ke7 $11) 13... Rxc3 $1 {Sam Collins: 'transposes to 12.N1c3.'} 14. bxc3 Nxe4 $15 {gives Black a great position.}) (12. N5c3 {Fernandez,Daniel Howard} a6 $15 {also gives White no good way to catch the rook, and}) 12... Rc8 {[%emt 0:02:32]} 13. Nxa7 {[%emt 0:00:59]} Rd8 {[%emt 0:00:12] Fernandez,Daniel Howard: 'Sam Collins: 'It turns out that White can't hold his e4-pawn, after which there is no possibility of a white advantage.''} 14. N7b5 {[%emt 0:08:58]} (14. f3 {Fernandez,Daniel Howard: 'Sam Collins: '?' '?''} d5 $17 {Fernandez,Daniel Howard: 'Sam Collins: '!' '!' Sam Collins: ', threatening ...Bc5+, is easy to miss from a distance.' Sam Collins: ', threatening ...Bc5+, is easy to miss from a distance. Fernandez,D: '''' Fernandez,Daniel Howard: 'Sam Collins: '!' Sam Collins: ', threatening ...Bc5+, is easy to miss from a distance.''}) 14... Nxe4 {[%emt 0:02:56]} 15. f3 {[%emt 0:04:13]} Nef6 {[%emt 0:00:29]} 16. Nxd6+ {[%emt 0:02:09]} Bxd6 {[%emt 0:00:24]} 17. Rxd6 {[%emt 0:00:01]} Ke7 {[%emt 0:02:41]} 18. Rd4 {[%emt 0:14:34]} Ne5 {[%emt 0:05:21] Fernandez,Daniel Howard: 'Sam Collins: 'It's easy to imagine White becoming worse in such an endgame, but Vidit plays accurately and energetically to bring the position to safety.''} 19. Be3 {[%emt 0:00:51]} Nc6 {[%emt 0:06:05]} (19... Nd5 {is a bit more ambitious; Black's minor pieces are probably slightly better placed so he should think about fighting for an advantage.}) 20. Rxd8 {[%emt 0:02:48]} Rxd8 {[%emt 0:00:11]} 21. Bc5+ {[%emt 0:04:35]} Kd7 {[%emt 0:00:57]} 22. Nc4 {[%emt 0:05:54]} Nd5 {[%emt 0:02:13]} 23. a4 {[%emt 0:02:19] Whereas in this version, White' bishop has become active so although Black may still be optically for choice, there decidedly isn't an edge unless White messes up. Fernandez,Daniel Howard: 'Whereas in this version, White' bishop has become active so although Black may still be optically for choice, there decidedly isn't an edge unless White messes up. Sam Collins: 'Fernandez,D: 'Whereas in this version, White' bishop has become active so although Black may still be optically for choice, there decidedly isn't an edge unless White messes up.'''} e5 {[%emt 0:08:33]} 24. a5 {[%emt 0:16:24]} Ke6 {[%emt 0:02:22]} (24... f6 {is more patient and keeps open knight re-routings starting with ...c7, but should objectively also be nothing.}) 25. a6 {[%emt 0:01:10]} bxa6 {[%emt 0:02:47]} 26. Rxa6 {[%emt 0:00:04]} Kd7 {[%emt 0:00:04]} 27. b4 {[%emt 0:07:20] A final simplifying combination. Fernandez,Daniel Howard: 'A final simplifying combination. Sam Collins: 'Fernandez,D: 'A final simplifying combination.'''} Ndxb4 {[%emt 0:01:58]} 28. Bxb4 {[%emt 0:02:33]} Nxb4 {[%emt 0:00:06]} 29. Rd6+ {[%emt 0:01:11]} Ke7 {[%emt 0:00:17]} 30. Rxd8 {[%emt 0:00:01]} Kxd8 {[%emt 0:00:08]} 31. Nxe5 {[%emt 0:00:02]} 1/2-1/2


