1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 Bb4 5. Bg5 h6 6. Bxf6 Qxf6 7. e3 O-O 8. Rc1 dxc4 9. Bxc4 c5 10. O-O cxd4 11. Ne4 Qe7 12. exd4 Nc6 13. a3 Ba5 14. b4 Bb6 15. Rc3 $1 (15. d5 exd5 16. Bxd5 Bg4 $11 {½-½ (41) Zivanic,M (2459)-Yermolinsky,A (2522) Stillwater 2009}) (15. Rc2 Rd8 16. Rd2 Qc7 17. Ba2 Bd7 18. Qe2 Be8 19. Rfd1 Ne7 20. Nc5 Nd5 $11 {0-1 (39) Girya,O (2390)-Zaiatz,E (2441) Rogaska Slatina 2011}) 15... Rd8 16. Rd3 Bd7 $6 ({If Black would sense the danger, he would move the queen away from the potential rook attack:} 16... Qc7 17. Nc5 a5 18. Qd2 axb4 19. axb4 $14) 17. Re1 Rac8 18. Ba2 Qf8 (18... Be8 $2 19. d5 exd5 20. Nc3 Qf8 21. Nxd5 {would lead to the same disaster for Black as in the game.}) 19. Nc3 Be8 $2 (19... Bc7 {should have been played.} {After} 20. d5 exd5 21. Nxd5 {White is in possession, but at least Black's light-squared bishop can come out.}) 20. d5 exd5 21. Nxd5 {Suddenly White has an overwhelming initiative. Black doesn't have weaknesses, but his pieces can't make even one move forward.} Kh8 22. Bb1 g6 23. Nf6 Kg7 24. Qd2 Rxd3 25. Qxd3 Nd4 26. Nxd4 Kxf6 27. Nf5 Ba4 28. Qg3 gxf5 29. Qe5+ Kg6 30. Bxf5+ 1-0


