{[%evp 0,55,16,20,35,-1,6,6,27,-26,-25,-33,-25,-25,0,0,16,27,45,50,33,49,57,55,40,67,75,55,52,59,38,88,77,22,32,25,39,45,70,77,75,93,83,56,360,378,776,1565,1565,29988,29989,29990,29991,29992,29993,29994,29997,29998]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. f3 d5 5. a3 Bxc3+ 6. bxc3 c5 7. cxd5 Nxd5 8. dxc5 Qa5 9. e4 Ne7 10. Be3 O-O 11. Qb3 Nd7 12. Bb5 Qc7 13. Bxd7 Bxd7 14. Ne2 e5 15. c4 Nc6 16. Rd1 (16. Nc3 Rab8 (16... Be6 17. Nd5 Qa5+ 18. Kf2 Rab8 19. Rhd1 f5 20. exf5 Bxf5 21. Kg1 $14 {½-½ (37) Hausner,I (2441)-Markos,J (2495) Czechia 2005}) (16... Nd4 17. Bxd4 exd4 18. Nd5 Qxc5 19. Qxb7 d3 20. Qxd7 Rad8 21. Qc7 Rxd5 22. Qxc5 Rxc5 23. Kd2 Rxc4 24. Rhc1 $16 {½-½ (57) Cebalo,M (2519)-Paschall,W (2403) Nova Gorica 2005}) 17. Nd5 Qa5+ 18. Kf2 f5 19. exf5 Bxf5 20. Rhd1 $14 {0-1 (37) Ulybin,M (2586)-Cherniaev,A (2500) Biel 2004}) 16... Be6 17. Rd5 $1 {This is a nice and typical idea. White is glad to sacrifice an exchange and to straighten up his central pawns if Black accepts it.} Na5 18. Qc3 b6 (18... f6 19. Kf2 $14 {White keeps the rook on d5.}) 19. Rxe5 (19. O-O $6 Bxd5 20. cxd5 bxc5 21. f4 Rab8 22. fxe5 Rb3 23. Qxc5 Qxe5 $13 {½-½ (45) Mamedyarov,S (2799)-Korobov,A (2652) Huaian 2017}) 19... Nxc4 20. Rg5 f6 21. Nd4 Bf7 $2 (21... Qf7 22. Nxe6 Qxe6 23. Rd5 Nxe3 24. Qxe3 Rfd8 25. Rxd8+ Rxd8 26. O-O Qa2 {Black is a pawn down, but has very decent chances for a draw.}) 22. Nf5 $1 $18 Nxe3 23. Rxg7+ Kh8 24. Qxf6 Nc2+ 25. Kf2 Qxc5+ 26. Kg3 Qc7+ 27. e5 Be6 28. Rf7+ 1-0


