dark-squared bishop with''} 16... Qd7 {Yermolinsky,A: 'as' as Yermolinsky,A: 'Yermolinsky,Alex : 'as''} 17. Qc2 Bh3 18. Nc5 Bxc5 19. Qxc5 Bxg2 20. Kxg2 Rxe1 21. Rxe1 Ne4 {Yermolinsky,A: 'offers counterchances.' offers counterchances. Yermolinsky,A: 'Yermolinsky,Alex : 'offers counterchances.''}) 17. Nc5 Bf5 18. Re5 $1 Bc8 ({Yermolinsky,A: 'For better or worse,' For better or worse, Yermolinsky,A: 'Yermolinsky,Alex : 'For better or worse,''} 18... Bxc5 19. Rxf5 Bd6 20. Rxc6 Bxf4 21. Rxf4 {Yermolinsky,A: 'although White enjoys a sizeable advantage here.' although White enjoys a sizeable advantage here. Yermolinsky,A: 'Yermolinsky,Alex : 'although White enjoys a sizeable advantage here.''}) 19. Qa4 Bd7 (19... Bxc5 20. Qxc6) 20. Nxd7 $1 {Yermolinsky,A: 'Played with no prejudice. The c6-pawn will fall.' Played with no prejudice. The c6-pawn will fall. Yermolinsky,A: 'Yermolinsky,Alex : 'Played with no prejudice. The c6-pawn will fall.''} Nxd7 21. Re2 $18 g5 22. Bd2 Nb6 23. Qxc6 Rc8 24. Qh6 Rxc1+ 25. Bxc1 f6 26. Bh3 Bf8 27. Rxe8 {Yermolinsky,A: 'The young Indian star has certainly shown some serious positional chops today.' The young Indian star has certainly shown some serious positional chops today. Yermolinsky,A: 'Yermolinsky,Alex : 'The young Indian star has certainly shown some serious positional chops today.''} (27. Rxe8 Qxe8 28. Qxf6 Qe1+ 29. Kg2 Qxc1 30. Be6#) 1-0


