1. d4 {Perunovic,Milos} Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 (3. g3 {in an earlier round didn't cause Vidit serious problems after} Bg7 4. Bg2 d5 5. cxd5 Nxd5 6. Nf3 Nb6 7. O-O Nc6 8. e3 O-O 9. Nc3 e5 (9... Re8 {has been the main move, but Black has a new idea connected with the older continuation.}) 10. d5 e4 11. dxc6 Qxd1 12. Rxd1 exf3 13. Bxf3 bxc6 14. Ne2 Nc4 15. Nd4 Ne5 16. Bg2 Rb8 $5 $146 17. Nxc6 (17. f4 Bg4 (17... c5 18. fxe5 Rd8 19. Bf3 Bb7 20. Be2 cxd4 21. exd4 c5 22. Be3 $14) 18. Rd2 c5 19. fxe5 cxd4 20. exd4 Rfd8 $44 {[%cal Yc7c5]}) 17... Nxc6 18. Bxc6 Bxb2 19. Rb1 Rb6 (19... Bg4 $5) 20. Bf3 (20. Bxb2 Rxc6 21. Rbc1 $14 {is pleasant for White, but might be not enough to win.}) 20... Bf6 21. Ba3 Rd8 22. Rxd8+ Bxd8 23. Rd1 Bf6 24. Bc5 Rb2 25. a3 a5 $11 {Fedoseev,V (2707)-Vidit,S (2718) Danzhou 2018}) 3... d5 4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. e4 Nxc3 6. bxc3 Bg7 7. Nf3 c5 8. Be3 {An important crossroads. White goes for one of the main lines.} ({Another even more popular system is} 8. Rb1 O-O 9. Be2 {, but here} cxd4 10. cxd4 Qa5+ 11. Bd2 Qxa2 12. O-O Bg4 {remains a reliable antidote. A recent top-level encounter went} 13. Be3 (13. Bg5 h6 14. Be3 Nc6 15. d5 Na5 16. Rb4 b6 17. e5 Bd7 $5 18. Re1 Rfd8 19. Rd4 Bf5 20. Bd3 Bxd3 21. Rxd3 Rac8 $132 {Kozul,Z (2590)-Baramidze,D (2605) Austria 2014 The retreat on move 17 worked well also in subsequent email games.}) 13... Nc6 14. d5 Na5 15. Bg5 b6 16. Bxe7 Rfe8 17. d6 Nc6 18. Bb5 Nxe7 19. h3 Bxf3 20. Qxf3 Qe6 21. Bxe8 Rxe8 22. dxe7 Qxe7 23. Rfd1 Bf8 24. Rbc1 $146 (24. Rd4 Qe6 25. Qb3 Qxb3 26. Rxb3 Bc5 27. Ra4 a5 28. Kf1 Bb4 $11 {½-½ (33) Shulman,Y (2617)-Svidler,P (2739) Ningbo 2011}) 24... Qxe4 25. Qc3 Qb4 26. Qa1 Bc5 27. Qxa7 Qb2 $44 {/=, Aronian,L (2799)-Vachier Lagrave,M (2804) Tbilisi 2017 The exchange sacrifice in different versions is typical for the whole branch, Black's queenside passed pawns give him sufficient counterplay and compensation.}) ({A few weaks earlier in the blitz part of his match against Svidler Yu opted for} 8. h3 O-O 9. Be3 Qa5 10. Bd2 cxd4 (10... Nc6 11. Be2 Qd8 $5 12. d5 Ne5 13. Nxe5 Bxe5 14. O-O f5 15. f4 Bg7 16. Bc4 fxe4 17. Qe2 Kh8 18. Qxe4 Bf5 19. Qe2 a6 20. a4 b5 21. axb5 axb5 22. Rxa8 Qxa8 23. Bxb5 Qxd5 24. Bc4 Qe4 25. Qxe4 Bxe4 26. Re1 Rd8 $11 {Grachev,B (2654)-Vachier Lagrave,M (2789) Tbilisi WCup 2017}) 11. cxd4 Qa3 12. Be2 Nc6 (12... Rd8 13. O-O Bxd4 14. Nxd4 Rxd4 15. Qc2 $44 Nc6 16. Bb5 Be6 17. Be3 Nb4 $2 (17... a6 18. Bxc6 Rc4 $11) 18. Qc7 Rxe4 19. Bc1 $18 {Yu,Y (2759)-Svidler,P (2753) Shenzhen blitz 2018}) 13. d5 Ne5 (13... Nd4 14. Nxd4 Bxd4 15. Rb1 Qxa2 16. O-O e5 $5 (16... Bf6 17. Bf4 Qa5 18. e5 Bg7 19. Bf3 Rd8 20. Re1 b5 21. d6 Rb8 22. dxe7 Re8 23. e6 $18 {Yu,Y (2759)-Svidler,P (2753) Shenzhen blitz 2018}) 17. Bh6 Qa3 18. Rb3 Qd6 19. Bxf8 Kxf8 20. Kh1 (20. Bg4 $142 $14) 20... a5 21. Rd3 Bc5 22. Qc1 b6 $44 {Kortschnoj,V (2608)-Braun,A (2491) Pulvermuehle 2006}) 14. O-O ({After} 14. Nxe5 Bxe5 15. O-O {Black doesn't have to take the exchange and can opt for} Bd7 $5 16. Rb1 Qxa2 17. Rxb7 Ba4 $44) 14... Nxf3+ 15. Bxf3 Bxa1 16. Qxa1 f6 17. Rb1 a5 18. e5 fxe5 19. Qxe5 Qd6 20. Qe3 Bd7 $1 21. Bc3 (21. Rxb7 Rab8 $15) 21... b5 22. Re1 Rac8 23. Be5 Qc5 24. Bd4 Qd6 25. Be5 Qc5 26. Bd4 Qd6 {½, Babula,V (2556)-Plat,V (2539) Slovakia 2018}) 8... Qa5 {The most popular reaction. If Black wants to play the  sortie, this is the time to do it - later taking on c3 might not be a threat at all.} (8... O-O 9. Be2 {Here it's already better to change tack with} b6 $142 (9... Qa5 10. O-O Rd8 (10... Bg4 11. Rb1 b6 12. h3 Bxf3 13. Bxf3 Nd7 14. e5 Rac8 15. Qb3 e6 16. a4 Rc7 17. Rfd1 Rfc8 18. Bd2 Bf8 19. Be2 Nb8 {Onischuk,A (2681)-Puranik,A (2520) chess.com INT 2018} 20. Qa2 Nc6 21. Bb5 c4 22. Bxc4 Nxe5 23. Bxe6 fxe6 24. Rb5 $16) 11. Qb3 Qb6 (11... Nc6 12. Rad1 {} (12. Bc4 $5)) 12. Qa3 Nd7 13. e5 Nf8 14. Rfd1 (14. Rab1 Qc7 15. Qxc5 $36) 14... Qc7 15. Ng5 Ne6 16. Ne4 b6 17. d5 Bb7 18. dxe6 Bxe4 19. exf7+ Kxf7 20. f4 Bc2 21. Re1 Bd3 22. Bf3 Rac8 23. Qb3+ c4 24. Qb5 e6 25. a4 Bf8 26. a5 $14 {Ponkratov,P (2590)-Dubov,D (2666) St Petersburg rpd 2017}) 10. O-O (10. Qd2 cxd4 11. cxd4 Bb7 12. e5 Nc6 13. h4 Qd5 14. h5 Rfd8 15. Rc1 Qa5 16. h6 Bf8 17. e6 f6 18. O-O Qxd2 19. Bxd2 {1-0 (97) Aronian,L (2799)-Dubov,D (2666) Tbilisi 2017} Rac8 $15 (19... g5 $5)) (10. Rc1 e6 11. Qa4 Bb7 12. e5 Nc6 13. O-O cxd4 14. cxd4 Ne7 15. Nd2 Nd5 16. Nc4 Nxe3 17. fxe3 Bh6 18. Bf3 Bd5 19. Qa3 Rc8 20. Nd2 Qd7 21. Kf2 Bg5 $132 {Korobov,A (2678)-Artemiev,V (2704) Poikovsky 2018}) 10... Bb7 11. Qd3 cxd4 12. cxd4 Qd7 (12... Nc6 13. Rad1 e6 14. Bg5 Qd7 15. Qe3 f6 16. Bh6 Bxh6 17. Qxh6 Ne7 18. Bd3 Rac8 19. Rfe1 Nc6 20. d5 Nb4 21. dxe6 Qxe6 22. Nd4 Qe7 23. Bb5 Rfd8 24. h4 Ba6 25. Bxa6 Nxa6 26. h5 $36 {Gromov,S (2256)-Groot,P (2143) email 2014}) (12... e6 13. Rad1 (13. Rac1) (13. Bg5 $5) 13... Qd6 14. Bc1 Re8 15. Qe3 Ba6 16. Ba3 Qd7 17. Bxa6 Nxa6 18. Qb3 Rac8 19. Rd3 Nc7 20. Rb1 Red8 21. h3 h6 22. d5 exd5 23. exd5 Ne6 $1 $11 {Hort,V (2600)-Huebner,R (2595) Hamburg 1979}) 13. Rac1 e6 14. Rfd1 Nc6 15. Qb5 Rfd8 16. Bg5 f6 17. Be3 Na5 18. Qd3 Rac8 19. h4 Rxc1 20. Rxc1 Rc8 21. Rxc8+ {½, Babula,V (2572)-Ftacnik,L (2570) Czechia 2011} Qxc8 22. h5 $14 {/}) (8... Bg4 9. Rc1 O-O 10. Be2 Qa5 11. Qd2 (11. O-O $5 Qxa2 12. Ra1 Qe6 (12... Qb2 13. Qd3 Qb6 14. Rfb1 Qc7 15. Qc4 Nd7 16. h3 Bxf3 17. Bxf3 e5 18. dxc5 a6 19. Qd5 Rfb8 20. Rd1 Rd8 21. Rab1 Rab8 22. Qd6 $16 {Nguyen,A (2454)-Gupta,A (2614) Abu Dhabi 2018}) 13. h3 Bxf3 14. Bxf3 $44) 11... cxd4 $6 (11... Nd7 $142) (11... e6 $5) 12. cxd4 Nc6 13. Qxa5 (13. d5 $1 $36) 13... Nxa5 14. h3 Bxf3 15. Bxf3 Rfc8 16. Ke2 e5 $2 (16... Nc4 $14) 17. dxe5 Bxe5 18. Bg4 Rc4 19. f4 Bb2 20. Rxc4 Nxc4 21. Bf2 Re8 22. Bf3 $16 {Onischuk,A (2667)-Xiong,J (2674) Saint Louis 2017 For details about this line see the notes to this gamein CBM 178.}) 9. Qd2 {A standard reply, but Black should also know something about the alternatives:} (9. Nd2 $5 cxd4 (9... Bd7 {was MVL's choice...} {but Black does have some problems after} 10. Rb1 (10. Be2 Ba4 (10... cxd4 11. Nc4 Qa4 12. cxd4 O-O 13. O-O Rc8 14. Qxa4 Bxa4 15. Rab1 Nc6 16. d5 Nd4 17. Bxd4 Bxd4 18. Rxb7 Rab8 19. Rfb1 Rxb7 20. Rxb7 Kf8 21. g3 Bd1 22. Bxd1 Rxc4 23. d6 $1 $16 {Korobov,A (2687)-Vachier Lagrave,M (2811) Bastia rpd 2016}) 11. Qc1 cxd4 12. Bxd4 Bxd4 (12... O-O $5 $11) 13. cxd4 Nc6 14. d5 Nd4 15. Bd3 O-O 16. Qb2 Qb6 17. Nc4 Qxb2 (17... Qf6 $5 $132) 18. Nxb2 Bb5 19. Rc1 f5 20. Bxb5 Nxb5 21. a4 Nd4 (21... Nd6 22. e5 Rac8 $132) 22. Rc4 e5 23. f4 $14 {Aleksandrov,A (2589)-Zhigalko,A (2578) Minsk 2018}) 10... Ba4 (10... Qxc3 11. d5 b6 12. Bc4 O-O 13. O-O Qa5 14. Bb3 (14. Qe2 e6 $13 {Mamedyarov,S (2799)-Svidler,P (2765) Riadh blitz 2017}) 14... Qa6 15. a4 (15. Re1 Bb5 16. Bg5 c4 17. a4 cxb3 18. axb5 Qxb5 19. Bxe7 Re8 20. Rxb3 Qa4 21. Bd6 Nd7 22. Qb1 Rac8 23. Ra3 Qc2 24. Qxc2 Rxc2 25. Rxa7 Rxd2 26. Rxd7 Rxd5 27. Re7 Rxe7 28. Bxe7 Rd7 $11 {Parligras,M (2595)-Ipatov,A (2652) Baku olm 2016}) 15... e6 16. Re1 exd5 17. exd5 Bf5 18. Rc1 Qc8 19. Nc4 Na6 20. Bg5 $44 Re8 $6 21. Rxe8+ Qxe8 22. Nd6 Qd7 23. Nxf7 Qxf7 24. d6 Be6 25. Bxe6 Qxe6 26. d7 Bd4 27. Qf3 Rb8 28. d8=Q+ Rxd8 29. Bxd8 $16 {Verst,P (2307)-Goffin,P (2331) email 2015}) 11. Qxa4+ Qxa4 12. Bb5+ Qxb5 13. Rxb5 b6 14. dxc5 Nd7 (14... Bxc3 15. Ke2 Bxd2 16. Kxd2 Nd7 17. c6 Nf8 {Melkumyan,H (2620)-Khalifman,A (2632) Moscow 2012} 18. Rd5 $5 Ne6 19. Rc1 {}) 15. Ke2 Bxc3 16. Nb3 (16. c6 $5 Nf6 17. Nc4 $36) 16... O-O 17. c6 (17. Rc1 $142) 17... Nf6 18. Kd3 Bb2 19. Nd2 Rfd8+ 20. Kc4 Ba3 21. e5 Rac8 22. exf6 Rxc6+ 23. Kb3 Rd3+ 24. Ka4 Bd6 25. Rb3 Rd5 26. Rb5 Rd3 $11 {½, Navara,D (2741)-Vachier Lagrave,M (2779) Biel 2018}) 10. Nc4 Qd8 11. cxd4 O-O 12. Rc1 f5 $5 {is maybe the way to go:} 13. Qb3 (13. exf5 Bxf5 14. Ne5 {Schreiner,P (2432)-Filipovic,S (2226) Skopje 2015} Bxe5 15. Bc4+ Kg7 16. dxe5 Qxd1+ 17. Kxd1 Nc6 $132) 13... Kh8 (13... f4 14. Bxf4 ({Black had enough couterplay after} 14. Nb6+ e6 15. Rxc8 Qxb6 16. Rxf8+ Kxf8 17. Qxb6 axb6 18. Bxf4 Nc6 19. d5 exd5 20. exd5 Ne5 21. h4 Rxa2 22. Rh3 Ra1+ 23. Ke2 Ra2+ $11 {½, Ponkratov,P (2601)-Dubov,D (2696) 