32. Qc2 Bf8 (32... a6 $14) 33. Rxd2 Rxd2+ 34. Bxd2 Qd5 $14 (34... Qc5+ 35. Qxc5 Bxc5+ 36. Be3 $16)) (32. Qc6 $142 $1 {[%csl Rh6] Perunovic,Milos: '!' is stronger - White prevents both a6 and b5 while eyeing the h6.} Qd5 {Perunovic,Milos: ''} (32... Kh7 {Perunovic,Milos} 33. Qc2+ Kh8 34. Rxd2 Rxd2+ 35. Bxd2 Qd5 36. Be3 $16) 33. Qc2 $14 {/ / Perunovic,Milos: ''}) 32... b5 $6 (32... a6 $1 {} 33. Qg6 (33. Ke2 {Perunovic,Milos} b5 34. Bxd2 Qxa4 35. Qxa4 bxa4 36. Bxh6 $1 Rb8 $11) (33. Qc6 {Perunovic,Milos} b5 34. axb5 (34. Bxh6 bxa4 35. Qg6 Bxh6 36. Qxh6+ Kg8 $11) 34... axb5 35. Bxh6 b4 $11) 33... Qxa4 34. Bxh6 Bxh6 35. Qxh6+ Kg8 36. Qg5+ (36. Rxd2 {Perunovic,Milos} Rxd2+ 37. Qxd2 Qf4 $11) 36... Kh7 37. Qe7+ (37. Rxd2 Rxd2+ 38. Qxd2 Qf4 $11) 37... Kg6 $11 (37... Kh6 $4 38. g5+ Kh5 39. Qh7+ Kxg5 40. Rg1+ $18)) 33. axb5 Qxb5 34. Rxd2 Rxd2+ 35. Bxd2 {[%mdl 4096] Black with his isolated pawns faces an unpleasant endgame. However, White's task also isn't simple, as the material is greatly reduced.} Qb2 36. Ke2 Qb5+ 37. Qd3 $1 Qb6 {Keeping the  is a must.} (37... Qxd3+ $2 38. Kxd3 Kh7 39. h4 $18 {[%cal Yh4h5,Yd3e4,Yd2c3]}) 38. h4 a6 {Perunovic,Milos: '?!' Vidit plays passively. He should have sought a chance to lash out, e.g.} (38... a5 $5 {Perunovic,Milos: ''} 39. Qc4 e4 $1 40. Qxe4 (40. fxe4 Qb8 $132) 40... Qa6+ 41. Qd3 Qe6+ 42. Kd1 a4 $14 {/}) 39. h5 (39. Qd5 $1 {Perunovic,Milos}) 39... Qe6 (39... a5 {Perunovic,Milos}) 40. Bc3 (40. Qe4 $5) 40... Kg8 (40... e4 41. Bxg7+ Kxg7 42. Qxe4 $16 {} Qxe4+ $2 43. fxe4 Kf6 44. Kd3 $18 {- White's  are untouchable.}) 41. Qe4 Qa2+ 42. Ke3 Qe6 43. Qb7 Qc4 44. Qb4 Qc6 45. Qa5 Qf6 46. Qd5+ Kh8 47. Ke4 Qf4+ 48. Kd3 Qf6 ({Tying down White's pieces with} 48... Qg3 $5 {is more resilient.}) 49. Ba5 Qf8 $2 {Perunovic,Milos: 'Diagram [#]' The decisive error, we have repeatedly stressed Black must avoid the  swap.} (49... Kh7 $142 $16 { and the fight continues.} 50. Kc4 $16 {Perunovic,Milos} (50. Bc3 {Perunovic,Milos} Qf8 51. Qe4+ Kg8)) 50. Qd8 $1 $18 Qxd8+ 51. Bxd8 Kg8 52. Ke4 Bf8 (52... Kf7 {Perunovic,Milos} 53. Kf5 Bf8 54. Ba5 Bd6 55. Bc3 $18) 53. Ba5 Bd6 54. Kd5 Bb8 55. Bc3 Ba7 (55... Kf7 56. Bxe5 Ba7 57. Bd4 Bb8 58. Be3 Kg7 59. Ke6 $1 {[%cal Rf3f8]}) 56. Kxe5 Bb6 57. Kf6 Be3 58. Kg6 (58. Be5 a5 59. f4 Kh7 60. g5 a4 61. g6+ Kg8 62. Ke6 $18) 58... Bf4 59. Bb4 $22 Bc1 (59... Kh8 60. g5 $5 Bxg5 61. Bd6 a5 62. f4 $18) 60. Bd6 a5 61. f4 a4 62. f5 1-0


