{[%evp 0,70,25,16,10,25,17,16,25,18,30,-5,97,-51,-38,-27,-9,-15,-2,-11,-11,-31,-20,-34,-11,-40,-29,-8,11,6,22,14,16,12,10,25,43,43,73,54,68,53,48,20,52,37,51,63,73,16,38,24,8,44,39,31,46,0,0,33,10,40,54,53,58,8,12,-4,-5,-4,-9,-8,-8]} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. d3 Bc5 5. c3 d5 6. exd5 Qxd5 7. Bc4 Qd6 8. Nbd2 Bf5 9. b4 (9. Ng5 $2 Bxd3 $1 10. Nxf7 Bxf2+ $1 11. Kxf2 Qc5+ 12. Kg3 Bxc4 13. Nxh8 O-O-O {and Black has a crushing attack.}) 9... Bb6 10. Ng5 $5 {Now the above variation doesn't work for Black because there is no Bxf2+ followed by Qc5+.} O-O 11. Nde4 (11. Qf3 Ne7 $1 $13 {This looks risky for White.}) 11... Nxe4 12. dxe4 Qxd1+ 13. Kxd1 Bg4+ $1 14. f3 Bd7 {The knight on g5 is in some kind of trouble.} 15. a4 h6 16. a5 hxg5 17. Bxg5 (17. axb6 axb6 18. Rxa8 Rxa8 $11) 17... Bxa5 18. bxa5 b6 19. Bd5 {The only try.} Rac8 ({The exchange sacrifice} 19... Nxa5 $5 {could be tried if you play for a win!}) 20. axb6 cxb6 21. h4 Rfe8 {Preparing Be6.} 22. Bxc6 Rxc6 23. Rxa7 Be6 {White won a pawn, but there is no real winning chances with the opposite coloured bishops.} 24. Ra3 b5 25. Ke2 Rec8 26. Bd2 Rd8 27. Rha1 Kh7 28. Ra8 Bc4+ 29. Ke1 Rd3 30. R1a6 Rxa6 31. Rxa6 b4 32. Rc6 bxc3 33. Rxc4 Rxd2 34. g4 Rh2 35. Rxc3 Rxh4 1/2-1/2


