1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Nf6 5. Nxf6+ exf6 6. c3 Bd6 7. Bd3 O-O 8. Ne2 Re8 9. Qc2 {This is the main move with the idea to provoke a kingside weakening using pressure on the b1-h7 diagonal.} h5 $5 {This interesting move gained popularity in GM-level play in 2017. The idea is to gain some useful kingside space with ...h4 after White castles short. Also the normal g3 is discouraged as it can be met by ...h4.} (9... h6 {is the main move and also playable.}) (9... g6 {can be strongly met by} 10. h4 $1 {with the idea h4-h5 and a dangerous initiative for White on the kingside.}) 10. Bd2 (10. Be3 {This is the most popular and is analysed in other games..}) (10. O-O {is a positional approach and will be checked in other games.}) 10... Nd7 11. O-O-O Nf8 $132 {Black will follow with ...e6 and advance the queenside pawns.} 12. h3 (12. Nf4 $6 Bxf4 13. Bxf4 {Manukian,A (2196)-Vidit,S (2718) chess.com INT 2018} Be6 $1 {This normal developing move improves on the game and gives Black the better chances:} 14. Kb1 b5 15. Be4 Qd7 16. h3 a5 $15 {with a more pleasant position for Black.}) (12. Kb1 Be6 13. Ng3 g6 14. Ne4 b5 15. h3 f5 16. Nxd6 (16. Ng5 $6 Bd5 17. Rhg1 {1/2 (20) Moen,A (2330)-Hansen,T (2443) Oslo 2017} Be7 $1 {improves on the game} 18. f4 Bxg5 $1 19. fxg5 h4 $1 $15 {Closes the kingside. Black intends ...e6 and will develop queenside play.}) 16... Qxd6 17. f3 {Intending g2-g4 and Black must be very precise now:} (17. Bc1 $6 a5 18. c4 bxc4 19. Bxc4 Bd5 $15 {0-1 (36) Vignesh,B (2287)-Hansen,T (2408) London ENG 2017}) 17... a5 $5 18. g4 Qd5 $1 19. b3 a4 20. b4 fxg4 $1 21. hxg4 Qxf3 22. Rdf1 $1 (22. gxh5 $2 Bb3 $3 23. axb3 axb3 24. Qxb3 Qxd3+ 25. Kc1 Re2 26. hxg6 Nxg6 27. Qb1 Rxd2 28. Qxd3 (28. Rxd2 Qxc3+ 29. Rc2 Qe3+ 30. Rd2 Ra3 $19) 28... Rxd3 29. Rxd3 Ra1+ $19) 22... Qxg4 23. Rhg1 Qh3 24. Bxg6 Nxg6 25. Rxg6+ fxg6 26. Qxg6+ Kh8 27. Qh6+ Kg8 $11 {with perpetual.}) 12... Ng6 (12... Be6 {A normal developing move.} 13. Kb1 (13. g4 h4 $1 $15) 13... Bd5 14. Rhg1 b5 $132 (14... Bh2 15. Rh1 Bd6 $11)) 13. Ng3 (13. Kb1 {with a double edged position.}) (13. g4 h4 14. f4 Ne7 $1 15. f5 Nd5 $132) 13... Nf4 14. Bxf4 Bxf4+ 15. Kb1 h4 16. Nf5 Bxf5 17. Bxf5 Qd5 $11 {The position is approximately equal.} 18. f3 Bg3 19. Bh7+ Kf8 20. Be4 Qd6 21. c4 Rad8 22. c5 Qe6 23. Bf5 Qe3 24. Qc3 Qf4 25. Bc2 Bf2 26. Qb3 Bxd4 27. Rhe1 Rxe1 28. Rxe1 Qc7 29. Qc4 g5 30. Rd1 Be5 31. Rxd8+ Qxd8 32. Bb3 Qd7 33. a3 Kg7 34. Ka2 f5 35. Kb1 Qe7 36. Bc2 Qe6 37. Qd3 Kg6 38. b4 Bg7 39. Qd6 Be5 40. Qd3 Bf6 41. Bb3 Qe5 42. Kc2 Qb2+ 43. Kd1 Qxg2 44. f4 g4 45. Bc2 Qg1+ 46. Ke2 Qh2+ 47. Kd1 Qxf4 48. hxg4 Qxg4+ 49. Qe2 Kg5 50. Ke1 h3 51. Qe3+ Kg6 52. Bd1 Qe4 53. Qxe4 fxe4 54. Kf2 Be5 55. Bg4 h2 56. Kg2 f5 57. Bh3 e3 58. Kh1 e2 0-1


