{Diagram [#] In this game Vidit had huge advantage in the early phase of the game. However, he missed several chances and the game was likely to end in a draw. He played} 46... Bc2 {thinking that it is a draw in any case.} 47. b4 $3 {Quite unexpected turn of events. Black cannot stop the passed pawn, and if Black captures...} axb3 {Diagram [#]} (47... Bb3 48. b5 Bd5 49. b6) 48. Bb2 $1 {Now, Black is completely lost and has no available tricks. Levon won the game in few more moves.} h5 49. g5 h4 50. a4 Kg8 51. a5 Kh7 52. a6 Bd1 53. Kxd1 d2 54. Qxg7+ Qxg7 55. Bxg7 Kxg7 56. Kxd2 1-0


