{[%evp 0,91,18,24,59,59,54,52,52,40,42,10,20,6,7,3,7,-17,-14,-7,-9,-25,-18,-30,-2,-4,2,-2,26,-1,2,4,9,-7,19,12,12,11,4,9,4,5,16,13,8,8,3,10,0,6,28,38,68,24,35,-14,1,10,23,23,43,31,41,6,14,-19,-45,22,0,0,0,0,0,0,14,65,119,85,118,106,521,176,641,711,749,748,1222,1384,29985,29986,29987,29984,29985,29986]} 1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 cxd5 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. Ne5 Nf6 6. Bb5 Bd7 7. Nxd7 Qxd7 8. c3 e6 9. O-O Bd6 10. Re1 O-O 11. Bd3 Qc7 12. g3 h6 $1 {Prophylaxis against Bg5} (12... a6 13. Bg5) 13. f4 Rab8 14. a4 {Prophylaxis against the minority attack.} a6 15. Qe2 Rfe8 16. Qf1 $1 {[#] Prophylaxis against ...e6-e5! break.} (16. Nd2 e5 $5 17. fxe5 Nxe5 18. dxe5 Rxe5 19. Qf1 Rxe1 20. Qxe1 Re8 21. Qf1 (21. Qf2 Bc5) 21... Bxg3 22. Nf3 Bxh2+ 23. Nxh2 Qg3+ 24. Qg2 Qxd3 25. Bxh6 Nh5 $44 {[%cal Ge8e6,Ge6g6]}) 16... Nd7 {One of several possible strategies, preparing to block the kingside with ...f7-f5 and create an outpost on e4.} (16... Na5 $5 17. Nd2 Rbc8 18. Ra2 $13) (16... Ne7 $5 17. Nd2 g6 18. Nf3 Nf5 19. Ne5 h5 20. a5 Be7 21. Bd2 Kg7 22. Qe2 Nd6 $11) 17. Nd2 f5 18. Nf3 Nf6 19. Be3 Ne4 $11 {Black is fine.} 20. Ne5 Rf8 ({Another strategy: 2 outposts, as in Rodshtein's game:} 20... Bxe5 $5 21. dxe5 Na5 $13) 21. Qg2 Nxe5 22. fxe5 Be7 23. Rf1 Bg5 (23... Qd8 $5) 24. Bxg5 hxg5 25. g4 Qe7 26. a5 g6 27. c4 Kg7 $11 {The position remained approximately equal for a long time, but Carlsen pressed slightly thanks to a safer king and capitalized on Vidit's mistake in a likely time trouble.} 28. Rac1 Rbd8 29. cxd5 exd5 30. Kh1 Rd7 31. gxf5 gxf5 32. Bxe4 dxe4 33. e6 Qxe6 34. Qxg5+ Kh8 35. Rc5 Rg7 36. Qh4+ Rh7 $2 (36... Kg8 $11) 37. Qf4 e3 $2 38. Re5 Qc6+ 39. d5 $18 Qb5 40. Rg1 Qxb2 41. Rxe3 Rc8 42. d6 Qf6 43. Re6 Qc3 44. d7 Rf8 45. Re8 Qc6+ 46. Rg2 1-0


