{Diagram [#] In this game Vidit was holding comfortably. However, Fabiano was ahead on time while Vidit thought a lot and was playing on seconds for most of the game. Fabiano finally managed to get into 2 bishops vs knight endgame which he won without any mistakes. I am not sure if Fabiano studied this kind of endgame, or he won by playing it over the board. Either way it is impressive. Fabiano offered a really funny reason that he had to use the restroom!!} 99. Bxa4 Kf3 100. Bd4 Kg4 (100... Ke2 $5) 101. Bd1+ Kg5 102. Be3+ Kg6 103. Bc2+ Kf7 104. Bd1 Kg6 105. Ke6 Nh5 106. Bc2+ Kg7 107. Ke7 Ng3 108. Bd3 Nh5 109. Bg5 Ng3 110. Ke6 Nh5 111. Kf5 Kf7 112. Bc4+ Kg7 113. Bh4 Kh6 114. Bf7 Ng7+ 115. Kg4 Kh7 116. Kg5 Kh8 117. Kg6 Ne6 118. Bf6+ Ng7 119. Bxg7# {#} 1-0


