{[%evp 0,70,16,-12,13,12,15,-21,-11,-5,13,0,8,-12,2,-28,-24,-18,-21,-7,1,-48,-49,-78,-88,-85,-81,-76,-67,-67,-69,-62,-91,-75,-36,-97,-80,-68,-70,-102,-107,-103,-99,-145,-152,-184,-127,-108,-105,-82,-80,-157,-157,-200,-211,-200,-197,-197,-196,-181,-201,-354,-445,-828,-847,-1043,-1050,-1050,-1069,-1074,-1074,-1272,-1258]} 1. c4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 e6 6. g3 Qb6 $1 7. Nb3 Ne5 8. Bg2 {A positional pawn sacrifice to gain two tempi as compensation.} (8. e4 {is the main move and is analysed in other games.}) 8... Nxc4 $1 9. O-O (9. e4 Bb4 $1 {Pinning the knight is the best.} (9... d6 10. Qe2 $1) 10. Qc2 {(Cuenca Jimenez-Hungaski, Neuquen 2017)} (10. O-O Bxc3 11. bxc3 d6 12. Nd2 (12. Bg5 $6 {xf6 is not a real threat, so this move makes no sense.} e5 $1 13. Rb1 (13. Bxf6 gxf6 14. Qh5 Ke7 $17) 13... Qc7 $17 {1/2 (62) Kalashian,D (2451)-Petrosian,D (2501) Yerevan 2010}) 12... Nxd2 13. Qxd2 $1 {Clearing the way for d1.} O-O 14. Rd1 e5 15. Qxd6 Qxd6 16. Rxd6 Be6 $132) 10... d6 $1 11. a3 (11. O-O $6 Bd7 $1 12. a3 Bxc3 13. Qxc3 Rc8 $17) 11... Bxc3+ 12. Qxc3 Qa6 13. Bf1 b5 14. a4 Qb7 15. f3 bxa4 16. Bxc4 axb3 $132) 9... d6 $1 {A very important move. Black prepares ...d7 / ...c8 to defend the strong c4-knight.} 10. e4 $6 {A straightforward continuation, but regaining the pawn is better and equalises the game.} (10. Qd3 Ne5 11. Qb5+ Bd7 $1 (11... Qxb5 {is not recommendable because the black king remains in the centre and the c7-square is weak:} 12. Nxb5 Kd8 13. Rd1 $36) 12. Qxb6 axb6 13. Bxb7 Ra7 14. Bg2 d5 $132) 10... Bd7 $1 11. a4 (11. Qe2 Rc8 12. Rd1 Be7 13. Rd4 Qc7 14. Bf1 Ne5 15. Bf4 O-O $17 {(Lalith-Macieja, Internet 2018) White had no compensation for the sacrificed pawn.} 16. Bg2) 11... Rc8 12. a5 Qd8 (12... Qc7 $1 {is the strongest move:} 13. a6 bxa6 14. Rxa6 Be7 $17) 13. a6 b5 14. Nd4 b4 15. Na4 Be7 16. b3 Ne5 17. Be3 O-O $17 18. h3 Ng6 19. Qd2 d5 20. exd5 Nxd5 21. Bxd5 exd5 22. Rfc1 Rxc1+ 23. Rxc1 Qa5 24. Qe2 Rc8 25. h4 Rxc1+ 26. Bxc1 Bf6 $17 27. Be3 Bxa4 28. bxa4 Qxa4 29. Kg2 b3 30. Nb5 b2 31. Qd3 Qc4 32. Qxc4 dxc4 33. Na3 c3 34. Bxa7 c2 35. Be3 b1=Q 0-1


