{[%evp 0,61,23,13,28,28,59,16,15,2,17,22,18,-16,1,1,1,-4,-23,-21,-14,7,3,1,1,-32,48,38,46,56,67,67,75,33,53,58,49,48,51,76,84,88,79,79,70,76,76,75,81,81,76,76,76,25,50,-14,0,0,0,7,5,5,0,0] Fier and Vidit are both opening specialists and provided some interesting discussions. Let's see two games from their match.} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 {Vidit goes for the Petroff. He is a very agressive and entertaining player, but in a match it is good to be solid with Black.} 3. d4 Nxe4 4. Bd3 d5 5. Nxe5 Nd7 6. Nc3 Nxe5 7. dxe5 Nxc3 8. bxc3 Bc5 9. O-O O-O 10. Qh5 g6 11. Qh6 Re8 12. Bg5 {Diagram [#]} Bf8 $1 $146 {A very good novelty.} (12... Be7 {Black faces some problems after this move.} 13. Bxe7 Qxe7 14. f4 $14 {Asadli,Vugar 2572 - Mamedov,Nidjat 2609, Azerbaijan 2021}) 13. Bxd8 (13. Qh4 Be7 $11) 13... Bxh6 14. Bxc7 {Diagram [#]} Bf5 $1 $146 (14... Bd7 {- 149/(98)} 15. Rab1 b6 16. Ba6 Bc6 17. Bd6 Bf4 18. c4 d4 19. Rfe1 f6 20. c5 Bxe5 21. Red1 Kf7 22. Bxe5 fxe5 23. cxb6 axb6 24. Rxb6 Bd5 25. c3 {1/2 : 1/2 Konstantinov,Maxim - Murden, Clive, corr 2020/21}) 15. Rab1 (15. Rad1 {Diagram [#]} Bxd3 $1 (15... Rac8 16. Bb5 $1) (15... Rec8 16. Bd6 Rxc3 17. Bxf5 gxf5 18. Rxd5 Rxc2 $14) 16. Rxd3 Rac8 17. Bd6 Bf8 $1 $11 {with a probable draw.}) (15. Rfd1 Bxd3 16. Rxd3 Rac8 17. Bd6 Bf8 $1) 15... Rac8 (15... Bxd3 {Is enough for a draw.} 16. cxd3 Rac8 17. Bd6 b6 18. Rb5 Rxc3 19. Rxd5 Rd8 $1 $11 {followed by Bf8  Bf8}) 16. Bb5 $1 Re6 17. Bd6 Rxc3 18. Bd7 Rxd6 $6 (18... b6 $1 {was more precise.} 19. Bxe6 fxe6 $44 {and Black has a solid compensation.}) 19. exd6 Bxd7 20. Rxb7 Be6 21. d7 Bg5 22. Rb8+ Kg7 23. d8=Q Bxd8 24. Rxd8 Rxc2 25. Ra1 {Now White can try to press a little bit.} a5 26. Ra8 {After this move it is a draw.} (26. a4 $1 $14) {Diagram [#]} 26... d4 $1 27. Rd1 Rxa2 28. f3 a4 29. Rxd4 Ra1+ 30. Kf2 a3 31. Rda4 1/2-1/2


