1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Nc3 Nc6 4. Bb5 Nd4 5. Ba4 Bc5 (5... c6 6. d3 b5 7. Bb3 Nxb3 8. axb3 d6 9. O-O Be7 10. Ne2 Bg4) 6. Nxe5 O-O 7. Nd3 Bb6 8. e5 $6 Ne8 9. Nd5 Qg5 (9... d6 10. Ne3 c6 (10... Qh4 11. O-O Be6 12. c3 Ne2+ (12... Nf5 13. Bb3) 13. Kh1 Bxe3 14. dxe3 Nxc1 15. Rxc1 Rd8 16. Bb3 dxe5 17. Bxe6 fxe6 18. Qc2) (10... dxe5 11. Nxe5 Qg5 12. N5c4 f5 13. f4 Qxf4 14. c3 Ne6 15. d4 Qh4+ 16. g3 Qh3 17. Bb3) 11. c3 (11. O-O Bc7 12. c3 Ne6 13. f4 dxe5 14. Nxe5 Nxf4 15. d4 Bxe5 16. dxe5 Qxd1 17. Bxd1 Nd3 18. Nc4 Be6 (18... b6) 19. Na5) 11... Nf5 (11... Ne6 12. Bc2 dxe5 (12... Bc7 13. exd6 Qxd6 14. Nf5 Qd8 15. O-O) 13. Nxe5 Bxe3 14. dxe3 Qg5 15. Nf3 Qxg2 16. Rg1 Qh3 17. Rg3 Qh5 18. e4 Nf6 19. Qe2 Re8 20. Be3 Nf8 21. O-O-O) 12. O-O Bc7 13. f4 Nxe3 (13... dxe5 14. Nxe5 Nxe3 15. dxe3) 14. dxe3 Bf5 15. exd6 Nxd6 16. Ne5 Qe7 17. Qe2 Rad8 18. Nf3 c5) 10. Ne3 d6 11. exd6 (11. f4 Qg6 (11... Qh4+ 12. g3 Qh3 13. Nf2) 12. O-O f6 13. Kh1 (13. exd6 Nxd6 14. Nf2 N4f5) 13... c6 14. b4 Nf5 15. Bb3+ Kh8 16. Qe1) 11... Nxd6 12. O-O N4f5 (12... Bh3 13. Kh1) (12... N6f5 13. c3 Nxe3 14. dxe3 Bh3 15. Ne1 Nc6 16. Bxc6 (16. e4 Qg6 17. Kh1 Be6 18. Qe2 Ne5) 16... bxc6 17. Kh1 Be6 18. Qe2) 13. Ne1 Nxe3 $1 14. fxe3 Bg4 15. Nf3 $2 Qe7 (15... Qh5 16. Qe1 c6 (16... c6 17. Qg3 Rad8 18. d4)) 16. Kh1 (16. Qe1 c6 17. Qh4) 16... f5 $6 17. d3 (17. Qe1 $2 f4 18. exf4 Qxe1 $19 19. Rxe1 $5 (19. Nxe1 Be2) 19... Rxf4 20. Bb3+ Kh8) (17. d4 c6 18. Qd3 Bc7 19. Bb3+ Kh8 20. Ne5 Bh5 21. Bd2 Ne4) 17... Bxe3 18. Bxe3 Qxe3 19. Qe1 $6 Qxe1 (19... f4 20. Qc3 $132 Bxf3 $2 21. Rxf3 Qe7 22. Raf1 $19) 20. Raxe1 Bxf3 21. Rxf3 c6 22. Bb3+ Kh8 23. Rfe3 Rae8 24. h4 (24. Kg1 Rxe3 $19 {Colin,V (2415)-Sumets,A (2581) Calvi 2009} 25. Rxe3 $2 Re8 $1 {Another great intermediate move!} 26. Kf2 g6 $19 27. Rxe8+ Nxe8 28. Ke3 Kg7 {see 11.xf6.} 29. Kd4 {(Vigo Allepuz,D (2156)-Tsatsalashvili,K (2271) Barbera del Valles 2008)} Kf6 $1) 24... Rxe3 25. Rxe3 Re8 $1 (25... g6 26. Re7) 26. Rxe8+ Nxe8 $19 27. h5 h6 (27... g5 {transposes to 12.f3.} 28. hxg6 $2 hxg6 $1 29. Bf7) (27... Nf6 28. Bf7 Ng4 $3 {What a smart reply! Black ignores the f6-bishop, instead he creates discover threat on the c-file.} 29. b4 Nh6 $3 {Another brilliant continuation!} 30. Be6 g6 $19 31. d4 $2 Ng4 32. Bc8 Ne3) 28. Kg1 g5 (28... Kh7 29. Bf7 Nd6 30. Bg6+ Kg8 31. Kf2 Kf8 32. Ke3 $36 {Gordievsky,D (2471)-Sjugirov,S (2673) Khanty-Mansiysk 2014} Ke7 33. Kf4) 29. hxg6 {(Gonda,L (2522)-Horvath,A (2519) Balatonlelle 2009)} Kg7 $36 30. Bf7 $6 Nd6 31. Kf2 $2 Nxf7 32. gxf7 Kxf7 $19 33. Kg3 $5 Kg6 $1 $36 34. Kf4 $6 Kf6 $1 {The correct way to go to the endgame,} 35. d4 (35. a4 Ke6 (35... b5 36. axb5 cxb5 $15 {Kozhuharov,S (2446)-Sjugirov,S (2673) Chess.com blitz 2017} 37. b4 $5 Ke6 38. c4) 36. b4 b6 37. d4 $15 {De Paz Gonzalez,Y (2152)-Rund,H (2187) ICCF email 2020} Kd5 $6 38. Kxf5 $1 {The strong move before White castles!} Kxd4 39. Kg6 Kc3) 35... b5 36. c3 a5 $1 37. b3 a4 38. c4 Ke6 {and without queens Black also has a nice attack.} 39. Kg3 bxc4 (39... Kf6 $15 {Borsuk,K (2431)-Vaibhav,S (2600) Chess.com blitz 2020} 40. Kf3) (39... axb3 40. axb3 bxc4 41. bxc4 Kf6 {see 11.xf6.} 42. Kh4 {transposes to 12.f3.} Kg6 43. g3 Kh7 44. Kh5 Kg7 45. d5 cxd5 46. cxd5 Kf6 47. Kxh6 Ke5 48. Kg5) 40. bxc4 {(Zierk,S (2499)-Hosseinzadeh,N (2217) Chess.com blitz 2020)} a3 $1 41. Kf4 Kf6 42. d5 cxd5 43. cxd5 Ke7 $17 44. Kxf5 $6 Kd6 $1 {Similar like in the previous line above.} 45. Ke4 h5 46. g3 Kd7 47. Kd4 Kd6 48. Kc4 Kd7 49. Kc5 Kc7 50. d6+ Kd7 51. Kd5 Kd8 52. Kc6 Kc8 53. Kb5 Kd7 54. Kc5 0-1


