1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nxc6 bxc6 6. e5 Qe7 $1 7. Qe2 Nd5 8. c4 {A positional pawn sacrifice to gain two tempi as compensation.} Ba6 $1 9. b3 g6 $1 {A very important move. Black prepares ...d7 / ...c8 to defend the strong c4-knight.} 10. f4 $6 {A straightforward continuation, but regaining the pawn is better and equalises the game.} Bg7 $1 (10... Qb4+) (10... f6) 11. Qf2 Nb6 (11... Nb4) (11... Nf6) 12. Ba3 Qe6 (12... d6) 13. Nd2 (13. Nc3 d6 14. O-O-O O-O 15. g3 Rfd8 16. Bg2 dxe5 17. Rhe1 Rxd1+ 18. Nxd1 Rd8 19. Bb2 f6 20. h4 Bc8 21. h5 gxh5 22. Ne3 Bd7 23. Be4) (13. Bd3 d6 14. O-O O-O-O 15. Bc2 dxe5 16. f5 Qf6 17. Bb2 Bh6 18. Qc5 Qd6 19. Qa5 Be3+ 20. Kh1 Bb7 21. Bxe5 Qxe5 22. Qxe5 Bd4 23. Qf4 Bxa1 24. Nd2) (13. c5) 13... d6 (13... f6 14. Bd3 (14. Ne4 d6 15. c5 fxe5 16. Bxa6 exf4 17. O-O-O d5 18. Ng5) 14... fxe5 15. O-O d6 16. f5 gxf5 $132 17. Bxf5 $6 {xf6 is not a real threat, so this move makes no sense.} Qe7 $1 18. Qf3 O-O $17 {1/2 (62) Kalashian,D (2451)-Petrosian,D (2501) Yerevan 2010} 19. Qh5 Rxf5 20. Rxf5 Bc8 $17 21. Rff1 Bd7 $1 22. Rae1 {is the main move and is analysed in other games.}) (13... Bb7 14. O-O-O O-O-O 15. Ne4 d6 16. c5 dxc5 17. Be2 c4 18. Nc5 Qe8 19. Bg4+ Kb8 20. Rxd8+ Qxd8 21. Rd1) 14. O-O-O (14. c5 Bxf1 $1 15. Rxf1 (15. Kxf1 Nc8 16. cxd6 $17 cxd6 17. Re1 dxe5 18. Nf3 Nb6 19. Nxe5 O-O-O $1 {Clearing the way for d1.}) 15... Nc8 16. cxd6 cxd6 17. O-O-O d5 $132 18. Nf3 {is not recommendable because the black king remains in the centre and the c7-square is weak:} Qd7 19. Ng5 Ne7 $36 20. Ne4 Qc7 $1 {Pinning the knight is the best.} 21. Nd6+ {(Cuenca Jimenez-Hungaski, Neuquen 2017)} Kf8 $1 22. f5 Qa5 23. Nc4 dxc4 24. Bxe7+ Kxe7 25. f6+ Kf8 26. fxg7+ Kxg7 27. Qxf7+ Kh6 $132 28. Qf4+ $6 Kg7 $1 29. Rd7+) 14... O-O 15. Bd3 (15. Ne4 c5 16. h4 (16. Qh4 f6 $17 17. Bd3 Nd7 18. exd6 cxd6 19. Rhe1) 16... h5 17. g4 hxg4 18. h5 Bb7 19. Ng5 Qe7 20. Qh4 gxh5 21. Qxh5 $1 {is the strongest move:} Rfd8 22. Rg1) (15. c5 Bxf1 16. Rhxf1 Nd5 17. cxd6 $17 {(Lalith-Macieja, Internet 2018) White had no compensation for the sacrificed pawn.} Nc3 18. Rde1 Nb5) 15... c5 (15... Rfd8) 16. Rhe1 Rad8 (16... f6 17. exd6) 17. f5 gxf5 $17 18. Bxf5 Qh6 19. Re4 Qg5 (19... Bxe5 $17 20. Rg4+ Kh8 21. Rh4) 20. Rg4 Qe7 21. Ne4 dxe5 22. Rxd8 Rxd8 23. Bxc5 Rd6 24. Qg3 f6 25. Nxd6 cxd6 26. Bxd6 0-1


