{[%evp 0,111,19,29,23,12,37,14,-4,4,9,5,-21,-26,-4,-67,-22,-41,-28,-2,-12,-35,-30,-1,36,-37,-25,-40,-26,-13,13,-18,-18,-18,-18,-15,-30,-19,-35,-47,-37,-62,4,-16,-7,-20,-20,12,-14,-49,-5,-47,-5,6,14,-36,-57,-97,-23,-23,40,45,43,21,45,-8,86,0,-1,2,22,0,0,0,1,-17,-15,0,0,0,0,0,27,21,12,39,40,42,42,16,42,43,43,0,43,35,33,540,839,934,1022,1032,1075,1092,1105,1122,1157,1281,1283,1330,1330,1300,1894,1894]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. Bd2 $5 {A reversed Schmid-Benoni! To be honest, I had never seen it.} Bg7 6. e4 Nxc3 7. Bxc3 c5 8. d5 Bxc3+ {The most solid move.} 9. bxc3 Qd6 10. Qd2 O-O 11. f4 e6 (11... Nd7 12. e5 Qc7 13. h4 c4 14. h5 Nb6 15. Nf3 Bg4 16. hxg6 {A tough one for Vidit!} fxg6 $5 17. Ng5 Rad8 18. d6 exd6 19. Rxh7 Qc5 20. Rh6 $18 dxe5 $1 $11 {It's now too late for} 21. Rxg6+ $4 Kh8 22. Nf7+ {because of} Kh7 $3 23. Rh6+ (23. f5 Rxd2 {would surely have brought Black the full point.} 24. Ng5+ Kh8 25. Rh6+ Kg7 26. Rg6+) 23... Kg7 {and White wins!} 24. Nxd8 $11 {But} Rxd8 {was an easy draw:} 25. Rh4 Rxd2 26. Rxg4+ Kf8 27. Kxd2 Qf2+ 28. Be2 Nd5 $11 29. Rh1 Qe3+ 30. Ke1 Qxc3+ 31. Kf2 Qe3+ $11 32. Ke1 $5 Nxf4 33. Rh8+ Kf7 34. Rxf4+ $11 exf4 $1 35. Rh7+ Kf6 36. Rxb7 $8 c3) 12. Nf3 (12. Bc4 b5 13. Bxb5 exd5 {Suddenly, it's unclear who is playing for a win!} 14. Bc4 (14. exd5 Nd7) (14. Qxd5 Qb6 15. Qxa8 Bb7) 14... Bb7 15. Nf3 Nd7 (15... Rd8 16. Bxd5 Bxd5 17. Qxd5 $4 Qxd5 $3 {Finally Levon has got what he wanted, and it's a masterpiece! He's going to queen one of his queenside pawns, as Black is totally paralysed on the kingside, while his bishop is stuck on c2!} 18. exd5 Rxd5) 16. O-O Nb6 17. Be2 d4 18. e5 Qd7 19. cxd4 Rad8 {Unbelievably enough, Black never took a decision to swap queens. True, it was hard to see Levon's winning idea coming.} 20. Rad1 Bxf3 21. Rxf3 Qxd4+ 22. Qxd4 $2 Rxd4 23. Rxd4 cxd4 24. Rd3) 12... exd5 13. Bc4 Be6 (13... Nd7 $2 14. Bxd5 Qa6 (14... Nb6 15. Bxf7+)) (13... d4 14. cxd4 cxd4) 14. O-O d4 (14... Rd8 15. exd5 Bf5 (15... Bxd5 16. Rfd1 Bxc4 17. Qxd6 $2 Rxd6 $1 18. Rxd6) 16. Nh4) 15. f5 Bxc4 (15... gxf5 16. Qg5+ Kh8 17. Qf6+ Kg8 18. Ng5) 16. e5 Qd7 (16... Qd8 17. f6 Kh8 18. Qh6 Rg8 {Here as well Black has more than enough compensation!} 19. Ng5) 17. f6 1-0


