line just yet and played 18...Bc8?. Duda,Jan Krzysztof: 'Giri,Anish: 'In 2013, in the game betweed Adhiban and Ashwin, Black wasn't aware of this forced line just yet and played 18...Bc8?.''} (18... Bc8 $2 {Duda,Jan Krzysztof Duda,Jan Krzysztof: 'Giri,Anish: 'Duda,Jan Krzysztof''} 19. Nxe5 O-O 20. Nd3 $16 {Duda,Jan Krzysztof: 'was clearly better for White in Adhiban,Baskaran 2587 - Ashwin,Jayaram 2461, India 2013 Giri,Anish: 'was clearly better for White in Adhiban,Baskaran 2587 - Ashwin,Jayaram 2461, India 2013''}) 19. Nxe5 {Duda,Jan Krzysztof: 'Giri,Anish: 'Mikhalevski,V: '!'''} Bxg2+ $1 {Duda,Jan Krzysztof: 'Giri,Anish: '!' Giri,Anish: 'Mikhalevski,V: 'The only move again.''' The crucial intermezzo, intending to throw out the d8 queen with a check. Duda,Jan Krzysztof: 'Giri,Anish: 'The crucial intermezzo, intending to throw out the d8 queen with a check.''} 20. Kg1 $1 {Duda,Jan Krzysztof: 'Giri,Anish: '!' Giri,Anish: 'Mikhalevski,V: 'White also has no choice again.''' Forced as well. Now Black has no checks. Duda,Jan Krzysztof: 'Giri,Anish: 'Forced as well. Now Black has no checks.''} (20. Kxg2 $2 {Duda,Jan Krzysztof Duda,Jan Krzysztof: '(Giri,Anish) Duda,Jan Krzysztof'} Qg5+ 21. Kf1 (21. Kh1 $2 Qh5+ 22. Kg2 dxe5 $19) 21... Qxe5 22. Qxf7+ Kd8 23. Be6 Qf6+ $17) (20. Qxg2 $2 {(Duda,Jan Krzysztof) (Giri,Anish) is bad due to} Qh4+ 21. Kg1 Qe1+ 22. Qf1 Qg3+ 23. Kh1 ({or} 23. Qg2 Qxe5) 23... Qh4+ 24. Kg1 Qg5+ 25. Kh1 Qh5+ 26. Kg1 dxe5 $19 {After protecting the f7-pawn with a check Black captures the knight and obtains a huge material advantage.}) 20... Qf6 {Duda,Jan Krzysztof: 'Giri,Anish: 'Mikhalevski,V: '!' Mikhalevski,V: 'One of a few equalisers.''' After the game JKD said that he expected Vidit to follow a correspondence game with 20...0-0 which leads to a draw. There seems to be nothing wrong with Vidit's solution either. Duda,Jan Krzysztof: 'Giri,Anish: 'After the game JKD said that he expected Vidit to follow a correspondence game with 20...0-0 which leads to a 