exf6 Bxf6 18. Bh6 $16) 15. Be3 $1 {David Cummings: 'Another good setup for White is: Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '!''} (15. Bf4 {David Cummings} Rc8 16. e3 {with pressure.}) 15... Be6 {An ugly looking move. It shows that Black really is in some trouble. David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'An ugly looking move. It shows that Black really is in some trouble.''} (15... Rd8 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi' I would have still preferred to move the rook and keep at least the bishop on f5 more active.} 16. Qc1 $1 $14 {With all kinds of threats like Nxd5/Nxb5.}) 16. Nd3 $1 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '!'' The key manouevre. Once the knight lands on c5. Black pieces are completely paralyzed. David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'The key manouevre. Once the knight lands on c5. Black pieces are completely paralyzed.''} O-O (16... Nxd4 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi'} 17. Ne5 $1 $18 {is the clever point. The d4 pawn is poisoned.}) 17. Nc5 {David Cummings: 'White has used his extra tempi to establish this powerful knight on the c5-square, and this makes a big difference.'} Rfd8 18. Ra3 $1 {David Cummings: 'Activating his rook. Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '!'' Using tactical tricks to improve the rook's position. Once White gets control of the a-file, he will have complete domination. David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Using tactical tricks to improve the rook's position. Once White gets control of the a-file, he will have complete domination.''} Ra8 {David Cummings: 'Black cannot grab the b4-pawn, since:'} (18... Nxb4 {David Cummings: '?' Now the b4 pawn is poisoned! David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Now the b4 pawn is poisoned!''} 19. Qb1 Nc6 20. Ra6 Qc7 21. Bf4 $18 {David Cummings: 'and White wins material. Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '+-'' wins material. David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'wins material.''}) 19. Rxa8 Rxa8 20. Qb3 {David Cummings: 'White has pressure against both the d5- and b5-pawns, and it is hard for Black to keep both defended.'} Qd8 (20... Rd8 {David Cummings: 'is well met by' would cede the control of the a-file: David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'would cede the control of the a-file:''} 21. Ra1 $16 {David Cummings: 'and the rook joins the party Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '''}) 21. Rc1 $1 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '!'' The final precise move in the sequence starting with 14.Ne5! After this, strategically Black's position is lost. He can't avoid losing material as both pawns b5 and d5 are very weak. David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'The final precise move in the sequence starting with 14.Ne5! After this, strategically Black's position is lost. He can't avoid losing material as both pawns b5 and d5 are very weak.''} Rc8 (21... Rb8 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi'} 22. Nxe6 fxe6 23. Nxd5 $18) 22. Nxb5 {David Cummings: 'White is a clear pawn up, and still has the more active pieces.'} Qb6 (22... Bf5 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi'} 23. Nc3 e6 24. h3 h5 25. b5 Na5 26. Qb4) 23. Nxe6 fxe6 24. Bh3 $1 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '!'' Using tactics to keep my pieces active. David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Using tactics to keep my pieces active.''} Kf7 25. Rc5 Ra8 {David Cummings: 'Not:' White's position is completely winning. He is a pawn up and has better pieces. I had played really well in the last phase of the game, but I failed to land the final blow. Over the next few moves, I improved my pieces further but didn't make much progress. David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'White's position is completely winning. He is a pawn up and has better pieces. I had played really well in the last phase of the game, but I failed to land the final blow. Over the next few moves, I improved my pieces further but didn't make much progress.''} (25... Nd7 {David Cummings: '?' David Cummings: 'because of'} 26. Bxe6+ $1 $18 {David Cummings: 'and White crashes through. Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '+-!''}) 26. Bf4 $1 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '!''} Nd8 27. Bc7 Qb7 28. Qf3 $6 {David Cummings: 'A convincing alternative was: Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '?!'' I wanted to stop the f6 knight from coming to e4. This doesn't lose the advantage, but practically Bxd8 would have won the game on the spot. David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'I wanted to stop the f6 knight from coming to e4. This doesn't lose the advantage, but practically Bxd8 would have won the game on the spot.''} (28. Bxd8 $1 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '!'' Simplest. David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Simplest.''} Rxd8 29. Nc7 Rd6 30. b5 $18 {David Cummings: 'and Black is busted Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '+-'' and all of Black's pieces are tied up. Soon White will sacrifice on e6 and push the b-pawn. David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'and all of Black's pieces are tied up. Soon White will sacrifice on e6 and push the b-pawn.''}) 28... Bh6 29. Be5 Bg7 30. Kg2 (30. Nc7 $1 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi'} Ra1+ 31. Kg2 Qxb4 32. Bxe6+ Nxe6 33. Nxe6 {This was a difficult tactics to see in timetrouble.}) 30... h5 31. g4 (31. Nc7 $1 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi'}) (31. Qf4 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi'} Ra4 32. Nc3 Rxb4 33. Rc7 Qb6 34. Bd6) 31... hxg4 32. Bxg4 Ra4 33. Qb3 $6 {David Cummings: 'White doesn't spoil anything, but by playing a little statically he allows Black to keep going. Instead: Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '?!'' Another indecisive move. White was still completely winning, but after this practically the task became tougher. David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Another indecisive move. White was still completely winning, but after this practically the task became tougher.''} (33. Bc7 $1 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '!'' It was possible to finish the game with brute force! David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'It was possible to finish the game with brute force!''} Nc6 34. e4 $1 {David Cummings: 'should win comfortably, for example Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '!'' Complete aggression! David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Complete aggression!''} (34. Ba5 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi'}) 34... dxe4 35. Bxe6+ $1 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '!''} Kxe6 36. Qb3+ $18 {David Cummings: 'picking up the a4-rook Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '+-''}) 33... Ra6 34. Bxf6 {It's a pity to give the bishop. Already at this point I started to feel that I had lost considerable portion of my advantage and I might have to 'rewin the game'. David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'It's a pity to give the bishop. Already at this point I started to feel that I had lost considerable portion of my advantage and I might have to 'rewin the game'.''} Bxf6 35. e3 Rb6 36. Be2 Nc6 37. Qa4 Kg7 (37... Bh4 $5 {(David Cummings) was more resilient, since} 38. f4 {can be met by} Be1 {activating the bishop}) 38. f4 {Stopping Black's counterplay ideas like ...e5. David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Stopping Black's counterplay ideas like ...e5.''} (38. Nc3 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi'} Nxb4 39. Qe8 Rc6 40. Na4 $1 {is just too brilliant of a win!}) 38... Ra6 39. Qb3 Rb6 40. Bd3 Na7 $2 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '?'' So many times the 40th move is the critical mistake! David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'So many times the 40th move is the critical mistake!''} (40... Qb8 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi' It made more sense to just wait as it's not easy to remove the knight on b5 and convert the advantage.}) 41. Nc7 $1 {David Cummings: 'Going for the breakthrough' Peter expected me to exchange the knights, but this counter intuitive knight jump practically wins the game. David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Peter expected me to exchange the knights, but this counter intuitive knight jump practically wins the game.''} (41. Rc7 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi'} Qb8) 41... Rxb4 42. Nxe6+ (42. Qd1 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi' was also possible, but simplying to the endgame looked easier.} Rb2+ 43. Bc2 {with Qg4 next.}) 42... Kf7 43. Nd8+ Kg7 {David Cummings: 'Or:'} (43... Ke8 {David Cummings} 44. Qxd5 Qxd5+ 45. Rxd5 {defends the d8-knight and White remains two pans up}) 44. Qxd5 Qxd5+ 45. Rxd5 Rb3 46. Ne6+ $1 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '!''} Kh6 47. Nc5 $1 {David Cummings: 'With two extra pawns, White eventually brings the point home. Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '!'' I had to foresee in advance that I can defend the d3 bishop this way and avoid losing the e3 pawn. The position is winning but still needs precision. David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'I had to foresee in advance that I can defend the d3 bishop this way and avoid losing the e3 pawn. The position is winning but still needs precision.''} Rb2+ 48. Kg3 Nc6 49. Rd7 Nb4 50. Bc4 $1 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '!''} (50. Be4 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi'} Re2 {Now White has to give up either the e3 or h2 pawn.}) 50... Nc2 (50... Rc2 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi'} 51. Bb5 g5) 51. Nd3 $1 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '!'' The knight danced all the way from b5-c7-e6-d8-e6-c5-d3! David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'The knight danced all the way from b5-c7-e6-d8-e6-c5-d3!''} Rb1 52. Kf3 g5 53. fxg5+ Bxg5 54. Ne5 $1 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '!'' Again a very important move, using tactics to defend the e3 pawn. David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Again a very important move, using tactics to defend the e3 pawn.''} Kg7 {Now taking on e3 is threatened again. David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Now taking on e3 is threatened again.''} (54... Nxe3 55. h4 $1 $18 {David Cummings: 'wins a minor piece Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '+-!''}) (54... Bxe3 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi'} 55. Ng4+ $18) 55. Rd8 $1 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: '!''} Bxe3 56. Rg8+ Kh7 (56... Kf6 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi'} 57. Ng4+ $18) (56... Kh6 {David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi'} 57. Ng4+ $18) 57. Rg6 {Threatening mate with Bg8+-Nf7++. Black's pieces are too far and not coordinated. David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'Threatening mate with Bg8+-Nf7++. Black's pieces are too far and not coordinated.''} Rb8 58. Bd3 Rf8+ 59. Rf6+ {White will win the piece on c2. Black resigned. After this game I took the lead of the tournament and didn't let it go till the last! I was very happy to win such a prestigious even like the Biel GM, on top of that with a margin of 6 points! David Cummings: 'Vidit,Santosh Gujrathi: 'White will win the piece on c2. Black resigned. After this game I took the lead of the tournament and didn't let it go till the last! I was very happy to win such a prestigious even like the Biel GM, on top of that with a margin of 6 points!''} 1-0


