1. d4 {Perunovic,Milos Perunovic,Milos} Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 (3. g3 {in an earlier round didn't cause Vidit serious problems after} Bg7 4. Bg2 d5 5. cxd5 Nxd5 6. Nf3 Nb6 7. O-O Nc6 8. e3 O-O 9. Nc3 e5 (9... Re8 {has been the main move, but Black has a new idea connected with the older continuation.}) 10. d5 e4 11. dxc6 Qxd1 12. Rxd1 exf3 13. Bxf3 bxc6 14. Ne2 Nc4 15. Nd4 Ne5 16. Bg2 Rb8 $5 $146 17. Nxc6 (17. f4 Bg4 (17... c5 18. fxe5 Rd8 19. Bf3 Bb7 20. Be2 cxd4 21. exd4 c5 22. Be3 $14) 18. Rd2 c5 19. fxe5 cxd4 20. exd4 Rfd8 $44 {[%cal Yc7c5]}) 17... Nxc6 18. Bxc6 Bxb2 19. Rb1 Rb6 (19... Bg4 $5) 20. Bf3 (20. Bxb2 Rxc6 21. Rbc1 $14 {is pleasant for White, but might be not enough to win.}) 20... Bf6 21. Ba3 Rd8 22. Rxd8+ Bxd8 23. Rd1 Bf6 24. Bc5 Rb2 25. a3 a5 $11 {Fedoseev,V (2707)-Vidit,S (2718) Danzhou 2018}) 3... d5 4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. e4 Nxc3 6. bxc3 Bg7 7. Nf3 c5 8. Be3 {An important crossroads. White goes for one of the main lines.} ({Another even more popular system is} 8. Rb1 O-O 9. Be2 {, but here} cxd4 10. cxd4 Qa5+ 11. Bd2 Qxa2 12. O-O Bg4 {remains a reliable antidote. A recent top-level encounter went} 13. Be3 (13. Bg5 h6 14. Be3 Nc6 15. d5 Na5 16. Rb4 b6 17. e5 Bd7 $5 18. Re1 Rfd8 19. Rd4 Bf5 20. Bd3 Bxd3 21. Rxd3 Rac8 $132 {Kozul,Z (2590)-Baramidze,D (2605) Austria 2014 The retreat on move 17 worked well also in subsequent email games.}) 13... Nc6 14. d5 Na5 15. Bg5 b6 16. Bxe7 Rfe8 17. d6 Nc6 18. Bb5 Nxe7 19. h3 Bxf3 20. Qxf3 Qe6 21. Bxe8 Rxe8 22. dxe7 Qxe7 23. Rfd1 Bf8 24. Rbc1 $146 (24. Rd4 Qe6 25. Qb3 Qxb3 26. Rxb3 Bc5 27. Ra4 a5 28. Kf1 Bb4 $11 {½-½ (33) Shulman,Y (2617)-Svidler,P (2739) Ningbo 2011}) 24... Qxe4 25. Qc3 Qb4 26. Qa1 Bc5 27. Qxa7 Qb2 $44 {/=, Aronian,L (2799)-Vachier Lagrave,M (2804) Tbilisi 2017 The exchange sacrifice in different versions is typical for the whole branch, Black's queenside passed pawns give him sufficient counterplay and compensation.}) ({A few weaks earlier in the blitz part of his match against Svidler Yu opted for} 8. h3 O-O 9. Be3 Qa5 10. Bd2 cxd4 (10... Nc6 11. Be2 Qd8 $5 12. d5 Ne5 13. Nxe5 Bxe5 14. O-O f5 15. f4 Bg7 16. Bc4 fxe4 17. Qe2 Kh8 18. Qxe4 Bf5 19. Qe2 a6 20. a4 b5 21. axb5 axb5 22. Rxa8 Qxa8 23. Bxb5 Qxd5 24. Bc4 Qe4 25. Qxe4 Bxe4 26. Re1 Rd8 $11 {Grachev,B (2654)-Vachier Lagrave,M (2789) Tbilisi WCup 2017}) 11. cxd4 Qa3 12. Be2 Nc6 (12... Rd8 13. O-O Bxd4 14. Nxd4 Rxd4 15. Qc2 $44 Nc6 16. Bb5 Be6 17. Be3 Nb4 $2 (17... a6 18. Bxc6 Rc4 $11) 18. Qc7 Rxe4 19. Bc1 $18 {Yu,Y (2759)-Svidler,P (2753) Shenzhen blitz 2018}) 13. d5 Ne5 (13... Nd4 14. Nxd4 Bxd4 15. Rb1 Qxa2 16. O-O e5 $5 (16... Bf6 17. Bf4 Qa5 18. e5 Bg7 19. Bf3 Rd8 20. Re1 b5 21. d6 Rb8 22. dxe7 Re8 23. e6 $18 {Yu,Y (2759)-Svidler,P (2753) Shenzhen blitz 2018}) 17. Bh6 Qa3 18. Rb3 Qd6 19. Bxf8 Kxf8 20. Kh1 (20. Bg4 $142 $14) 20... a5 21. Rd3 Bc5 22. Qc1 b6 $44 {Kortschnoj,V (2608)-Braun,A (2491) Pulvermuehle 2006}) 14. O-O ({After} 14. Nxe5 Bxe5 15. O-O {Black doesn't have to take the exchange and can opt for} Bd7 $5 16. Rb1 Qxa2 17. Rxb7 Ba4 $44) 14... Nxf3+ 15. Bxf3 Bxa1 16. Qxa1 f6 17. Rb1 a5 18. e5 fxe5 19. Qxe5 Qd6 20. Qe3 Bd7 $1 21. Bc3 (21. Rxb7 Rab8 $15) 21... b5 22. Re1 Rac8 23. Be5 Qc5 24. Bd4 Qd6 25. Be5 Qc5 26. Bd4 Qd6 {½, Babula,V (2556)-Plat,V (2539) Slovakia 2018}) 8... Qa5 {The most popular reaction. If Black wants to play the  sortie, this is the time to do it - later taking on c3 might not be a threat at all.} (8... O-O 9. Be2 {Here it's already better to change tack with} b6 $142 (9... Qa5 10. O-O Rd8 (10... Bg4 11. Rb1 b6 12. h3 Bxf3 13. Bxf3 Nd7 14. e5 Rac8 15. Qb3 e6 16. a4 Rc7 17. Rfd1 Rfc8 18. Bd2 Bf8 19. Be2 Nb8 {Onischuk,A (2681)-Puranik,A (2520) chess.com INT 2018} 20. Qa2 Nc6 21. Bb5 c4 22. Bxc4 Nxe5 23. Bxe6 fxe6 24. Rb5 $16) 11. Qb3 Qb6 (11... Nc6 12. Rad1 {} (12. Bc4 $5)) 12. Qa3 Nd7 13. e5 Nf8 14. Rfd1 (14. Rab1 Qc7 15. Qxc5 $36) 14... Qc7 15. Ng5 Ne6 16. Ne4 b6 17. d5 Bb7 18. dxe6 Bxe4 19. exf7+ Kxf7 20. f4 Bc2 21. Re1 Bd3 22. Bf3 Rac8 23. Qb3+ c4 24. Qb5 e6 25. a4 Bf8 26. a5 $14 {Ponkratov,P (2590)-Dubov,D (2666) St Petersburg rpd 2017}) 10. O-O (10. Qd2 cxd4 11. cxd4 Bb7 12. e5 Nc6 13. h4 Qd5 14. h5 Rfd8 15. Rc1 Qa5 16. h6 Bf8 17. e6 f6 18. O-O Qxd2 19. Bxd2 {1-0 (97) Aronian,L (2799)-Dubov,D (2666) Tbilisi 2017} Rac8 $15 (19... g5 $5)) (10. Rc1 e6 11. Qa4 Bb7 12. e5 Nc6 13. O-O cxd4 14. cxd4 Ne7 15. Nd2 Nd5 16. Nc4 Nxe3 17. fxe3 Bh6 18. Bf3 Bd5 19. Qa3 Rc8 20. Nd2 Qd7 21. Kf2 Bg5 $132 {Korobov,A (2678)-Artemiev,V (2704) Poikovsky 2018}) 10... Bb7 11. Qd3 cxd4 12. cxd4 Qd7 (12... Nc6 13. Rad1 e6 14. Bg5 Qd7 15. Qe3 f6 16. Bh6 Bxh6 17. Qxh6 Ne7 18. Bd3 Rac8 19. Rfe1 Nc6 20. d5 Nb4 21. dxe6 Qxe6 22. Nd4 Qe7 23. Bb5 Rfd8 24. h4 Ba6 25. Bxa6 Nxa6 26. h5 $36 {Gromov,S (2256)-Groot,P (2143) email 2014}) (12... e6 13. Rad1 (13. Rac1) (13. Bg5 $5) 13... Qd6 14. Bc1 Re8 15. Qe3 Ba6 16. Ba3 Qd7 17. Bxa6 Nxa6 18. Qb3 Rac8 19. Rd3 Nc7 20. Rb1 Red8 21. h3 h6 22. d5 exd5 23. exd5 Ne6 $1 $11 {Hort,V (2600)-Huebner,R (2595) Hamburg 1979}) 13. Rac1 e6 14. Rfd1 Nc6 15. Qb5 Rfd8 16. Bg5 f6 17. Be3 Na5 18. Qd3 Rac8 19. h4 Rxc1 20. Rxc1 Rc8 21. Rxc8+ {½, Babula,V (2572)-Ftacnik,L (2570) Czechia 2011} Qxc8 22. h5 $14 {/}) (8... Bg4 9. Rc1 O-O 10. Be2 Qa5 11. Qd2 (11. O-O $5 Qxa2 12. Ra1 Qe6 (12... Qb2 13. Qd3 Qb6 14. Rfb1 Qc7 15. Qc4 Nd7 16. h3 Bxf3 17. Bxf3 e5 18. dxc5 a6 19. Qd5 Rfb8 20. Rd1 Rd8 21. Rab1 Rab8 22. Qd6 $16 {Nguyen,A (2454)-Gupta,A (2614) Abu Dhabi 2018}) 13. h3 Bxf3 14. Bxf3 $44) 11... cxd4 $6 (11... Nd7 $142) (11... e6 $5) 12. cxd4 Nc6 13. Qxa5 (13. d5 $1 $36) 13... Nxa5 14. h3 Bxf3 15. Bxf3 Rfc8 16. Ke2 e5 $2 (16... Nc4 $14) 17. dxe5 Bxe5 18. Bg4 Rc4 19. f4 Bb2 20. Rxc4 Nxc4 21. Bf2 Re8 22. Bf3 $16 {Onischuk,A (2667)-Xiong,J (2674) Saint Louis 2017 For details about this line see the notes to this gamein CBM 178.}) 9. Qd2 {A standard reply, but Black should also know something about the alternatives:} (9. Nd2 $5 cxd4 (9... Bd7 {was MVL's choice...} {but Black does have some problems after} 10. Rb1 (10. Be2 Ba4 (10... cxd4 11. Nc4 Qa4 12. cxd4 O-O 13. O-O Rc8 14. Qxa4 Bxa4 15. Rab1 Nc6 16. d5 Nd4 17. Bxd4 Bxd4 18. Rxb7 Rab8 19. Rfb1 Rxb7 20. Rxb7 Kf8 21. g3 Bd1 22. Bxd1 Rxc4 23. d6 $1 $16 {Korobov,A (2687)-Vachier Lagrave,M (2811) Bastia rpd 2016}) 11. Qc1 cxd4 12. Bxd4 Bxd4 (12... O-O $5 $11) 13. cxd4 Nc6 14. d5 Nd4 15. Bd3 O-O 16. Qb2 Qb6 17. Nc4 Qxb2 (17... Qf6 $5 $132) 18. Nxb2 Bb5 19. Rc1 f5 20. Bxb5 Nxb5 21. a4 Nd4 (21... Nd6 22. e5 Rac8 $132) 22. Rc4 e5 23. f4 $14 {Aleksandrov,A (2589)-Zhigalko,A (2578) Minsk 2018}) 10... Ba4 (10... Qxc3 11. d5 b6 12. Bc4 O-O 13. O-O Qa5 14. Bb3 (14. Qe2 e6 $13 {Mamedyarov,S (2799)-Svidler,P (2765) Riadh blitz 2017}) 14... Qa6 15. a4 (15. Re1 Bb5 16. Bg5 c4 17. a4 cxb3 18. axb5 Qxb5 19. Bxe7 Re8 20. Rxb3 Qa4 21. Bd6 Nd7 22. Qb1 Rac8 23. Ra3 Qc2 24. Qxc2 Rxc2 25. Rxa7 Rxd2 26. Rxd7 Rxd5 27. Re7 Rxe7 28. Bxe7 Rd7 $11 {Parligras,M (2595)-Ipatov,A (2652) Baku olm 2016}) 15... e6 16. Re1 exd5 17. exd5 Bf5 18. Rc1 Qc8 19. Nc4 Na6 20. Bg5 $44 Re8 $6 21. Rxe8+ Qxe8 22. Nd6 Qd7 23. Nxf7 Qxf7 24. d6 Be6 25. Bxe6 Qxe6 26. d7 Bd4 27. Qf3 Rb8 28. d8=Q+ Rxd8 29. Bxd8 $16 {Verst,P (2307)-Goffin,P (2331) email 2015}) 11. Qxa4+ Qxa4 12. Bb5+ Qxb5 13. Rxb5 b6 14. dxc5 Nd7 (14... Bxc3 15. Ke2 Bxd2 16. Kxd2 Nd7 17. c6 Nf8 {Melkumyan,H (2620)-Khalifman,A (2632) Moscow 2012} 18. Rd5 $5 Ne6 19. Rc1 {}) 15. Ke2 Bxc3 16. Nb3 (16. c6 $5 Nf6 17. Nc4 $36) 16... O-O 17. c6 (17. Rc1 $142) 17... Nf6 18. Kd3 Bb2 19. Nd2 Rfd8+ 20. Kc4 Ba3 21. e5 Rac8 22. exf6 Rxc6+ 23. Kb3 Rd3+ 24. Ka4 Bd6 25. Rb3 Rd5 26. Rb5 Rd3 $11 {½, Navara,D (2741)-Vachier Lagrave,M (2779) Biel 2018}) 10. Nc4 Qd8 11. cxd4 O-O 12. Rc1 f5 $5 {is maybe the way to go:} 13. Qb3 (13. exf5 Bxf5 14. Ne5 {Schreiner,P (2432)-Filipovic,S (2226) Skopje 2015} Bxe5 15. Bc4+ Kg7 16. dxe5 Qxd1+ 17. Kxd1 Nc6 $132) 13... Kh8 (13... f4 14. Bxf4 ({Black had enough couterplay after} 14. Nb6+ e6 15. Rxc8 Qxb6 16. Rxf8+ Kxf8 17. Qxb6 axb6 18. Bxf4 Nc6 19. d5 exd5 20. exd5 Ne5 21. h4 Rxa2 22. Rh3 Ra1+ 23. Ke2 Ra2+ $11 {½, Ponkratov,P (2601)-Dubov,D (2696) Sochi 2018}) 14... Nc6 15. Ne5+ e6 16. Nxc6 bxc6 17. Be3 Bxd4 18. Bxd4 Qxd4 19. f3 Rd8 20. Be2 Bd7 21. Bc4 Rab8 22. Rd1 Rxb3 23. Rxd4 Rb1+ 24. Rd1 Rxd1+ 25. Kxd1 Rb8 26. Kc2 $14 {[%csl Ra7,Rc6,Re6] Mesquita,F (2341)-O'Grady,J (2296) email 2011}) 14. Ne5 Bxe5 (14... f4 15. Bd2 Nc6 16. Nf7+ Rxf7 17. Qxf7 Nxd4 18. Bc4 f3 19. gxf3 Bh3 20. Rg1 Qd6 21. Rg3 Be6 22. Bxe6 Nxe6 23. Rh3 Rd8 24. Be3 Qd3 25. e5 Nd4 26. Bxd4 Qxd4 27. Kf1 Qd2 28. Re1 $18 {Kavutskiy,K (2369)-Paragua,M (2513) Las Vegas 2017}) 15. dxe5 Nc6 16. Rd1 Qa5+ 17. Bd2 Qb6 18. Bc4 fxe4 19. O-O Qxb3 20. axb3 Bg4 21. Rde1 Rfd8 22. Bc3 Bf5 23. h3 Nd4 24. Rd1 b5 $132 {=, Babula,V (2572)-Hoffmann,M (2496) Germany 2012}) (9. Bd2 O-O 10. Be2 e6 (10... Bg4 $142 11. O-O Rd8 $132 {or 11...e6 is a more circumspect choice.}) 11. O-O Qc7 12. Rc1 Nd7 13. e5 a6 14. h4 b5 15. h5 Bb7 16. Ng5 (16. h6 Bh8 17. a4 $36) 16... Rad8 17. hxg6 hxg6 18. Qe1 Rfe8 19. f4 Nf8 20. Be3 cxd4 21. cxd4 Qd7 22. Bd3 f5 23. Rf2 Bh6 24. Nf3 Rc8 25. Rfc2 Rxc2 26. Rxc2 Rc8 $11 {Sunilduth Lyna,N (2573)-Duda,J (2724) Caleta 2018}) 9... O-O (9... Nc6 {is an alternative, which retains its good reputation. As it was also covered last year in the notes to Onischuk-Xiong, we will mention just a few more recent examples:} 10. Rb1 {is currently more popular:} (10. Rc1 cxd4 11. cxd4 Qxd2+ 12. Kxd2 O-O 13. Bb5 (13. d5 Rd8 14. Kc2 Na5 15. Bg5 Bd7 16. Bd3 f5 17. Kb1 fxe4 18. Bxe4 Bf5 19. Bxf5 gxf5 20. Bxe7 Rxd5 21. Rc5 Rxc5 22. Bxc5 b6 $11 {½, Neumeier,L (2333)-Weber,M (2243) Germany 2018}) 13... f5 $1 14. exf5 Bxf5 15. Ke2 (15. Bxc6 bxc6 16. Rxc6 Rfb8 17. Kc3 Rb6 $44) 15... Rad8 (15... Be6 $1 16. Bc4 Bxc4+ 17. Rxc4 Rad8 18. Rb1 Rd7 $11) 16. Bxc6 bxc6 17. Rxc6 Be4 18. Re6 Bxf3+ 19. gxf3 Bf6 20. Rc1 Rd7 21. Rc4 Rb8 22. a4 Kf7 23. Rec6 Rb2+ 24. Kd3 Ra2 25. Ke4 Bh4 26. Rc8 Bxf2 27. Bh6 $13 {Korobov,A (2652)-Ivanchuk,V (2726) Huaian rpd 2017}) {Lately Black has been doing OK after} 10... a6 (10... cxd4 11. cxd4 O-O (11... Qxd2+ 12. Kxd2 O-O 13. d5 $5 (13. Bd3 e6 14. Rhc1 Rd8 15. Rc4 Bd7 {and in practice White hasn't been able to prove an advantage in this typical Grünfeld endgame:} 16. Bg5 f6 17. Be3 b6 (17... Bf8 18. Ke2 Be8 19. Bd2 Rd7 20. Rc2 Rad8 21. Bb5 Re7 22. e5 Bg7 23. Be3 Rc7 24. exf6 Bxf6 25. Bd3 g5 26. g4 h6 27. Be4 Kg7 28. Kf1 Bg6 $11 {Sanikidze,T (2542)-Nepomniachtchi,I (2729) Aix les Bains 2011}) 18. Ke2 Rac8 19. Rbc1 Bf8 20. g4 Bd6 21. h3 Kf7 22. R4c3 Bb4 23. Rc4 Bd6 24. R4c3 Bb4 25. Rc4 Ba3 26. R1c3 Bb4 $132 {Akobian,V (2647)-Hansen,E (2629) chess.com INT 2018}) 13... Rd8 14. Bd3 Na5 15. Bg5 f6 16. Bf4 b6 17. Bb5 e5 18. Be3 Bd7 19. Rhc1 Bxb5 20. Rxb5 Nb7 21. Ke2 Nd6 22. Rb4 a5 23. Rxb6 Nxe4 24. Nd2 Nxd2 25. Bxd2 Rxd5 26. Rc7 $44 {Svidler,P (2769)-Hammer,J (2608) Stavanger 2013 Although this subline seems more promising and White went on to win the game, the evaluation is still far from clear - see the notes to this game in CBM 155 by Marin.}) 12. Qxa5 Nxa5 13. Bd3 Bg4 (13... Rd8 14. Ke2 Bg4 15. d5 e6 16. Bg5 f6 17. Bd2 b6 18. Bxa5 bxa5 (18... exd5 19. h3 $5 dxe4 (19... Bxf3+ 20. Kxf3 bxa5 21. exd5 $14) 20. Bxe4 (20. Bc4+ Kh8 21. hxg4 exf3+ 22. Kxf3 bxa5 23. Bf7 $44) 20... Re8 21. hxg4 Rxe4+ 22. Kd3 Rxg4 23. Bd2 Rxg2 24. Be3 $14) 19. h3 Bxf3+ 20. Kxf3 f5 21. Rhd1 $14 {Harutyunian,T (2421)-Sarana,A (2377) Kirishi 2014}) 14. h3 (14. Ke2 Rad8 15. d5 f5 16. Rhc1 e6 17. h3 Bxf3+ 18. gxf3 fxe4 19. fxe4 exd5 20. Rb5 dxe4 21. Bxe4 b6 22. Rc7 $14 {Matlakov,M (2693)-Bok,B (2587) Moscow 2015}) 14... Bxf3 15. gxf3 Rfd8 16. d5 e6 17. Bg5 Bc3+ $5 (17... f6 18. Bd2 b6 19. Bxa5 bxa5 20. Bc4 Rac8 21. Bb3 exd5 22. Bxd5+ Kf8 23. O-O Rc7 24. Rb5 f5 25. Rxa5 Bd4 26. Rb5 $14 {Onischuk,A (2672)-Robson,R (2660) Saint Louis 2018}) 18. Ke2 f6 19. Rhc1 fxg5 20. Rxc3 exd5 21. Rb5 b6 22. Rxd5 Rxd5 23. exd5 Rd8 24. Be4 Rd7 25. Ke3 Kf7 26. Kd4 Nb7 $11 {Socko,B (2584)-Swiercz,D (2655) Civitanova Marche 2016}) 11. Rc1 cxd4 12. cxd4 Qxd2+ 13. Kxd2 f5 14. e5 O-O $5 (14... Be6 15. Bc4 Bxc4 16. Rxc4 {causes Black more problems}) 15. Bc4+ e6 16. Ke2 Bd7 17. h4 (17. d5 Nxe5 18. Nxe5 Bxe5 19. dxe6 Bb5 20. Bxb5 axb5 21. Rc5 Bf6 22. Rxb5 Rfe8 23. Rxb7 Rxa2+ 24. Kf3 Ra6 25. Rd1 Raxe6 26. Rdd7 R6e7 $11 {Akobian,V (2647)-Durarbayli,V (2618) Saint Louis 2018}) 17... Rfc8 (17... Rac8 18. Bd2 (18. d5 $1 Nxe5 19. Nxe5 Bxe5 20. dxe6 $16) 18... h6 19. Bb3 Kf7 20. Rhg1 Rfd8 21. g4 Ne7 22. g5 h5 23. Ba5 Re8 24. Bb4 Bf8 $15 {So,W (2815)-Giri,A (2785) chess.com INT 2017}) 18. Ng5 (18. d5 Nxe5 19. Nxe5 Bxe5 20. dxe6 Bc6 $132) 18... Nd8 19. Bb3 a5 $5 (19... h6 20. Nh3 Rxc1 21. Rxc1 Rc8 22. Rxc8 Bxc8 {Akobian,V (2641)-Durarbayli,V (2618) Saint Louis 2018} 23. Nf4 Kf7 24. g4 $1 $14 {} fxg4 25. Bc2) 20. a4 b5 21. axb5 h6 22. Nh3 Bxb5+ 23. Kd2 Kf7 24. Nf4 Bf8 25. d5 Bb4+ 26. Kd1 Kg7 27. Bb6 g5 28. hxg5 hxg5 29. Rxc8 (29. Nxe6+ Nxe6 30. dxe6 Bc6 $36) 29... Rxc8 30. Bxd8 gxf4 31. Bf6+ Kg6 32. dxe6 a4 33. Bd5 a3 34. Bf3 Ba4+ {½, Lunek,F (2297)-Karakas,S (2264) email 2015} 35. Ke2 Bb5+ $11) 10. Rc1 Nd7 {A rare line, which hs started appearing more often lately. Black's ide is not so much to put White's  undedr pressure, but rather to blockade it and achieve a position with a fixed pawn structure.} ({In CBM 178 we also checked the popular} 10... Rd8 11. d5 e6 12. Bg5 f6 (12... Rd6 13. Be2 $5 exd5 14. exd5 b5 15. Bf4 Rd8 16. O-O Bb7 17. d6 Nd7 18. Rfd1 {Mesaros,F (2415)-Rajkovic,M (2305) Paracin 2017} Re8 $132) 13. Be3 Nc6 14. Bd3 {and now:} {Svidler currently prefers} Ne7 ({Last year we briefly mentioned} 14... exd5 15. exd5 c4) ({and also} 14... b6 15. O-O Ba6 16. Be2 Qa4 17. c4 Na5 18. Qd1 Qxa2 ({Black spurns the safer} 18... Qxd1 19. Rfxd1 Re8 $132) 19. Ra1 Qb2 20. Ra4 exd5 21. exd5 Bc8 22. Bxc5 Bd7 23. Ra1 Re8 24. Bd3 f5 25. Rb1 Qa2 26. Bd4 Bxd4 27. Nxd4 Qa3 28. Qd2 Nb7 29. h4 Qf8 30. h5 Nc5 31. Bc2 Qf6 $13 {/, Elias,H (2057)-Khanas,V (2184) email 2017} 32. f4 Ne4 33. Bxe4 fxe4 34. Nc2 gxh5 35. f5 Re7 36. Rbe1 Rae8 37. Nd4 Re5 38. Qa2 a5 39. Qa1 R5e7 40. Qd1 Rg7 41. Ne6 Rg4 42. Rf2 Kh8 43. Qb1 Rc8 44. Qxb6 Rcg8 45.