: 'The typical plan in the positions without the a-pawn would be a massive invasion starting with' The typical plan in the positions without the a-pawn would be a massive invasion starting with} 43... Kc4 {Marin,Mihail Marin,M: 'It would work perfectly fine here, too.' It would work perfectly fine here, too.} 44. Bb4 Kb3 45. g4 ({Marin,M: 'Passive defence would not do either:' Passive defence would not do either:} 45. Bf8 Kc2 46. Bb4 Kd1 {Marin,M: 'Planning ...Ke2, ...Rf3 followed by preparing the pawn break ...f5-f4.' Planning ...e2, ...f3 followed by preparing the pawn break ...f5-f4.} 47. Kf1 f4 $19) 45... Kc2 46. gxf5 gxf5 47. Bc5 Kd1 48. a4 Ke2 49. a5 Rc3 50. Be3 Ra3 51. Kg3 (51. Bb6 f4 $19) 51... Rxa5 52. Kf4 Rb5 {Marin,M: 'Putting White in some sort of zugzwang.' Putting White in some sort of zugzwang.} (52... Kf1 53. Kf3 {Marin,M: 'slightly complicates matters.' slightly complicates matters.}) 53. Ba7 (53. Kg3 Rb4 54. Bc5 Rb3+ 55. Be3 Rxe3+ 56. fxe3 Kxe3 $19) 53... Kf1 {[%cal Gf1g2]} 54. Kf3 Rb4 55. Bc5 Rc4 56. Bb6 h5 57. Ba7 h4 58. Be3 Kg1 $19) 44. Bf8 $1 {Marin,Mihail: 'Perunovic,Milos: '!''} g5 {Flear,Glenn: 'This turns out to be committal, but I'm not confident enough to know if it's actually a mistake. What else could he try anyway, I'm thinking?' Marin,Mihail: '?!' '?!' '?!' Marin,M: '?!'} 45. Bc5 Rc3 46. Be3 {Flear,Glenn: '!' Flear,Glenn: 'Oh, a surprise choice. The a-pawn is abandoned in order to trade some kingside pawns.' Marin,Mihail: '!' '!' '!' Marin,M: '!' Marin,M: 'Obviously underestimated by Black.' Marin,Mihail: 'Obviously underestimated by Black.'} (46. Bb4 $17 {Marin,Mihail: 'Perunovic,Milos'} Rb3 $140 47. Bf8) 46... h6 (46... Rxa3 {Marin,Mihail: 'Perunovic,Milos'} 47. Bxg5 Kd5 48. Bf4 $11) ({One idea is Marin,M: 'I failed to find a winning plan for Black after' Marin,Mihail: 'I failed to find a winning plan for Black after'} 46... g4 47. hxg4 fxg4 48. a4 (48. Bb6 {Marin,Mihail} Rxa3 {½-½ Cebalo,M (2515)-Nedev,T (2415) Cannes Martinez op