{Fun fact. This was the 19th edition of Karpov Poikovsky Tournament and Bologan was participating for the 18th time! I don't know any other player who has participated in the same tournament for so many years. Local people must really love him there!} 1. d4 {Abramovic,Bosko} Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 b6 4. g3 Bb7 5. Bg2 Be7 6. O-O O-O 7. Re1 Na6 (7... d6 {I was once lucky enough to trap a fellow GM in this line.} 8. Nc3 Ne4 9. Ng5 $1 Nxc3 10. Qc2 $1 $16 {The entire point of e1 is to protect against ...xe2+ in this position.}) 8. Nc3 Ne4 9. Bf4 {On the advice of my coach, I took the decision to play this line at the very last moment. Experience does bring a lot of wisdom!} (9. Bd2 {(Abramovic,Bosko) - 135/173}) 9... Nxc3 10. bxc3 Nb8 {Abramovic,Bosko: 'N'} (10... Be4 {is the most popular move}) 11. e4 d6 {Abramovic,Bosko: 'Diagram [#]'} 12. e5 {Abramovic,Bosko: '!' I felt that White has to act 'fast'. Black doesn't have any long-term weaknesses, so it makes sense to utilise the temporary initiative quickly.} (12. h4 {Abramovic,Bosko}) 12... dxe5 $2 {Horrific. I didn't even consider this move. After this White has total domination} (12... Nd7 {was much more normal} 13. d5 dxe5 14. Nxe5 Nxe5 15. Bxe5 exd5 16. cxd5 {with ideas like g4/d4 and connecting the rooks. White still has some initiative.}) (12... Nc6 {Abramovic,Bosko} 13. d5 exd5 14. exd6 (14. cxd5 Nxe5 15. Nxe5 dxe5 16. Bxe5 Qd7 $11) 14... Bxd6 15. cxd5 Na5 16. Be3 c6 17. Nd4 $1 cxd5 18. Nf5 Qf6 19. Qh5 $36) 13. Nxe5 Bxg2 14. Kxg2 {The main problem of Black's position is the co-ordination. It's not so easy to bring the b8-knight into the game.} Bd6 15. Qf3 {Abramovic,Bosko: ''} Nd7 16. Rad1 {I was tempted with the chance to organise a kingside attack, which could happen after 16...xe5.} (16. Nc6 Qf6 17. Re4 Nb8 18. Ne5 {would be similiar to the game} Bxe5 {Abramovic,Bosko} 19. Rxe5 Nd7 20. Re2 $36) 16... Qe7 {Strange move. Inviting c6 with a tempo?} (16... Bxe5 17. dxe5 (17. Bxe5 {Abramovic,Bosko} Nxe5 18. Rxe5 Qc8 19. d5 $14) 17... Qc8 (17... Qe8 18. Rd4 (18. Bg5 $14 {Abramovic,Bosko})) 18. Rd4 {with ideas of g5-g4/h4.}) 17. Nc6 Qf6 18. Re4 {Abramovic,Bosko: '!'} Kh8 (18... g5 {falls to a cute tactic} 19. Bxg5 $1 Qxg5 20. Rg4) 19. Qe2 {Not the best. Probably it was better to play h4 and gain more space on the kingside. Being 'greedy' is not always bad :)} (19. h4 $1 {When the engine says that the best move is ...a5 or ...a6, It's a sign that something is wrong with Black's position.}) (19. Qh5 $5 {Abramovic,Bosko}) 19... Qg6 {With idea of ...f6.} 20. Bc1 (20. Be5 {This looked prettier, but I didn't want to allow the liberating move ...f5:} f5 21. Rh4 $14) 20... Nf6 $2 {Abramovic,Bosko: '?!' Probably the last mistake. In bad positions the defending side has to walk a very thin line! After this White's pieces co-ordinate with amazing ease.} (20... Rae8 {Again being persistent with the ideas of ...f5 was called for.} 21. Re1 {Abramovic,Bosko: '' The computer's first line is 21...a6 and 22.h3 h6! If I could, I would rationalise them.}) (20... Nb8 {Abramovic,Bosko} 21. Ne5 Bxe5 22. dxe5 Na6 23. Ba3 c5 24. Rg4 Qf5 25. Rf4 Qg6 26. h4 $16) 21. Rh4 {e5 is actually a very serious threat.} Qf5 {Abramovic,Bosko: 'Diagram [#]'} 22. Rd3 $1 g5 23. Rf3 Qg6 24. Ne5 $1 Qg7 {Abramovic,Bosko: 'Diagram [#]'} (24... Bxe5 $2 {Abramovic,Bosko} 25. Qxe5 gxh4 26. Rxf6 Qg7 27. Bh6 $18) 25. Rxf6 $1 {The point of the entire combination.} gxh4 (25... Qxf6 26. Rh5 {It gives a lot of pleasure when you can play such slow moves after sacrificing an exchange :)} Rg8 27. Bxg5 $1 {The black king is way too weak.} (27. h4 $1 {Abramovic,Bosko} gxh4 (27... Bxe5 28. dxe5 Qf5 29. Bxg5 Rg6 30. Bf6+ Rxf6 31. Rxf5 Rxf5 32. g4 Rg8 33. Kh2 Rf4 34. f3 $18) 28. Qe4 Qg7 29. Bh6 $18)) 26. Qf3 {Abramovic,Bosko: '!'} Bxe5 (26... Kg8 {Abramovic,Bosko} 27. Bh6 $18) 27. dxe5 hxg3 28. Bh6 Qg8 29. hxg3 Rad8 30. Qf4 {Black is unable to move any piece! He is helpess against the slow invasion of queen or bishop to f6.} c5 {Abramovic,Bosko} 31. Qh4 Rd7 32. Rf5 f6 33. Bxf8 Qxf8 34. Rxf6 Rf7 35. g4 $18 1-0


