1. e4 {[%emt 0:00:04]} c5 {[%emt 0:00:47]} 2. Nf3 {[%emt 0:00:09]} d6 {[%emt 0:01:07]} 3. Bb5+ {[%emt 0:02:47]} Nd7 {[%emt 0:02:48]} 4. O-O {[%emt 0:06:21]} Ngf6 {[%emt 0:05:10]} 5. Re1 {[%emt 0:00:29]} a6 {[%emt 0:00:10]} 6. Bd3 {[%emt 0:06:12]} (6. Bxd7+ Bxd7 7. e5 dxe5 8. Nxe5 Rc8 9. d3 e6 10. Nc3 Be7 11. Qf3 Bc6 12. Nxc6 Rxc6 13. Bf4 O-O 14. Be5 Nd7 15. Bf4 Nf6 16. Be5 Nd7 17. Bf4 Nf6 18. Be5 {½-½ (18) Tomashevsky,E (2713)-Vitiugov,N (2722) St Petersburg 2017}) 6... b5 {[%emt 0:05:30]} 7. c4 {[%emt 0:04:56]} b4 {[%emt 0:04:35] Sam Collins: 'A new move for us, having previously covered lots of alternatives.'} 8. a3 {[%emt 0:02:25]} bxa3 {[%emt 0:00:11]} ({Van Kampen gives} 8... e5 9. Bc2 Be7 (9... bxa3 10. Rxa3 Be7 (10... g6 11. Ba4 (11. d3 Bg7 12. Ba4 O-O {B.Prince - T.Nguyen, Graz 2017 (1/2-1/2 in 20)} 13. Nc3 $14) 11... Bg7 {M.Mahjoob - K.Tarlev, Rasht 2015 (1/2-1/2 in 45)} 12. d3 $14) 11. d3 O-O 12. Bd2 Qb6 13. Ba5 Qb7 {K.Lagno - A.Ushenina, Khanty-Mansiysk 2014 (1-0 in 44)} 14. Ba4 $5 $14 {with similar play to the game.}) 10. axb4 cxb4 11. d4 O-O 12. Nbd2 $14 {as slightly better for White, an assessment not disturbed by the outcome of M.Sidhant - F.Amonatov, New Delhi 2018 (0-1 in 37).}) 9. Rxa3 {[%emt 0:00:34]} ({I suspect Harika was inspired by the following game:} 9. b3 g6 10. Bxa3 Bg7 11. Nc3 Rb8 12. Rb1 Ng4 13. Bf1 Nde5 $15 {N.Grandelius - S.Lu, Wijk aan Zee 2017 (0-1 in 40). However, cutting off the bishop's route to a4 is the wrong plan.}) 9... e5 {[%emt 0:00:18]} 10. Nc3 {[%emt 0:00:31]} Be7 {[%emt 0:00:19]} 11. Bc2 {[%emt 0:02:33] Sam Collins: '!' Sam Collins: 'Bringing the bishop to a4, which is about as much as you need to know against 7...b4.'} O-O {[%emt 0:00:25]} 12. d3 {[%emt 0:00:14]} Nb8 {[%emt 0:01:33]} 13. Ba4 {[%emt 0:02:12] Sam Collins: 'This was assessed by Robin Van Kampen as slightly better for White, with which I'd agree.'} Bd7 $146 {[%emt 0:02:47]} (13... h6 14. Bd2 Bd7 15. Bxd7 Qxd7 16. Qa4 Qxa4 17. Rxa4 Nc6 18. Rea1 Nb4 19. Ne1 Rab8 20. Nd1 Nd7 21. Ne3 Nb6 22. Ra5 Nc8 23. Bxb4 Rxb4 24. R1a2 {Sam Collins: '' Sam Collins: 'and, as in the text game, Black's queenside weaknesses and passive pieces led to defeat in E.Van den Doel - E.Goudriaan, Germany 2014 (1-0 in 52).'} Bg5 25. Rxa6 Bxe3 26. fxe3 f5 27. exf5 Rxf5 28. Rc6 Rb8 29. Nf3 Rf6 30. Rc7 Re6 31. e4 Re7 32. Rxe7 Nxe7 33. Kf2 Nc6 34. Ke3 Rb3 35. Ra6 Rxd3+ 36. Ke2 Nb4 37. Ra3 Rxa3 38. bxa3 Nc6 39. Nh4 Kf7 40. Nf5 Na5 41. Nxd6+ Ke6 42. Nf5 Nxc4 43. Nxg7+ {Van den Doel,E (2564)-Goudriaan,E (2410) Germany 2014 1-0}) 14. Bg5 {[%emt 0:17:39]} Ra7 {[%emt 0:04:21]} 15. Bxf6 {[%emt 0:07:25]} Bxf6 {[%emt 0:00:43]} 16. Nd5 {[%emt 0:00:02]} Be6 {[%emt 0:02:24]} 17. Qb3 {[%emt 0:00:56]} Bxd5 {[%emt 0:00:58]} 18. cxd5 {[%emt 0:00:14]} Qc7 {[%emt 0:09:09]} 19. Nd2 {[%emt 0:04:13]} Rb7 {[%emt 0:10:45]} 20. Qc3 {[%emt 0:04:20]} Rb4 {[%emt 0:01:41]} 21. Nc4 {[%emt 0:00:12]} Be7 {[%emt 0:00:11]} 22. Rea1 {[%emt 0:01:59] Sam Collins: '' Sam Collins: 'Black has no play. It's not immediately apparent how the white bishop will outperform its black counterpart (aside from dominating the knight on b8), but Vidit's play is deeply instructive.'} g6 {[%emt 0:02:25]} 23. Rb3 {[%emt 0:04:58]} Rxb3 {[%emt 0:01:58]} 24. Bxb3 {[%emt 0:00:39]} Bd8 {[%emt 0:01:27]} ({Going for counterplay with an immediate} 24... f5 $16 {looks like a better practical attempt. White retains the better chances, although} 25. Nxe5 $2 Bf6 $15 {is the wrong direction}) 25. Ba4 {[%emt 0:03:46]} f5 {[%emt 0:02:59]} 26. Ra3 {[%emt 0:03:45]} fxe4 {[%emt 0:02:38]} 27. dxe4 {[%emt 0:00:08]} Qf7 {[%emt 0:01:41]} 28. Qc2 {[%emt 0:02:03]} Bh4 {[%emt 0:10:41]} 29. g3 {[%emt 0:10:04]} Be7 {[%emt 0:00:11] Sam Collins: '+-' Sam Collins: 'Black's demonstration on the kingside has resulted in no gains, while the queenside is about to be opened.'} 30. Rb3 {[%emt 0:00:27]} Qf6 {[%emt 0:00:05]} 31. Rb7 {[%emt 0:01:47]} h5 {[%emt 0:00:05]} 32. h4 {[%emt 0:00:57]} Kh8 {[%emt 0:01:27]} 33. Qe2 {[%emt 0:01:26]} Kg8 {[%emt 0:00:22]} 34. Qe3 {[%emt 0:01:12]} Rd8 {[%emt 0:01:33]} 35. Kg2 {[%emt 0:02:31]} Qf8 {[%emt 0:01:13]} 36. Na5 {[%emt 0:01:51] Sam Collins: '!' Sam Collins: 'The winning plan.'} Rc8 {[%emt 0:03:28]} 37. Nc6 {[%emt 0:00:42]} Bf6 {[%emt 0:02:09]} 38. Qf3 {[%emt 0:00:31]} Nxc6 {[%emt 0:00:26] Sam Collins: 'Such a knight can't be tolerated...'} 39. dxc6 {[%emt 0:00:02] Sam Collins: '...but neither can the weakness on the a2-g8 diagonal.'} Bd8 {[%emt 0:01:30] Sam Collins: '?' Sam Collins: 'Almost the worst move in the position, but against any move White would win huge material very quickly.'} 1-0


