{After a win in the first round I had missed a couple of chances and drew all the games uptill this round. My opponent didn't have a good tournament so I was hoping to score in this game.} 1. d4 {Arsovic,Goran} d6 2. Nf3 g6 3. g3 Bg7 4. Bg2 Nf6 5. O-O O-O 6. c4 Nc6 7. Nc3 e5 8. dxe5 dxe5 9. Bg5 Be6 10. Nd2 {We both were playing pretty fast until this point.} h6 (10... Qb8 11. Qa4 Nd4 12. e3 Nf5 13. Bxf6 Bxf6 14. Nde4 Bg7 15. Nc5 Bc8 16. Rad1 $14) 11. Bxf6 Bxf6 12. Nde4 Be7 13. Qc1 Kg7 {Arsovic,Goran: 'N'} (13... Bxc4 14. Rd1 Qe8 15. Qxh6 Nd4 16. g4) (13... Bg5 {(Arsovic,Goran) - 129/(189)}) 14. Rd1 Qe8 (14... Qc8 {Arsovic,Goran} 15. Nd5 Rb8 16. Nxe7 Nxe7 17. Qc3 f6 18. e3 $14) 15. Nd5 Rc8 (15... Bd8 16. Qc3 (16. e3 f5 17. Nc5 Bc8 18. f4 b6 19. Nb3 e4) (16. Qd2 b6) 16... Nd4 (16... f5 17. Nc5 Bc8 18. Re1 Kh7 19. e4 f4 20. gxf4 exf4 21. e5 f3 22. Bxf3 Qf7 23. Re3 Bg5 24. Rae1 Bxe3 25. Rxe3 $16) 17. Rd2 c6 18. Nf4 Bg4 (18... Bf5 19. Nd6 Qe7 (19... Qd7 20. c5 Bf6 21. e3 exf4 22. exd4 $14) 20. c5 $14) 19. e3 Nf3+ 20. Bxf3 Bxf3 21. Nd6 Qe7 22. e4 Bg4 23. c5 $14) (15... Nd4 {Arsovic,Goran} 16. Qd2 Bxd5 17. cxd5 Nb5 18. Rac1 $14) 16. Nxe7 $146 {This was my planned improvement. It's rare nowadays to get your preparation in! :)} (16. Nec3 Bg5 (16... Bxd5 {Arsovic,Goran} 17. cxd5 Nd4 18. e3 Nb5 $13) (16... f5 {Arsovic,Goran} 17. Nxe7 (17. b3 e4 $132)) 17. e3 f5 18. f4 Bd8) 16... Qxe7 {Arsovic,Goran: 'Diagram [#]'} 17. Nc3 {Arsovic,Goran: '!' Black is already worse now. He can't really avoid crippling of his pawn structure on queenside.} Bxc4 (17... f5 {(Arsovic,Goran) -16.Nec3} 18. Bxc6 {Arsovic,Goran} bxc6 19. b3 $14) (17... Qc5 {Arsovic,Goran} 18. b3 Rfd8 19. Qb2 $14) 18. b3 $1 {It is important to define the bishop's position before capturing on c6.} (18. Bxc6 {gives Black some extra option:} bxc6 19. Qe3 a5 20. Qe4 (20. b3 Bb5 $1 {Black has this extra option with this move order} 21. Nxb5 cxb5 22. a4 bxa4 23. Rxa4 Ra8) 20... Qe6 (20... Qc5 21. Na4 Qb5 22. b3 Be6 23. Rac1 $14) 21. b3 Bb5 22. Nxb5 cxb5 23. Rd5 c6 24. Rxe5 Qf6) 18... Ba6 (18... Be6 19. Bxc6 bxc6 20. Qe3 $14 f6 {Arsovic,Goran} 21. Qxa7 $14) 19. Bxc6 bxc6 20. Qe3 {Arsovic,Goran: ''} Ra8 {I wasn't sure how to prove compensation for the pawn. But it is clear that uncoordinated pieces and damaged pawn structure give White a very comfortable position.} 21. Rac1 $1 (21. Rd2 $6 {allows Black to simplify:} Rfd8 22. Rxd8 Rxd8 23. Qxa7 Qb4 $132) 21... Rfe8 (21... f5 22. Na4 (22. f4 Rf7 23. fxe5) 22... f4 23. gxf4 Rxf4 24. Nc5 Bc8 25. Nd3 $16) 22. Rc2 {I played this quickly. The potential threat of doubling on c or d-files gives White a lot of flexibility in plans.} (22. f3 $5 f5 23. Na4) 22... Bc8 {Black is threatening to co-ordinate his pieces so White should act quickly.} (22... Red8 23. Rxd8 Rxd8 24. Qxa7 Bc8 25. Qe3 $14) 23. Ne4 (23. Na4 Bh3 24. Rxc6 Rad8 {I was afraid that the knight would be out of the game.}) 23... Bf5 {Arsovic,Goran: '?!'} (23... Bh3 24. f3 Rad8 25. Rdc1 $16) (23... Bd7 {Although this looks passive it was the most tenacious.} 24. Rdc1 a5 (24... f6 25. Nc5 Bf5 26. Rc4 $14) 25. Rc4 (25. Nc5 $14 {Arsovic,Goran}) 25... h5 $14) 24. Rxc6 Rad8 25. Rdc1 Qb4 (25... Qa3 {I was more worried about this move, but even here White has a nice advantage with few good moves:} 26. Nc3 Qb2 27. f3 $1 $16 {and Black's weak pawns are hard to defend.}) 26. R6c4 {Not the best move.} (26. Nc3 $1 {In good positions sometimes simple moves are the best! :)} Qd4 (26... Rd7 27. Qxa7) 27. Rxc7 Rc8 28. Nb5 $1 $16) (26. Nf6 {I was very tempted to make this work and spent most of the time here. I played pretty fast uptill this point.} Re7 27. g4 Bc8 {It looked very nice to force Black's pieces back, but it was hard to progress.} 28. g5 Qf4 $132) 26... Qb6 27. Nc5 (27. Nc3 {It looked very anti positional to play such a move. But it was also a possibility} Rd4 28. Na4 Qd6 29. Rxd4 Qxd4 30. Rxc7 Qxe3 31. fxe3 $16) 27... Rd5 28. Qc3 $6 {I started losing the thread at this point.} (28. Qf3 {was my original intention but after} Rd4 $1 $132 {Black has counterplay.}) (28. Kg2 $1 Red8 29. h3 $16 {is the computer|s suggestion. White slowly pushes Black back.}) 28... Qd6 29. e4 $6 (29. g4 $1 Bc8 30. Ne4 Rd1+ 31. Kg2 Bb7 32. f3 $16) 29... Rd1+ 30. Kg2 Bg4 (30... Bc8 $1 31. Rxd1 Qxd1 32. Qc2 Qh5 $1 $132) 31. Rxd1 (31. h3 {was my original plan but suddenly I realized that Black can play} Be2 $1 32. Rxd1 Qxd1 33. Qc1 $1 Bf3+ 34. Kh2 Rd8 35. Qxd1 Rxd1 36. g4 {and it's still equal.}) 31... Qxd1 32. Qd3 $1 {White's position was so good that even after a few inaccuracies White still holds some advantage.} (32. Qe3 $6 {Arsovic,Goran} Be2 33. Rc1 Bf3+ 34. Kh3 Bg4+ $11) 32... Rd8 (32... Qe1 33. Rc2 $16) (32... Qxd3 33. Nxd3 Be2 34. Rc3 Bxd3 35. Rxd3 $14 Re6 36. Rc3 Ra6 37. a4 c6 $11 38. Kf3) 33. Qxd1 Bxd1 $6 {I was a bit scared to see this move as I cannot consolidate with c2. Fortunately, I had a better option!} (33... Rxd1 34. Rc2 (34. Ra4 Be2 35. f4 Rc1) 34... Kf8 {Arsovic,Goran} 35. f3 Bc8 36. Kf2 $14) 34. Ra4 $1 {Arsovic,Goran: '' Now it's hard to defend Black's pawns.} g5 (34... Be2 35. Rxa7 Rd1 36. Rxc7 g5 37. g4 $1 Bxg4 38. f3 $18) 35. h3 h5 {Arsovic,Goran: 'Diagram [#]'} 36. g4 {Arsovic,Goran: '!'} h4 $6 {Black was hoping to build a net around the king but it turns out to be too slow.} (36... hxg4 37. hxg4 Rd2 $1 (37... Bxg4 38. Rxa7 Rd2 (38... Rc8 {Arsovic,Goran} 39. Kg3 $16) 39. a4 Bd1 40. Rxc7 g4 41. Kg3 Ra2 42. Rd7 Bf3 43. Nd3 Kf6 44. Rd6+ Ke7 45. Ra6 $16) 38. Rxa7 Rc2 39. b4 Bxg4 40. a4 Rc3 41. Rxc7 $16) 37. Rxa7 Be2 38. Rxc7 Rd1 39. Nd7 $1 {Arsovic,Goran: '+-' I believe my opponent missed this important move.} Bf1+ (39... Bd3 {Arsovic,Goran} 40. Nxe5 Bxe4+ 41. f3 Bd5 (41... Rd2+ 42. Kg1 Bg6 43. a4 $18) 42. Rc2 $18) 40. Kh2 Rd2 (40... Be2 41. Nxe5 Kf6 42. Rc2 Re1 43. Rc5 Ke6 44. Rd5 f6 45. Nc6) 41. Nxe5 {Now the rest it easy :)} Kf6 (41... Rxf2+ {Arsovic,Goran} 42. Kg1 Rf4 43. Nxf7 $18 (43. Rxf7+ $18)) 42. Nxf7 Rxa2 43. e5+ Kg6 44. Nh8+ Kh6 45. Nf7+ (45. Rf7 Ra6) (45. e6 Rxf2+ 46. Kg1 Rg2+ 47. Kh1) 45... Kg6 46. Nd6 Re2 (46... Bd3 47. e6 (47. Rf7)) 47. Rc1 {I was very relieved to score a nice win after four consecutive draws!} 1-0


