{Sagar,Shah: 'If ever you were in doubt about how important an advantage in space is then you should have a look at this game!  Arsovic,Zoran: 'Sagar Shah: 'If ever you were in doubt about how important an advantage in space is then you should have a look at this game! '''} 1. d4 {Sagar,Shah Sagar,Shah: 'Arsovic,Zoran Arsovic,Zoran: 'Sagar Shah''} Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nf3 Bg7 4. e3 O-O 5. Be2 {Sagar,Shah: 'This line with not committing your knight to c3 is becoming quite popular against Grünfeld experts. ...d5 now would not be so great due to cxd5 xd5 and e4, and there is no knight to exchange on c3. Arsovic,Zoran: 'Sagar Shah: 'This line with not committing your knight to c3 is becoming quite popular against Grünfeld experts. ...d5 now would not be so great due to cxd5 xd5 and e4, and there is no knight to exchange on c3.'''} d6 (5... c5 $5 {(Sagar,Shah) Arsovic,Zoran: 'Sagar Shah' A possible decision could be to transpose into a Benoni structure where e3 is not such a dangerous line.}) 6. O-O Nbd7 7. Nc3 e5 8. Qc2 Re8 9. Re1 exd4 $146 {Sagar,Shah: 'Arsovic,Zoran: 'N' 'N''} (9... e4 10. Nd2 Qe7 {Sagar,Shah: 'is a reversed King's Indian Attack. This is definitely preferable to exd4. The attack might not be very dangerous, but it is better than what happened in the game. Arsovic,Zoran: 'Sagar Shah: 'is a reversed King's Indian Attack. This is definitely preferable to exd4. The attack might not be very dangerous, but it is better than what happened in the game.'''} 11. b4 {Sagar,Shah: 'Arsovic,Zoran'} (11. f3 {Sagar,Shah: 'Arsovic,Zoran'} exf3 12. Nxf3 c5 $132) 11... c6 12. b5 c5 $13) (9... c6 {- 126/188 Sagar,Shah: '(Arsovic,Zoran) - 126/188'}) 10. exd4 (10. Nxd4 {Sagar,Shah: 'Arsovic,Zoran'} a5 11. b3 Nc5 $11) 10... Nb6 11. Bf4 {Sagar,Shah: '' '' '' '' Sagar,Shah: 'Arsovic,Zoran: 'Sagar Shah: '''' Sagar,Shah: 'White now has a static advantage of space which is difficult to neutralise due to the symmetrical pawn structure. Arsovic,Zoran: 'Sagar Shah: 'White now has a static advantage of space which is difficult to neutralise due to the symmetrical pawn structure.'''} Bf5 12. Bd3 Bxd3 (12... Nxc4 $6 {(Sagar,Shah) Arsovic,Zoran: 'Sagar Shah'} 13. Bxf5 gxf5 14. Qxf5 $16) 13. Qxd3 $14 {Sagar,Shah: 'Arsovic,Zoran: '' '''} Qd7 14. b3 Rxe1+ 15. Rxe1 Re8 16. Rxe8+ Qxe8 17. h3 {Sagar,Shah: 'So what exactly is White's advantage? In one simple word it is - space! White has so much space in this position that it is extremely difficult for Black to find a constructive plan. And Ni Hua is pretty good at converting such dry technical positions. Arsovic,Zoran: 'Sagar Shah: 'So what exactly is White's advantage? In one simple word it is - space! White has so much space in this position that it is extremely difficult for Black to find a constructive plan. And Ni Hua is pretty good at converting such dry technical positions.'''} a6 18. a4 Nbd7 19. a5 {Sagar,Shah: 'Gaining further space. Arsovic,Zoran: 'Sagar Shah: 'Gaining further space.'''} Qd8 (19... Qe6 {(Sagar,Shah) Arsovic,Zoran: 'Sagar Shah' with the idea of c6 followed by d5 would have at least brought some active possibilities to the second player.} 20. b4 c6 21. b5 h6 22. bxa6 bxa6 23. Kf1 (23. c5 dxc5 24. Qxa6 cxd4 $132) 23... Ne8 $14 {[%cal Ge8c7] White's advantage still exists but it is not as huge as in the game.}) 20. b4 b6 $6 {Sagar,Shah: 'Tired of waiting passively, Vidit lashes out, but now the a6-pawn becomes weak.  Arsovic,Zoran: 'Sagar Shah: 'Tired of waiting passively, Vidit lashes out, but now the a6-pawn becomes weak. '''} (20... Nf8 {Sagar,Shah: 'Arsovic,Zoran'} 21. Be3 h6 22. b5 $14) 21. axb6 Nxb6 22. Bg5 Qa8 (22... h6 23. Bxf6 Qxf6 {Sagar,Shah: 'Arsovic,Zoran'} (23... Bxf6 24. c5 {Sagar,Shah: '' '' '' '' Sagar,Shah: 'Arsovic,Zoran: 'Sagar Shah: ''''} dxc5 {Sagar,Shah: 'Arsovic,Zoran'} 25. bxc5 Nd7 (25... Nd5 $6 26. Nxd5 Qxd5 27. Qxa6 $16) 26. Qc4 $14) 24. c5 dxc5 25. bxc5 Nd7 26. Nd5 Qd8 27. Qc4 $14) 23. Bxf6 Bxf6 {Diagram [#] Sagar,Shah: 'Arsovic,Zoran: 'Diagra